Name: kEnableHangWatcher
Documentation:
Determines if the HangWatcher is activated. When false the HangWatcher
thread never started.

Name: kUseThreadPoolForMediaStreamVideoTaskRunner
Documentation:
Causes MediaStreamVideoSource video frames to be transported on a
SequencedTaskRunner backed by the threadpool instead of the normal IO thread.

Name: kAvoidH2Reprioritization
Documentation: Disable H2 reprioritization, in order to measure its impact.

Name: kWebrtcMediaCapabilitiesParameters
Documentation:
Used to set a few tunable parameters for the WebRTC Media Capabilities
implementation.

Name: kTailoredSecurityUpdatedMessages
Documentation: Enable new updated strings and icons for the Tailored Security dialogs.

Name: kBrowsingTopicsXHR
Documentation:
Enables the deprecatedBrowsingTopics XHR attribute. For this feature to take
effect, the main Topics feature has to be enabled first (i.e.
`kBrowsingTopics` is enabled, and, either a valid Origin Trial token exists
or `kPrivacySandboxAdsAPIsOverride` is enabled.)

Name: kSidePanelJourneys
Documentation: Enables Side Panel Journeys.

Name: kAutofillVirtualCardsOnTouchToFillAndroid
Documentation:
Controls whether virtual card suggestions are shown on the touch to fill
surface for credit cards on Android.

Name: kScrollableTabStripOverflow
Documentation:
Enables different methods of overflow when scrolling tabs in tabstrip
https://crbug.com/951078

Name: kRenderSurfaceCommonAncestorClip
Documentation:
Whether RenderSurface::common_ancestor_clip_id() is used to clip to the
common ancestor clip when any contributing layer escapes the clip of the
render surface's owning effect.

Name: kDCompDebugVisualization
Documentation:
Enable DComp debug visualizations. This can be useful to determine how much
work DWM is doing when we update our tree.

Please be aware that some of these visualizations result in quickly flashing
colors.

Name: kThrottleInstallingServiceWorker
Documentation:
Enable throttling of fetch() requests from service workers in the
installing state.  The limit of 3 was chosen to match the limit
in background main frames.  In addition, trials showed that this
did not cause excessive timeouts and resulted in a net improvement
in successful install rate on some platforms.

Name: kSyncSessionOnVisibilityChanged
Documentation:
If enabled, triggers a synchronisation when WebContentsObserver's
-OnVisibilityChanged method is called.

Name: kPaymentHandlerRequireLinkHeader
Documentation:
If enabled, the payment method manifest fetch for Payment Handler must go via
a Link header with rel="payment-method-manifest".

Name: kFrequencyCappingForOverlayPopupDetection
Documentation:
Enables the frequency capping for detecting overlay popups. Overlay-popups
are the interstitials that pop up and block the main content of the page.

Name: kIdleDetection
Documentation:
This is intended as a kill switch for the Idle Detection feature. To enable
this feature, the experimental web platform features flag should be set,
or the site should obtain an Origin Trial token.

Name: kDynamicSchedulerForDraw
Documentation: Used by Viz to parameterize adjustments to scheduler deadlines.

Name: kAutofillKeyboardAccessory
Documentation:
When enabled, Autofill suggestions are displayed in the keyboard accessory
instead of the regular popup.

Name: kAutofillUpdateChromeSettingsLinkToGPayWeb
Documentation:
When enabled, GPay-related links direct to the newer GPay Web site instead of
the legacy Payments Center.

Name: kSurfaceSyncFullscreenKillswitch
Documentation:
To disable the updated fullscreen handling of the companion Viz
SurfaceSyncThrottling flag. Disabling this will restore the base
SurfaceSyncThrottling path.

Name: kEncryptedReportingFeature
Documentation:
Feature to enable/disable encryption.
By default encryption is enabled and supported by server.
Disabled only for testing/stress purposes.

Name: kCustomizeChromeColorExtraction
Documentation:
If enabled, Chrome theme color will be set to match the NTP background
on NTP Customize Chrome background change.

Name: kDrawCutoutEdgeToEdge
Documentation: Enable drawing under System Bars within DisplayCutout.

Name: kOverlayFullscreenVideo
Documentation: Only used for disabling overlay fullscreen (aka SurfaceView) in Clank.

Name: kHttpsUpgrades
Documentation: Enables automatically upgrading main frame navigations to HTTPS.

Name: kContextMenuCopyVideoFrame
Documentation: Enables the "Copy Video Frame" context menu item.

Name: kTPCDAdHeuristicSubframeRequestTagging
Documentation:
Enables ad tagging decisions to be propagated to network requests by removing
an optimization which parallelizes filter list checks and navigation request
start.

Name: kCanvasFreeMemoryWhenHidden
Documentation: Whether to aggressively free resources for canvases in background pages.

Name: kEnableImageSearchSidePanelFor3PDse
Documentation:
Enables the image search side panel experience for third party default search
engines

Name: kCdmStorageDatabaseMigration
Documentation:
This guards between using the MediaLicense* code path and the CdmStorage*
code path for storing Cdm data. This will be enabled by default as we do not
want the CdmStorageDatabase to be used solely, and instead when we conduct
our experiments, we will enable kCdmStorageDatabase to flow the migration.
Later when the migration is finished, we will remove this flag so that
kCdmStorageDatabase serves as the only flag. Refer to
go/cdm-storage-migration-details for more details.

Name: kServiceWorkerBypassFetchHandlerHashStrings
Documentation:
The set of ServiceWorker to bypass while making navigation request.
They are represented by a comma separated list of HEX encoded SHA256 hash of
the ServiceWorker's scripts.
e.g.
9685C8DE399237BDA6FF3AD0F281E9D522D46BB0ECFACE05E98D2B9AAE51D1EF,
20F0D78B280E40C0A17ABB568ACF4BDAFFB9649ADA75B0675F962B3F4FC78EA4

Name: kTabSearchFeedback
Documentation: Enables the tab search submit feedback button.

Name: kCrashBrowserOnAnyChildMismatch
Documentation:
Crash the browser process if a child process is created which does not match
the browser process regardless of whether the browser package appears to have
changed.

Name: kTFLiteLanguageDetectionIgnoreEnabled
Documentation:
Controls whether the TFLite-based language detection is computed, but ignored
and the CLD3 version is used instead.

Name: kNetUnusedIdleSocketTimeout
Documentation: Changes the timeout after which unused sockets idle sockets are cleaned up.

Name: kPrivacySandboxAggregationService
Documentation: Enables the Aggregation Service. See crbug.com/1207974.

Name: kAutofillUseNewSectioningMethod
Documentation:
Controls whether to use the combined heuristic and the autocomplete section
implementation for section splitting or not. See https://crbug.com/1076175.

Name: kProactivelyThrottleLowPriorityRequests
Documentation:
When kProactivelyThrottleLowPriorityRequests is enabled,
resource scheduler proactively throttles low priority requests to avoid
network contention with high priority requests that may arrive soon.

Name: kTreatUnsafeDownloadsAsActive
Documentation:
Disable downloads of unsafe file types over insecure transports if initiated
from a secure page. As of M89, mixed downloads are blocked on all platforms.

Name: kForceGoogleSafeSearchForSupervisedUsers
Documentation: Forces Safe Search for supervised users.

Name: kWebUITabStrip
Documentation:
Enables a web-based tab strip. See https://crbug.com/989131. Note this
feature only works when the ENABLE_WEBUI_TAB_STRIP buildflag is enabled.

Name: kBlockingDownloadsInAdFrameWithoutUserActivation
Documentation:
Enable intervention for download that was initiated from or occurred in an ad
frame without user activation.

Name: kCr2023ActionChips
Documentation:
If enabled, uses the Chrome Refresh 2023 design's shape for action chips in
the omnibox suggestion popup.

Name: kAndroidApproximateLocationPermissionSupport
Documentation: Alphabetical:

Name: kFedCmMetricsEndpoint
Documentation: Enables usage of the FedCM API with metrics endpoint at the same time.

Name: kVaapiEnforceVideoMinMaxResolution
Documentation:
Reject creation of encode/decode VAContexts when the requested resolution is
outside the enumerated minimum and maximum. TODO(b/171041334): Remove and
enable by default once the ARC++ hw codecs issue is fixed.

Name: kUrgentPageDiscarding
Documentation: Whether tabs are discarded under high memory pressure.

Name: kWebAssemblyDynamicTiering
Documentation: Enable WebAssembly dynamic tiering (only tier up hot functions).

Name: kEarlyEstablishGpuChannel
Documentation: Enable establishing the GPU channel early in renderer startup.

Name: kWebApkInstallFailureRetry
Documentation:
Allow user to retry install WebAPK with the failure notification if the
initial install failed. This needs to be used with
|kWebApkInstallFailureNotification| Enabled.

Name: kRevokeMediaSourceObjectURLOnAttach
Documentation:
Approach original pre-REC MSE object URL autorevoking behavior, though await
actual attempt to use the object URL for attachment to perform revocation.
This will hopefully reduce runtime memory bloat for pages that do not
explicitly detach their HTMLME+MSE object collections nor explicitly revoke
the object URLs used to attach HTMLME+MSE. When disabled, revocation only
occurs when application explicitly revokes the object URL, or upon the
execution context teardown for the MediaSource object. When enabled,
revocation occurs upon successful start of attachment of HTMLME to the object
URL. Note, rather than immediately scheduling a task to revoke upon the URL's
creation, as at least one other browser does and the original File API
pattern used to follow, this delay until attachment start enables new
scenarios that could use the object URL for attaching HTMLME+MSE cross-thread
(MSE-in-workers), where there could be significant delay between the worker
thread creation of the object URL and the main thread usage of the object URL
for starting attachment to HTMLME.

Name: kExperimentalFlingAnimation
Documentation: Keep sorted!

Name: kIgnoreSyncEncryptionKeysLongMissing
Documentation:
Causes Sync to ignore updates encrypted with keys that have been missing for
too long from this client; Sync will proceed normally as if those updates
didn't exist.

Name: kHashRealTimeOverOhttp
Documentation:
For hash-prefix real-time lookup requests that are triggered by the lookup
mechanism experiment (see kSafeBrowsingLookupMechanismExperiment), enables
sending the requests over OHTTP to anonymize the source of the requests.

Name: kUseMapRectForPixelMovement
Documentation: Kill switch for using MapRect() to compute filter pixel movement.

Name: kAutofillEnableEmailOtpForVcnYellowPath
Documentation:
When enabled, if the user encounters the yellow path (challenge path) in the
VCN retrieval flow and the server denotes that the card is eligible for email
OTP authentication, email OTP authentication will be offered as one of the
challenge options.

Name: kBrowserVerifiedUserActivationMouse
Documentation: When enabled, mouse user activation will be verified by the browser side.

Name: kPasswordReuseDetectionEnabled
Documentation: Enables password reuse detection.

Name: kWebAuthnICloudKeychainForInactiveWithDrive
Documentation: Enabled in M118. Remove in or after M121.

Name: kNavigationPredictorEnablePreconnectOnSameDocumentNavigations
Documentation: Enables triggering of same-origin preconnects on same-document navigations.

Name: kAutofillServerCommunication
Documentation:
Enables or Disables (mostly for hermetic testing) autofill server
communication. The URL of the autofill server can further be controlled via
the autofill-server-url param. The given URL should specify the complete
autofill server API url up to the parent "directory" of the "query" and
"upload" resources.
i.e., https://other.autofill.server:port/tbproxy/af/

Name: kWebRtcThreadsUseResourceEfficientType
Documentation:
If enabled, the WebRTC_* threads in peerconnection module will use
kResourceEfficient thread type.

Name: kMacCoreLocationBackend
Documentation:
Enables usage of the CoreLocation API for LocationProvider instead of
NetworkLocationProvider for macOS or iOS.

Name: kQueueBlockingGestureScrolls
Documentation:
When enabled, gesture scroll updates that hit a JS touch handlers
will be queued normally on CC, enabling coalescing and consistent
input handling.

Name: kWebViewSurfaceControl
Documentation: Hardware Overlays for WebView.

Name: kBluetoothFlossTelephony
Documentation: Enables/disables the bluetooth telephony feature for floss

Name: kBackForwardCacheEntryTimeout
Documentation:
Set a time limit for the page to enter the cache. Disabling this prevents
flakes during testing.

Name: kUserLevelMemoryPressureSignalOn4GbDevices
Documentation: (for Android 4GB devices)

Name: kOverlayScrollbar
Documentation:
Enables or disables overlay scrollbars in Blink (i.e. web content) on Aura
or Linux.  The status of native UI overlay scrollbars is determined in
PlatformStyle::CreateScrollBar. Does nothing on Mac.

Name: kPrivacyGuidePreload
Documentation:
Enables or disables the Privacy Guide preload card update of the Privacy
Guide feature in Chrome Settings. Also, this requires the PrivacyGuide3
feature to be enabled as well.

Name: kAlpsClientHintParsing
Documentation: Whether ALPS parsing is on for client hint parsing specifically.

Name: kAutofillPopupDoesNotOverlapWithContextMenu
Documentation: Controls whether the autofill popup is hidden when the context menu is open.

Name: kInMemoryCodeCache
Documentation: A feature flag for the memory-backed code cache.

Name: kLowPriorityAsyncScriptExecution
Documentation:
If enabled, async scripts will be run on a lower priority task queue.
See https://crbug.com/1348467.

Name: kSupportPartitionedBlobUrl
Documentation:
Whether to use the new code paths needed to support partitioning Blob URLs.
This exists as a kill-switch in case an issue is identified with the Blob
URL implementation that causes breakage.

Name: kV8MinorMS
Documentation: Enables MinorMC young generation garbage collector.

Name: kCodeCacheDeletionWithoutFilter
Documentation: When enabled, code cache does not use a browsing_data filter for deletions.

Name: kWebAuthnPrelinkPlayServices
Documentation: Get caBLE pre-linking information from Play Services

Name: kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsDeprecationTrial
Documentation:
Enables use of the PrivateNetworkAccessNonSecureContextsAllowed deprecation
trial. This is a necessary yet insufficient condition: documents that wish to
make use of the trial must additionally serve a valid origin trial token.

Name: kGreaseUACH
Documentation:
Determines if an extra brand version pair containing possibly escaped double
quotes and escaped backslashed should be added to the Sec-CH-UA header
(activated by kUserAgentClientHint)

Name: kSegmentationPlatformOptimizationTargetSegmentationDummy
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling OptimizationTargetSegmentationDummy segment.

Name: kVisualSearchSuggestions
Documentation: Enables visual search capabilities for the companion.

Name: kNtpHistoryClustersModuleFetchClustersUntilExhausted
Documentation:
If enabled, the History Clusters module will attempt to fetch clusters until
it has enough clusters for the module or the History Clusters service says
that all visits have been exhausted.

Name: kConsolidatedMovementXY
Documentation: When enabled, event.movement is calculated in blink instead of in browser.

Name: kAutofillEnableMovingGPayLogoToTheRightOnClank
Documentation:
When enabled, the GPay logo will be moved to the right side in payments
autofill dialogs and bubbles on clank.

Name: kInstallableAmbientBadgeMessage
Documentation: Enables or disables the installable ambient badge message.

Name: kMediaCastOverlayButton
Documentation: Display the Cast overlay button on the media controls.

Name: kWebIdentityDigitalCredentials
Documentation: Enables the Digital Credential API.

Name: kKeepRvfcFrameAlive
Documentation:
Takes a reference on a video frame, keeping it alive during the duration of a
video.requestVideoFrameCallback call. Doesn't change anything to the API for
now, as this is only used to measure the potential impact of keeping frames
alive for longer. See crbug.com/1259784.

Name: kShareThisTabInsteadButtonGetDisplayMedia
Documentation:
Controls whether a "Share this tab instead" button should be shown for
getDisplayMedia captures. Note: This flag does not control if the "Share this
tab instead" button is shown for chrome.desktopCapture captures.

Name: kSyncPasswordCleanUpAccidentalBatchDeletions
Documentation: Flag to enable clean up of password deletions that may be unintentional.

Name: kVaapiLowPowerEncoderGen9x
Documentation: Enable VA-API hardware low power encoder for all codecs on intel Gen9x gpu.

Name: kRenderDocument
Documentation: Enable using the RenderDocument.

Name: kDisableBlackholeOnNoNewNetwork
Documentation:
Enables whether blackhole detector should be disabled during connection
migration and there is no available network.

Name: kWebAuthnRequireEasyAccessorFieldsInJSON
Documentation:
Require the "easy accessor" fields to be provided in JSON attestation
responses. Otherwise the fields are only checked if provided.

Name: kFocusFollowsCursor
Documentation: Enables focus follow follow cursor (sloppyfocus).

Name: kUserBypassUI
Documentation: Feature to enable the User Bypass UI.

Name: kStrictDownloadTimeout
Documentation:
Controls whether the download inspection timeout is applied over the entire
request, or just the network communication.

Name: kPreferNonShortcutMatchesWhenDeduping
Documentation:
When enabled, deduping prefers non-shortcut provider matches, while still
treating fuzzy provider matches as the least preferred.

Name: kEncryptedClientHello
Documentation:
Enables the TLS Encrypted ClientHello feature.
https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/draft-ietf-tls-esni-13

Name: kDeferredSyncStartupCustomDelay
Documentation: Customizes the delay of a deferred sync startup.

Name: kNtpRecipeTasksModule
Documentation: If enabled, recipe tasks module will be shown.

Name: kImprovedSemanticsActivityIndicators
Documentation: Hide activity indicators if a permission is no longer used.

Name: kEnableLatencyLogging
Documentation: Enables Latency logging for the LensStandalone feature.

Name: kThreadedScrollPreventRenderingStarvation
Documentation:
Finch flag for preventing rendering starvation during threaded scrolling.
With this feature enabled, the existing delay-based rendering anti-starvation
applies, and the compositor task queue priority is controlled with the
`kCompositorTQPolicyDuringThreadedScroll` `FeatureParam`.

Name: kFencedFramesM120FeaturesPart1
Documentation:
Enable the new fenced frame-related features in M120. (These are
conditionally dependent on other fenced frame-related feature flags being
enabled.)
Part 1:
* Extra format for ad size macro substitution:
  ${AD_WIDTH} and ${AD_HEIGHT}, on top of the previous
  {%AD_WIDTH%} and {%AD_HEIGHT%}.
* Input validation (no disallowed URI component characters) in
  registerAdMacro keys and values.
* Send automatic beacons to all registered destinations without requiring
  event data to be in place.

Name: kAndroidAutofillViewStructureWithFormHierarchyLayer
Documentation:
Adds an additional hierarchy layer for forms into the `ViewStructure` that
is passed to Android's `AutofillManager`.
If the feature is disabled, AutofillProvider.java returns a `ViewStructure`
of depth 1: All form field elements are represented as child nodes of the
filled `ViewStructure`.
If the feature is enabled, there is an additional hierarchy level:
* The child nodes of the filled `ViewStructure` correspond to forms.
* The child nodes of nodes representing forms correspond to form field
  elements of the respective form.

Name: kInsecureDownloadWarnings
Documentation: Show warnings on downloads not delivered over HTTPS.

Name: kUseMultiPlaneFormatForSoftwareVideo
Documentation:
Enables creating single shared image and mailbox for multi-planar formats for
software video decoders.

Name: kOptimizationGuidePersonalizedFetching
Documentation: Enables fetching personalized metadata from Optimization Guide Service.

Name: kExtensionTelemetryReportContactedHosts
Documentation: Enables reporting of remote hosts contacted by extensions in telemetry.

Name: kAsyncCheck
Documentation: Note: this feature is a no-op on non-Android platforms.

Documentation:
Partitions Network Error Logging and Reporting API data by
NetworkAnonymizationKey. Also partitions all reports generated by other
consumers of the reporting API. Applies the NetworkAnonymizationKey to
reports uploads as well.

When disabled, the main entry points of the reporting and NEL services ignore
NetworkAnonymizationKey parameters, and they're cleared while loading from
the cache, but internal objects can be created with them (e.g., endpoints),
for testing.

Name: kPermuteTLSExtensions
Documentation:
Enables permuting TLS extensions in the ClientHello, to reduce the risk of
non-compliant servers ossifying parts of the ClientHello and interfering with
deployment of future security improvements.

Name: kSkipUndecryptablePasswords
Documentation:
Displays at least the decryptable and never saved logins in the password
manager

Name: kSetTimeoutWithoutClamp
Documentation:
If enabled, the setTimeout(..., 0) will not clamp to 1ms.
Tracking bug: https://crbug.com/402694.

Name: kCanvas2DImageChromium
Documentation:
If Canvas2D Image Chromium is allowed, this feature controls whether it is
enabled.

Name: kEagerSurfaceGarbageCollection
Documentation:
If enabled, do not rely on surface garbage collection to happen
periodically, but trigger it eagerly, to avoid missing calls.

Name: kSquareSuggestIcons
Documentation:
If enabled, adds a grey square background to search icons, and makes answer
icon square instead of round.

 `OmniboxSquareSuggestIconWeather`. Clean up when that param launches and
 reaches stable.

show for a user whose google account has sync turned on. This feature helps
run the tailored security logic for users where the integration failed in the
past.

Name: kContextualPageActionPriceTracking
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling price tracking action feature.

Name: kMbiCompositorTaskRunnerPerAgentSchedulingGroup
Documentation:
If enabled, per-AgentGroupScheduler CompositorTaskRunner will be used instead
of per-MainThreadScheduler CompositorTaskRunner.

Name: kUseParallelRequestsForQUIC
Documentation: Whether parallel download is used for QUIC connections.

Name: kRawDraw

Name: kOptimizationGuideMetadataValidation
Documentation: Enables the validation of optimization guide metadata.

Documentation:

Tracker: https://crbug.com/1451889

Name: kSignedExchangeReportingForDistributors
Documentation:
Signed Exchange Reporting for distributors
https://www.chromestatus.com/feature/5687904902840320

Name: kAutofillDisableShadowHeuristics
Documentation:
Kill switch for computing heuristics other than the active ones
(GetActivePatternSource()).

Name: kFedCmWithoutThirdPartyCookies
Documentation: Enables usage of the FedCM API without third party cookies at the same time.

Name: kPreferCompositingToLCDText

Whether we should composite a PLSA (paint layer scrollable area) even if it
means losing lcd text.

Name: kV8MegaDomIC
Documentation: Enables faster DOM methods for megamorphic ICs

Name: kNoStatePrefetchHoldback
Documentation: Feature which holdbacks NoStatePrefetch on all surfaces.

Name: kCompressParkableStrings
Documentation:
Disabling this will cause parkable strings to never be compressed.
This is useful for headless mode + virtual time. Since virtual time advances
quickly, strings may be parked too eagerly in that mode.

Name: kTpcdHeuristicsGrants
Documentation:
Enables writing and reading temporary storage access grants from 3PCD
heuristics.

Name: kExtensionTelemetryPotentialPasswordTheft
Documentation:
Enables collection of potential password theft data and uploads
telemetry reports to SB servers.

Name: kBufferQueueImageSetPurgeable
Documentation:
Used to gate calling SetPurgeable on OutputPresenter::Image from
SkiaOutputDeviceBufferQueue.

Name: kFledgeBiddingAndAuctionServer
Documentation:
See
https://github.com/WICG/turtledove/blob/main/FLEDGE_browser_bidding_and_auction_API.md

Name: kFeedImageMemoryCacheSizePercentage
Documentation:
Feature that allows tuning the size of the image memory cache. Value is a
percentage of the maximum size calculated for the device.

Name: kAudioWorkletThreadRealtimePriority
Documentation:
A server-side switch for the kRealtimeAudio thread type of
RealtimeAudioWorkletThread object. This can be controlled by a field trial,
it will use the kNormal type thread when disabled.

Name: kOmniboxCR23SteadyStateIcons
Documentation:
If enabled, Omnibox LHS and RHS icons are updated to match CR23
guidelines.

Name: kLensRegionSearchStaticPage
Documentation: Enables launching the region search experience in a new tab with WebUI.

Name: kOnDeviceClusteringKeywordFiltering
Documentation: Specifies how keywords get filtered and added to a cluster.

Name: kDisablePasswordsDropdownForCvcFields
Documentation:
Disables fallback filling if the server or the autocomplete attribute says it
is a credit card field.

Name: kFedCmDomainHint

Enables usage of the FedCM DomainHint feature. ChromeStatus entry:
https://chromestatus.com/feature/5202286040580096

Name: kBackForwardCacheMediaSessionService
Documentation:
Allows pages that created a MediaSession service to stay eligible for the
back/forward cache.

Name: kLocalNetworkAccessAllowPotentiallyTrustworthySameOrigin
Documentation:
Allow potentially trustworthy same origin local network requests without
preflights.

Name: kMmapLanguageDetectionModel
Documentation: Controls whether mmap is used to load the language detection model.

Name: kCorrectFloatExtensionTestForWebGL
Documentation:
Enable the correction testing for float extension for webgl version 1.
This is simply a killswitch in case we need to restore original behavior.

Name: kAnnouncementNotification
Documentation: Whether to enable announcement notification system.

Name: kAutofillEnableCardArtImage
Documentation:
When enabled, card art images (instead of network icons) will be shown in

Name: kNtpComprehensiveThemeRealbox
Documentation:
If enabled, Comprehensive Theming color changes will be applied to the

Name: kJavaScriptChangeArrayByCopy

Name: kWebUIOmniboxPopup

overrides kEnforceRevocationChecking.

Name: kFedCmAuthz
Documentation: Enables usage of the FedCM Authz API.

Name: kNtpPhotosModuleSplitSvgOptInArtWork
Documentation:
If enabled, the single svg image show in Photos opt-in screen will be
replaced by constituent images to support i18n.

Name: kNtpHistoryClustersModule
Documentation: If enabled, the History clusters module will be shown.

Name: kNonUniformityValidationFeature

Used to assess the reliability of field trial data by sending artificial

Name: kJavaScriptRegExpUnicodeSets

Name: kRestorePrimaryAccountInfo
Documentation: Internal feature - exposed only unit testing.

Documentation:
Enables Cross-Origin Opener Policy (COOP).
https://gist.github.com/annevk/6f2dd8c79c77123f39797f6bdac43f3e
https://html.spec.whatwg.org/C/#cross-origin-opener-policy

Name: kNewTabPageTriggerForPrerender2

This flag is used for enabling New Tab Page triggered prerendering. See
crbug.com/1462832 for more details of New Tab Page triggered prerendering.

Name: kWebUICodeCache
Documentation: Enables code caching for scripts used on WebUI pages.

Name: kNtpLensDirectUpload
Documentation:
If enabled, Google Lens image search will call Lens v3 direct upload
endpoint instead of uploading to Scotty.

Name: kPersistentHistogramsFeature
Documentation:
Feature definition for enabling histogram persistence. Note that this feature
(along with its param `kPersistentHistogramsStorage`, declared below) is not
used for Chrome on Linux, ChromeOS, Windows, macOS, and Android. Instead,
histograms are persisted to a memory-mapped file, and set up before field
trial initialization (see //chrome/app/chrome_main_delegate.cc).

Name: kCoopRestrictProperties
Documentation:
Introduce a new COOP value: restrict-properties. It restricts window
properties that can be accessed by other pages. This also grants
crossOriginIsolated if coupled with an appropriate COEP header.
This used solely for testing the process model and should not be enabled in
any production code. See https://crbug.com/1221127.

Name: kSpeculationRulesHeaderEnableThirdPartyOriginTrial
Documentation:
Allows certain origin trials to be enabled using third-party tokens
associated with the origin of external speculation rules.

Name: kAllowSourceSwitchOnPausedVideoMediaStream
Documentation:
If enabled, allows MediaStreamVideoSource objects to be restarted by a
successful source switch. Normally, switching the source would only allowed
on streams that are in started state. However, changing the source also first
stops the stream before performing the switch and sometimes it can be useful
to do a change directly on a paused stream.

Name: kAlignWakeUps
Documentation:
Under this feature, wake ups are aligned at a 8ms boundary when allowed per
DelayPolicy.

Name: kAutoplayIgnoreWebAudio
Documentation:
Whether the autoplay policy should ignore Web Audio. When ignored, the
autoplay policy will be hardcoded to be the legacy one on based on the
platform

Name: kCooperativeScheduling
Documentation: Enables Blink cooperative scheduling.

Name: kNoDiscardableMemoryForGpuDecodePath
Documentation:
Enabling this will make the GPU decode path use a mock implementation of
discardable memory.

Name: kUIExperimentMaxAutocompleteMatches
Documentation:
Feature used to cap max suggestions shown according to the params
UIMaxAutocompleteMatches and UIMaxAutocompleteMatchesByProvider.

Name: kLiveCaption
Documentation: Enables the Live Caption feature on supported devices.

Name: kDownloadServiceFeature
Documentation:
Used to set configuration of download service through Finch. This is not used
to turn on/off the feature.

Name: kClientHintsDeviceMemory
Documentation: Enable `sec-ch-device-memory` client hint.

Name: kAutofillEnableMovingGPayLogoToTheRightOnDesktop
Documentation:
When enabled, the GPay logo will be moved to the right side in payments
autofill dialogs and bubbles on desktop.

Name: kTabSearchFuzzySearch
Documentation: Controls whether or not to use fuzzy search for tab search.

Name: kNoReferrers
Documentation:
When kNoReferrers is enabled, most HTTP requests will provide empty
referrers instead of their ordinary behavior.

Name: kCompanionEnabledByObservingExpsNavigations
Documentation:
Dynamically enables the search companion if the user has experiments
enabled.

Name: kEnablePixelCanvasRecording
Documentation:
If enabled, all draw commands recorded on canvas are done in pixel aligned
measurements. This also enables scaling of all elements in views and layers
to be done via corner points. See https://crbug.com/720596 for details.

Name: kLCPPFontURLPredictor
Documentation:
If enabled, fetched font URLs are observed to predict font usage in the
future navigation.

Name: kEnableWindowsGamingInputDataFetcher
Documentation: Enables the Windows.Gaming.Input data fetcher.

Name: kBookmarksExportUseSaf
Documentation: disabled by default because of an issue on Android 6.0

Name: kTurnOffStreamingMediaCachingOnBattery
Documentation: Turns off streaming media caching to disk when on battery power.

Name: kAutofillEnableRankingFormulaCreditCards
Documentation:
When enabled, autofill will use the new ranking algorithm for credit card
autofill suggestions.

Name: kNtpSafeBrowsingModule
Documentation: If enabled, SafeBrowsing module will be shown to a target user.

Name: kFilterAdsOnAbusiveSites
Documentation: Enables the blocking of ads on sites that are abusive.

Name: kCustomizeChromeSidePanelNoChromeRefresh2023
Documentation:
If both kCustomizeChromeSidePanelNoChromeRefresh2023 and
kCustomizeChromeSidePanel are enabled, Customize Chrome will be an option in
the Unified Side Panel when on the New Tab Page but Chrome Refresh 2023 will
be disabled. This state is useful in the Customize Chrome holdback
experiment.

Name: kEnablePasswordsAccountStorage
Documentation:
Enables a second, Gaia-account-scoped password store for users who are signed
in but not syncing.

Name: kAutofillSuggestServerCardInsteadOfLocalCard
Documentation:
When enabled, Autofill suggestions that consist of a local and server
version of the same card will attempt to fill the server card upon selection
instead of the local card.

Name: kDCompTripleBufferVideoSwapChain
Documentation: Use BufferCount of 3 for direct composition video swap chains.

Name: kUseWritePixelsYUV
Documentation:
Enables writing pixels together for all planes to a multi-planar shared
image.

Name: kHardwareMediaKeyHandling
Documentation: Enables handling of hardware media keys for controlling media.

Name: kAutofillUndo
Documentation: Changes Autofill Clear Form into Undo Autofill.

Name: kEnablePixPayments
Documentation: When enabled, Chrome will offer to pay with accounts supporting Pix.

Name: kLiveCaptionUseWaitK
Documentation:
Use a wait-k approach to reduce flickering when translating partial speech
recognition results.

Name: kTranslateRankerQuery
Documentation:
Features used to enable ranker query, enforcement and logging. Note that
enabling enforcement implies (forces) enabling queries.

Name: kThrottleDisplayNoneAndVisibilityHiddenCrossOriginIframes
Documentation:
Forces same-process display:none cross-origin iframes to be throttled in the
same manner that OOPIFs are.
Note: this feature should never be accessed directly. Instead, use
IsThrottleDisplayNoneAndVisibilityHiddenCrossOriginIframesEnabled defined
below.

Name: kWebViewVulkan
Documentation:
If webview-draw-functor-uses-vulkan is set, use vulkan for composite and
raster.

Name: kNtpHistoryClustersModuleSuggestionChipHeader
Documentation: If enabled a suggestion chip will show in the header for Quests V2.

Name: kForceRestartGpuKillSwitch
Documentation:
Kill switch for forcing restart GPU with context loss.
See https://crbug.com/1172229 for detail.

Name: kBiometricTouchToFill
Documentation: Enables Biometrics for the Touch To Fill feature. This only effects Android.

Name: kAutofillPopupUseLatencyInformationForAcceptThreshold
Documentation:
Controls whether the threshold for accepting Autofill popup suggestions
should take into account latency information of the user event.

Name: kBackgroundResourceFetch
Documentation:
Enable background resource fetch in Blink. See https://crbug.com/1379780 for
more details.

Name: kTabGroupsCollapseFreezing
Documentation:
Enables tabs to be frozen when collapsed.
https://crbug.com/1110108

Name: kSecurePaymentConfirmationDebug
Documentation:
Used to control whether to remove the restriction that PaymentCredential in
WebAuthn and secure payment confirmation method in PaymentRequest API must
use a user verifying platform authenticator. When enabled, this allows using
such devices as UbiKey on Linux, which can make development easier.

Name: kJXL
Documentation: Enables the JPEG XL Image File Format (JXL).

Name: kFeedShowSignInCommand
Documentation: When enabled, allow show sign in command to request a user signs in / syncs.

Name: kPostMessageThirdPartyToThirdPartyDifferentBucketSameOriginBlockedIfStorageIsPartitioned
Documentation:
Whether third-party to third-party different-bucket same-origin post messages
are blocked when storage partitioning is enabled.

Name: kServiceWorkerScopeCache
Documentation:
When this is enabled, The ServiceWorker's scope URLs are cached on the UI
thread, and stops calling FindRegistrationForClientUrl mojo function if
possible.

Name: kDesktopPWAsElidedExtensionsMenu
Documentation:
Moves the Extensions "puzzle piece" icon from the title bar into the app menu
for web app windows.

Name: kParallelDownloading
Documentation: Whether a download can be handled by parallel jobs.

Name: kBrowsingTopicsDocumentAPI
Documentation:
Enables calling the Topics API through Javascript (i.e.
document.browsingTopics()). For this feature to take effect, the main Topics
feature has to be enabled first (i.e. `kBrowsingTopics` is enabled, and,
either a valid Origin Trial token exists or `kPrivacySandboxAdsAPIsOverride`
is enabled.)

Name: kAutofillConvergeToExtremeLengthStreetAddress
Documentation:
Enables converging towards the longer or shorter street address in profile
merging.

Name: kJourneysPersistCachesToPrefs
Documentation: Persist keyword caches via pref service.

Name: kAutofillForUnclassifiedFieldsAvailable
Documentation:
Controls whether field filling through the context menu will be available for
the unclassified fields.
TODO(crbug.com/1493361): Clean up when launched.

Name: kCorsNonWildcardRequestHeadersSupport
Documentation: https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#cors-non-wildcard-request-header-name

Name: kSyncTrustedVaultVerifyDeviceRegistration
Documentation:
Enables logging a UMA metric that requires first communicating with the
trusted vault server, in order to verify that the local notion of the device
being registered is consistent with the server-side state.

Name: kLensStandalone
Documentation: Enables context menu search by image sending to the Lens homepage.

Name: kThreatDomDetailsTagAndAttributeFeature
Documentation:
Specifies which non-resource HTML Elements to collect based on their tag and
attributes. It's a single param containing a comma-separated list of pairs.
For example: "tag1,id,tag1,height,tag2,foo" - this will collect elements with
tag "tag1" that have attribute "id" or "height" set, and elements of tag
"tag2" if they have attribute "foo" set. All tag names and attributes should
be lower case.

Name: kDesktopPWAsIconHealthChecks
Documentation:
Runs diagnostics during start up to measure how broken web app icons are to
feed into metrics.

Name: kWebAppEnableScopeExtensions
Documentation:
Controls scope extensions feature in web apps. Controls parsing of
"scope_extensions" field in web app manifests. See explainer for more
information:
https://github.com/WICG/manifest-incubations/blob/gh-pages/scope_extensions-explainer.md

Name: kMultiPlaneVideoCaptureSharedImages
Documentation:
Enable binding multiple shared images to a single GpuMemoryBuffer for video
frames created by video capture.

Name: kRSAKeyUsageForLocalAnchors
Documentation:
Enables checking the X.509 keyUsage extension in TLS 1.2 for RSA server
certificates that chain to a local trust anchor.

Independent of the setting of this feature, keyUsage is always checked at TLS
1.3, for ECDSA certificates, and for all certificates that chain to a known
root.

Name: kAllowForceMergeRenderPassWithRequireOverlayQuads
Documentation:
Allow SurfaceAggregator to merge render passes when they contain quads that
require overlay (e.g. protected video). See usage in |EmitSurfaceContent|.

Name: kRequestDesktopSiteAdditions
Documentation:
Request Desktop Site secondary settings for Android; including display
setting and peripheral setting.

Name: kFedCmError
Documentation:
Enables usage of the FedCM Error API.
ChromeStatus entry: https://chromestatus.com/feature/5384360374566912

Name: kAutofillShowAutocompleteDeleteButton
Documentation:
Controls whether to offer a delete button for Autocomplete entries in the
Autofill popup.

Name: kConvertTrackpadEventsToMouse
Documentation:
Enables converting trackpad click gestures to mouse events in
order for them to be interpreted similar to a desktop
experience (i.e. double-click to select word.)

Name: kUnifiedAutoplay
Documentation:
Enables the Unified Autoplay policy by overriding the platform's default
autoplay policy.

Name: kNtpDriveModule
Documentation: If enabled, Google Drive module will be shown.

Name: kInstallAndroidUnwindDfm
Documentation: Used to gate unwind prerequisites' installation for some unit tests.

Name: kDisplayOpenLinkAsProfile
Documentation:
Enables displaying the submenu to open a link with a different profile if
there is at least one other active profile. Fully rolled out on Desktop.

Name: kLoginDetection
Documentation: Enables login detection to sited based on various heuristics.

Name: kSkipEarlyCommitPendingForCrashedFrame
Documentation:
Enables skipping the early call to CommitPending when navigating away from a
crashed frame.

Name: kAlpsParsing
Documentation: Whether ALPS parsing is on for any type of frame.

Name: kAutofillEnableCardArtServerSideStretching
Documentation:
When enabled, server will return card art images of the exact required
dimension.

Name: kUseFeatureEngagementForUserTargeting
Documentation:
Feature flag to determine whether feature engagement tracker should be used
instead of segmentation platform.

Name: kPrefetchReusable
Documentation:
If enabled, PrefetchContainer can be used for more than one navigation.
https://crbug.com/1449360

Name: kShoppingUserSegmentFeature
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling shopping user segment feature.

Name: kAutofillEnableVirtualCardMetadata
Documentation:
When enabled, Chrome will show metadata along with other card information
when the virtual card is presented to users.

Name: kAutofillPreferLabelsInSomeCountries
Documentation:
If enabled, Autofill will first look at field labels and then at field
attributes when classifying address fields in Mexico.

Name: kDisambiguateTabMatchingForEntitySuggestions
Documentation: Entity suggestion disambiguation.

Name: kEvDetailsInPageInfo
Documentation: Enables showing the EV certificate details in the Page Info bubble.

Name: kTailoredSecurityIntegration
Documentation: Controls whether the integration of tailored security settings is enabled.

Name: kWebLockScreenApi
Documentation:
Enable the web lockscreen API implementation
(https://github.com/WICG/lock-screen) in Chrome.

Name: kPreconnectToSearch
Documentation: Feature to control preconnect to search.

Name: kKeyPinningComponentUpdater
Documentation:
Controls whether the static key pinning list can be updated via component
updater.

Name: kUseElementInsteadOfRegionCapture
Documentation:
If enabled, element capture will be performed instead of region capture. Used
for testing until the restrictTo API is finished.
TODO(https://crbug.com/1473342): remove once restrictTo API is in place.

Name: kEnableSaveDataHeader
Documentation: Enable save-data header separately (without enabled data reduction service).

Name: kFedCmMultipleIdentityProviders
Documentation:
Enables usage of the FedCM API with multiple identity providers at the same
time.

Name: kResamplingScrollEvents
Documentation:
Enables resampling GestureScroll events on compositor thread.
Uses the kPredictorName* values in ui_base_features.h as the 'predictor'
feature param.

Name: kRunOnMainThread
Documentation:
If enabled the PM runs on the main (UI) thread. Incompatible with
kRunOnDedicatedThreadPoolThread.

Name: kWebAuthnJSONSerializeRequests
Documentation:
Serialize WebAuthn requests to JSON on the desktop. Useful for future
projects but only concretely used for better logging at the time of writing.

Name: kWebApkInstallService
Documentation: Enables the Chrome Android WebAPK-install service.

Name: kExtensionTelemetryTabsApiSignal
Documentation:
Enables collection of telemetry signal whenever an extension invokes the
chrome.tabs API methods.

Name: kAllowDevToolsMainThreadDebuggerForMultipleMainFrames
Documentation:
Allows running DevTools main thread debugger even when a renderer process
hosts multiple main frames.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformSearchUser
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling search user segment.

Name: kPeriodicSyncPermissionForDefaultSearchEngine
Documentation:
If enabled, the installability criteria for granting PBS permission is
dropped and the content setting is checked. This only applies if the
requesting origin matches that of the browser's default search engine.

Name: kUseBuiltInRetryingMechanismForListFamilyMembers
Documentation: Instead of manually implementing the process, use the proto_fetcher.cc's one.

Name: kEnableHardwareMirrorMode
Documentation:
A temporary flag to control hardware mirroring until it is decided whether to
permanently remove hardware mirroring support. See crbug.com/1161556 for
details.

Name: kPrerenderFallbackToPreconnect
Documentation: Allows Chrome to do preconnect when prerender fails.

Name: kAutofillEnableSupportForAddressOverflow
Documentation:
Controls if Chrome support filling and importing address overflow fields.
TODO(crbug.com/1441904) Remove once launched.

Name: kWebOTPAssertionFeaturePolicy
Documentation:
Enables WebOTP calls in cross-origin iframes if allowed by Permissions
Policy.

Name: kNtpModulesHeaderIcon
Documentation: If enabled, module headers will display an associated icon.

Name: kV8Turboshaft
Documentation: Enables Turbofan's new compiler IR Turboshaft.

Name: kScrollSnapCoveringUseNativeFling
Documentation:
When enabled, scrolling within a covering snap area uses the native fling,
allowing much more natural scrolling within these areas.

Name: kFedCmIdAssertionCORS
Documentation: Enables CORS checks on the ID assertion endpoint of the FedCM API.

Name: kAllowDropAlphaForMediaStream
Documentation:
When enabled, allow dropping alpha on media streams for rendering sinks if
other sinks connected do not use alpha.

Name: kAutofillEnableDevtoolsIssues
Documentation: Controls if Autofill emits form issues to devtools.

Name: kProcessSharingWithStrictSiteInstances
Documentation:
Whether cross-site frames should get their own SiteInstance even when
strict site isolation is disabled. These SiteInstances will still be
grouped into a shared default process based on BrowsingInstance.

Name: kFFmpegAllowLists
Documentation: Enables FFmpeg allow lists for supported codecs / containers.

Name: kCacheControlNoStoreEnterBackForwardCache
Documentation:
Allows pages with cache-control:no-store to enter the back/forward cache.
Feature params can specify whether pages with cache-control:no-store can be
restored if cookies change / if HTTPOnly cookies change.
TODO(crbug.com/1228611): Enable this feature.

Name: kWebRtcInitializeEncoderOnFirstFrame
Documentation: Initialize VideoEncodeAccelerator on the first encode.

Name: kEvaluateProtectedPasswordLengthMinimum
Documentation: Enables decreased Phishguard password length minimum.

Name: kLensImageFormatOptimizations
Documentation: Enables using more optimized image formats for Lens requests.

Name: kKAnonymityService
Documentation: When enabled, allows other features to use the k-Anonymity Service.

Name: kUserVisibleDebug
Documentation:
Enables debug info in user-visible surfaces, like the actual WebUI page.
Does nothing if `kJourneys` is disabled.

Name: kWebAudioBypassOutputBuffering
Documentation:
Enabling this flag bypasses additional buffering when using the Web Audio
API, which may reduce audio output latency but may also increase the
probability of an audio glitch.

Name: kEnforceLocalAnchorConstraints
Documentation:
Most code should not check this feature flag directly, instead use
IsLocalAnchorConstraintsEnforcementEnabled().

Name: kDownloadsMigrateToJobsAPI
Documentation: Whether downloads uses Android Jobs API instead of FGS.

Name: kReferrerChainParameters
Documentation:
Enables modifying key parameters on the navigation event collection used to
populate referrer chains.

Name: kMemoryPressureBasedSourceBufferGC
Documentation:
Make MSE garbage collection algorithm more aggressive when we are under
moderate or critical memory pressure. This will relieve memory pressure by
releasing stale data from MSE buffers.

Name: kSyncTrustedVaultPeriodicDegradedRecoverabilityPolling
Documentation: Whether the periodic degraded recoverability polling is enabled.

Name: kLocalHistoryZeroSuggestBeyondNTP
Documentation:
Enables local history zero-prefix suggestions in every context in which the
remote zero-prefix suggestions are enabled.

Name: kStripCredentialsForExternalProtocolHandler
Documentation:
When enabled, it strips credentials from URL to mitigate the mitigate the
risk of credential leakage when registering protocol handlers for standard
schemes. This feature is enabled by default and meant to be used as a
killswitch.
https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/system-state.html#security-and-privacy

Name: kNtpReducedLogoSpace
Documentation: If enabled, logo will fill up less vertical space.

Name: kAImageReaderVideoOutput
Documentation: Enables the Android Image Reader path for Video decoding(for AVDA and MCVD)

Name: kMetricsServiceAllowEarlyLogClose
Documentation:
Determines at what point the metrics service is allowed to close a log when
Chrome is closed (and backgrounded/foregrounded for mobile platforms). When
this feature is disabled, the metrics service can only close a log if it has
already started sending logs. When this feature is enabled, the metrics
service can close a log starting from when the first log is opened.

Name: kUseDecoderStreamForWebRTC
Documentation:
If enabled, RTCVideoDecoderAdapter will wrap a DecoderStream as a video
decoder, rather than using MojoVideoDecoder.  This causes the RTC external
decoder to have all the decoder selection / fallback/forward logic of the
non-RTC pipeline.
TODO(liberato): This also causes the external decoder to use software
decoding sometimes, which changes the interpretation of "ExternalDecoder".

Name: kPriorityHeader
Documentation:
Enables the HTTP extensible priorities "priority" header.
RFC 9218

Name: kPrivacyGuide3
Documentation:
Enables or disables the Privacy Guide v3 update of the Privacy Guide feature
in Chrome Settings.

Name: kAutoPictureInPictureForVideoPlayback
Documentation:
Allows the AutoPictureInPictureTabHelper to automatically enter
picture-in-picture for websites with video playback (instead of only websites
using camera or microphone).

Name: kUsernameFirstFlowWithIntermediateValuesVoting
Documentation:
Enables voting for more text fields outside of the password form in Username
First Flow.

Name: kNtpChromeCartInHistoryClusterModule
Documentation:
If enabled, ChromeCart tile will show in the History clusters module when
available.

Name: kPrivacySandboxAdsAPIsOverride
Documentation:
Enables exposure of ads APIs in the renderer: Attribution Reporting,
FLEDGE, Topics, along with a number of other features actively in development
within these APIs.

Name: kAblateSendPendingAccessibilityEvents
Documentation: Experiment to increase the cost of SendPendingAccessibilityEvents.

Name: kUseRealBuffersForPageFlipTest
Documentation:
Whether we should use the real buffers corresponding to overlay candidates in
order to do a pageflip test rather than allocating test buffers.

Name: kVisibilityAwareResourceScheduler
Documentation:
Enables visibility aware network service resource scheduler. When enabled,
request may be prioritized or de-prioritized based on the visibility of
requestors.

Name: kImageServiceObserveSyncDownloadStatus
Documentation:
Enables observing sync service for download status to determine whether
images for already synced sync entities can be fetched.

Name: kRealboxIsTall
Documentation: If enabled, the realbox will be taller.

Name: kInnerFrameCompositorSurfaceEviction
Documentation:
During compositor frame eviction, collect not only the surfaces that are
reachable from the main frame tree, but also recurse into inner
frames. Otherwise only toplevel frames and OOPIF are handled, and other
cases, e.g. PDF tiles are ignored. See https://crbug.com/1360351 for details.

Name: kEnableAriaElementReflection
Documentation:
Enable support for ARIA element reflection, for example
element.ariaActiveDescendantElement = child;

Name: kIntensiveWakeUpThrottling
Documentation:
When enabled, wake ups from throttleable TaskQueues are limited to 1 per
minute in a page that has been backgrounded for 5 minutes.

Intensive wake up throttling is enforced in addition to other throttling
mechanisms:
 - 1 wake up per second in a background page or hidden cross-origin frame
 - 1% CPU time in a page that has been backgrounded for 10 seconds

Feature tracking bug: https://crbug.com/1075553

The base::Feature should not be read from; rather the provided accessors
should be used, which also take into account the managed policy override of
the feature.

The base::Feature is enabled by default on all platforms. However, on
Android, it has no effect because page freezing kicks in at the same time. It
would have an effect if the grace period ("grace_period_seconds" param) was
reduced.

Name: kAsyncQuicSession
Documentation: A flag to use asynchronous session creation for new QUIC sessions.

Name: kV8OffThreadFinalization
Documentation: Enables finalizing streaming JS compilations on a background thread.

Name: kFedCmRevoke
Documentation: Enables the revoke method within the FedCM API.

Name: kUserNotes
Documentation: Feature controlling the User Notes feature on desktop platforms.

Name: kAttributionDebugReportingCookieDeprecationTesting
Documentation:
Enables attribution reporting transitional debug reporting for the cookie
deprecation experiment.

Name: kRemoteOptimizationGuideFetching
Documentation: Enables fetching from a remote Optimization Guide Service.

Name: kHideWebAppOriginText
Documentation: Hides the origin text from showing up briefly in WebApp windows.

Name: kSkipTpcdMitigationsForAds
Documentation:
This feature allows skipping TPCD mitigation checks when the cookie access
is tagged as being used for advertising purposes. This means that cookies
will continue to be blocked for cookie accesses on ad requests even if the
3PC mitigations would otherwise allow the access.

Name: kPortalsCrossOrigin
Documentation:
When kPortals is enabled, allow portals to load content that is third-party
(cross-origin) to the hosting page. Otherwise has no effect.

https://crbug.com/1013389

Name: kDelayFirstWorkerWake
Documentation:
This feature controls whether ThreadPool WorkerThreads should hold off waking
up to purge partition alloc within the first minute of their lifetime. See
base::internal::GetSleepTimeBeforePurge.

Name: kBackForwardCache
Documentation: Enable using the BackForwardCache.

Name: kReadingListEnableSyncTransportModeUponSignIn
Documentation:
Feature flag used for enabling sync (transport mode) for signed-in users that
haven't turned on full sync.

Name: kHistoryClustersVisitDeduping
Documentation: Enables experimentation for how to dedupe visits in clusters.

Name: kAdSamplerTriggerFeature
Documentation:
Controls various parameters related to occasionally collecting ad samples,
for example to control how often collection should occur.

Name: kCastStreamingVp9
Documentation:
Controls whether mirroring negotiations will include the VP9 codec for video
encoding.

NOTE: currently only software VP9 encoding is supported.
TODO(https://crbug.com/1311770): hardware VP9 encoding should be added.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidPermissionUpdate
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether permission update prompts use Messages or
Infobars infrastructure.

Name: kHistoryClustersKeywordFiltering
Documentation: Enables use of additional keyword filtering operations on clusters.

Name: kUsePlatformDelegatedInk
Documentation:
Enables platform supported delegated ink trails instead of Skia backed
delegated ink trails.

Name: kTabScrollingButtonPosition
Documentation: Enables buttons when scrolling the tabstrip https://crbug.com/951078

Name: kWebViewThreadSafeMediaDefault
Documentation:
This is used as default state because it's different for webview and chrome.
WebView hardcodes this as enabled in AwMainDelegate.

Name: kEnableAccessibilityAriaVirtualContent
Documentation: Enable recognizing "aria-virtualcontent" as a valid aria property.

Name: kAnchorElementInteraction
Documentation: Anchor Element Interaction

Name: kMessagesForAndroidAdsBlocked
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether "ads blocked" messages use Messages or
Infobars infrastructure.

Name: kOsFeedbackSaveReportToLocalForE2ETesting
Documentation: Alphabetical:

Name: kAutofillEnableStickyManualFallbackForCards
Documentation:
When enabled, if the user interacts with the manual fallback bottom sheet
on Android, it'll remain sticky until the user dismisses it.

Name: kBackForwardCacheWithKeepaliveRequest
Documentation:
Allows pages with keepalive requests to stay eligible for the back/forward
cache. See https://crbug.com/1347101 for more details.

Name: kWebAppEnableUrlHandlers
Documentation:
Controls URL handling feature in web apps. Controls parsing of "url_handlers"
field in web app manifests. See explainer for more information:
https://github.com/WICG/pwa-url-handler/blob/main/explainer.md

Name: kBlinkHeapIncrementalMarking
Documentation: Enables incrementally marking Blink's heap.

Name: kMigrateSessionsOnNetworkChangeV2
Documentation:
Whether QuicParams::migrate_sessions_on_network_change_v2 defaults to true or
false. This is needed as a workaround to set this value to true on Android
but not on WebView (until crbug.com/1430082 has been fixed).

Name: kWebRtcAllowWgcZeroHz
Documentation:
When enabled we will tell WebRTC that we want to use the 0Hz mode of the
Windows.Graphics.Capture API based DesktopCapturer, if the WGC capturer is
available and enabled. In this mode, only frames with new content will be
sent to the client leading to to 0fps for a static source.
This flag has no effect if kWebRtcAllowWgcScreenCapturer and
kWebRtcAllowWgcWindowCapturer are both disabled.

Name: kProcessGaiaRemoveLocalAccountHeader
Documentation:
Enables the client-side processing of the HTTP response header
Google-Accounts-RemoveLocalAccount.

Name: kNewBrowsingContextStateOnBrowsingContextGroupSwap
Documentation:
Currently there are two paths - legacy code, in which BrowsingContextState
will be 1:1 with FrameTreeNode, allowing us to move proxy storage to it as a
no-op, and a new path hidden behind a feature flag, which will create a new
BrowsingContextState for cross-BrowsingInstance navigations.

Name: kSpeculativeServiceWorkerWarmUp
Documentation: TODO(crbug/1431792): Speculatively warm-up service worker.

Name: kInstalledApp
Documentation: Kill switch for the GetInstalledRelatedApps API.

Name: kFrequentFeatureUserSegmentFeature
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling frequent feature user segment.

Name: kMediaPowerExperiment
Documentation: Enable aggregate power measurement for media playback.

Name: kEnableADPFScrollBoost
Documentation:
Used to enable the HintSession::Mode::BOOST mode. BOOST mode try to force
the ADPF(Android Dynamic Performance Framework) to give Chrome more CPU
resources during a scroll.

Name: kVaapiJpegImageDecodeAcceleration
Documentation:
Controls the decode acceleration of JPEG images (as opposed to camera
captures) in Chrome OS using the VA-API.
TODO(andrescj): remove or enable by default in Chrome OS once
https://crbug.com/868400 is resolved.

Name: kFeedStamp
Documentation: Feature that enables StAMP cards in the feed.

Name: kNtpMostLikelyFaviconsFromServerFeature
Documentation:
Feature to allow the new Google favicon server for fetching favicons for Most
Likely tiles on the New Tab Page.

Name: kPrivateNetworkAccessPermissionPrompt
Documentation:
When kPrivateNetworkAccessPermissionPrompt is enabled, public secure websites
are allowed to access private insecure subresources with user's permission.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformFeature
Documentation: Core feature flag for segmentation platform.

Name: kAutofillEnableSupportForApartmentNumbers
Documentation:
Controls if Chrome support filling and importing apartment numbers.
TODO(crbug.com/1153715): Remove once launched.

Name: kEnableServiceWorkersForChromeScheme
Documentation: Enables service workers on chrome:// urls.

Name: kIncreasedCmdBufferParseSlice
Documentation:
Use a 100-command limit before forcing context switch per command buffer
instead of 20.

Name: kAppStoreBillingDebug
Documentation:
Used to control whether to remove the restriction that TWA has to be
installed from specific app stores.

Name: kFontsFingerprintMitigation
Documentation: Filter the list of fonts allowing the use of only standard fonts

Name: kWebSQLAccess
Documentation: Allow access to WebSQL APIs.

Name: kRunOnDedicatedThreadPoolThread
Documentation:
If enabled the PM runs on a single ThreadPool thread that isn't shared with
any other task runners. It will be named "Performance Manager" in traces.
This makes it easy to identify tasks running on the PM sequence, but may not
perform as well as a shared sequence, which is the default. Incompatible with
kRunOnMainThread.

Name: kSchemefulSameSite
Documentation:
When enabled this feature will cause same-site calculations to take into
account the scheme of the site-for-cookies and the request/response url.

Name: kQueueNavigationsWhileWaitingForCommit
Documentation:
When enabled, queues navigations instead of cancelling the previous
navigation if the previous navigation is already waiting for commit.
See https://crbug.com/838348 and https://crbug.com/1220337.

Name: kPushMessagingBackgroundMode
Documentation:
Enables or disables push subscriptions keeping Chrome running in the
background when closed.

Name: kFractionalScrollOffsets
Documentation:
Enables scrollers inside Blink to store scroll offsets in fractional
floating-point numbers rather than truncating to integers.

Name: kQueryInMemoryTextEmbeddings
Documentation: Enables text embeddings to annotated on every page visit and later queried.

Name: kEncryptedReportingPipeline
Documentation: static

Name: kFailUrlProvisionFetcherForTesting
Documentation:
Prevents UrlProvisionFetcher from making a provisioning request. If
specified, any provisioning request made will not be sent to the provisioning
server, and the response will indicate a failure to communicate with the
provisioning server.

Name: kSelectiveInOrderScript
Documentation:
If enabled, parser-blocking scripts are loaded asynchronously. The target
scripts are selectively applied via the allowlist provided from the feature
param. See https://crbug.com/1356396

Name: kStartCanvasWithAccelerationDisabled
Documentation:
Controls whether canvases may start with acceleration disabled. This behavior
is controlled by two params. When this feature is enabled, a newly created
canvas will start with acceleration disabled if the following two
requirements are met (per Document);
1. More than `kCanvasDisableAccelerationThresholdParam` canvases have been
   created.
2. The percent of canvases with acceleration disabled is >=
   `kCanvasDisableAccelerationPercentParam`.

Name: kKAnonymityServiceStorage
Documentation:
When enabled, the k-Anonymity Service can use a persistent storage to cache
public keys.

Name: kMainThreadHighPriorityImageLoading
Documentation: If enabled, image loading tasks on visible pages have high priority.

Name: kSafeBrowsingSkipSubresources
Documentation:
Controls whether to skip Safe Browsing checks on all subresource URLs in
renderer and browser URL loader throttles.

Name: kOnDeviceHeadProviderIncognito
Documentation: On Device Suggest.

Name: kReuseInitialRenderFrameHostForWebUI
Documentation:
When enabled, allow reusing an initial RenderFrameHost with an unused process
for a subsequent WebUI navigation.  WebUI navigations typically trigger a
BrowsingInstance swap, but the swap is not necessary in that case: see
https://crbug.com/1485586.  This is intended to be used as a kill switch.

Name: kRasterInterfaceInVideoResourceUpdater
Documentation: Enables using RasterInterface in VideoResourceUpdater.

Name: kEventTimingMatchPresentationIndex
Documentation: Enables reporting Event Timing with matching presentation promise index only.

Name: kExtensionTelemetryFileDataForCommandLineExtensions
Documentation:
Allows the Extension Telemetry Service to include file data of extensions
specified in the --load-extension commandline switch in telemetry reports.

Name: kCollectAndroidFrameTimelineMetrics
Documentation: Whether to report frame metrics to the Android.FrameTimeline.* histograms.

Name: kZstdContentEncoding
Documentation: Enables Zstandard Content-Encoding support.

Name: kDCompTripleBufferRootSwapChain
Documentation: Use BufferCount of 3 for the direct composition root swap chain.

Name: kUseNAT64ForIPv4Literal
Documentation: Whether to do IPv4 to IPv6 address translation for IPv4 literals.

Name: kAudioFocusEnforcement
Documentation:
Enables Audio Focus enforcement which means that only one media session can
have audio focus at any one time.

Name: kAllowEyeDropperWGCScreenCapture
Documentation: Enables the use of WGC for the Eye Dropper screen capture.

Name: kVerifyDidCommitParams
Documentation:
Enables comparing browser and renderer's DidCommitProvisionalLoadParams in
RenderFrameHostImpl::VerifyThatBrowserAndRendererCalculatedDidCommitParamsMatch.

Name: kCastEnableStreamingWithHiDPI
Documentation: TODO(crbug.com/1412589): Should be removed once working properly.

Name: kSingleSortAndCullPass
Documentation:
When disabled, when providers update their matches, the new set of matches
are sorted and culled, then merged with the old matches, then sorted and
culled again. When enabled, the first sort and cull is skipped.

Name: kWebFeedAwareness
Documentation: Feature that provides the user assistance in discovering the web feed.

Name: kSiteIsolationMemoryThresholds
Documentation:
kSiteIsolationMemoryThresholds is checked before individual site isolation
mode base::Features (such as kSitePerProcess or
kSiteIsolationForPasswordSites), and (if enabled) can restrict those modes
to not apply to low-memory devices below a certain memory threshold.  The
threshold for what is considered a "low memory" device can be set (in MB)
via field trial params with the names defined below, with independent params
for strict site isolation (kSitePerProcess) and partial site isolation modes
(kSiteIsolationForPasswordSites, kSiteIsolationForOAuthSites, etc). These
thresholds are compared against base::SysInfo::AmountOfPhysicalMemoryMB().
On devices below the memory threshold, the site isolation features such as
kSitePerProcess won't be checked at all, and field trials won't activate
either the control or the experiment group.

Name: kContentCaptureConstantStreaming
Documentation: Enables the constant streaming in the ContentCapture task.

Name: kDiscountConsentV2
Documentation: Feature flag for Discount user consent v2.

Name: kSearchEngineChoiceFre
Documentation: Enables the search engine choice feature in the FRE.

Name: kStopLoadingAnimationForHiddenWindow
Documentation:
Reduce resource usage when view is hidden by not rendering loading animation.
TODO(crbug.com/1322081): Clean up the feature in M117.

Name: kPageContentAnnotations
Documentation: Enables page content to be annotated.

Name: kReportUserNoisedUserBirthYearAndGender
Documentation:
Enables adding the synced user's noised birth year and gender to the UKM
report. For more details, see doc of metrics::DemographicMetricsProvider in
components/metrics/demographics/demographic_metrics_provider.h.

Name: kEnableProfileTokenManagement
Documentation: Controls whether token-based profile management is enabled.

Name: kDisableQuotaDbFullFSync
Documentation:
Disables the `flush_to_media` setting for the quota SQLite db, which maps to
F_FULLFSYNC on mac, which is known to have performance issues. Specifically,
this is suspected of causing a high number of SQLite IO errors as encountered
by CDM storage code.

Name: kPopulateVisitedLinkDatabase
Documentation:
When enabled, this feature flag begins populating the VisitedLinkDatabase
with data.

Name: kV8FlushCodeBasedOnTime
Documentation: Enables code flushing based on time.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformUserVisibleTaskRunner
Documentation:
Feature flag to increase segmentation platform background processing task
runner priority.

Name: kJavaScriptCompileHintsMagic
Documentation: Enables the experiment with compile hints as magic comments.

Name: kOriginIsolationHeader
Documentation:
Controls the Origin-Agent-Cluster header. Tracking bug
https://crbug.com/1042415; flag removal bug (for when this is fully launched)
https://crbug.com/1148057.

The name is "OriginIsolationHeader" because that was the old name when the
feature was under development.

Name: kWebRtcAllowWgcScreenCapturer
Documentation:
When enabled we will tell WebRTC that we want to use the
Windows.Graphics.Capture API based screen capturer, if it is available.

Name: kAndroidAutofillSupportVisibilityChanges
Documentation:
If enabled, visibility changes of form fields of the form of an ongoing
Autofill session are communicated to Android's `AutofillManager` by calling
`AutofillManager.notifyViewVisibilityChanged()`.
See
https://developer.android.com/reference/android/view/autofill/AutofillManager#notifyViewVisibilityChanged(android.view.View,%20int,%20boolean)
for more details on the API.

Name: kCompressionDictionaryTransport
Documentation:
When both this feature and the kCompressionDictionaryTransportBackend feature
are enabled, the following will happen:
  * A <link rel=dictionary> HTML tag and a `Link: rel=dictionary` HTTP header
    will trigger dictionary download.
  * HTMLLinkElement.relList.supports('dictionary') will return true.
  * The network service may register a HTTP response as a dictionary if the
    response header contains a `use-as-dictionary` header.
This feature can be enabled by an Origin Trial token in Blink. To propagate
the enabled state to the network service, Blink sets the
`shared_dictionary_writer_enabled` flag in resource requests.

Name: kBackForwardCache_NoMemoryLimit_Trial
Documentation:
The BackForwardCache_NoMemoryLimit_Trial feature flag's sole purpose is to
make it possible to get a group for "all devices except when BackForwardCache
feature is specifically disabled due to non-memory-control reasons". This is
done by querying the flag if and only if the device satisifes one of the
following:
1) The device does not have enough memory for BackForwardCache, or
2) The device has enough memory and the BackForwardCache feature is enabled.
With that, we will include the devices that don't have enough memory while
avoiding activating the BackForwardCache experiment, and won’t include
devices that do have enough memory but have the BackForwardCache flag
disabled.

Name: kDetailedLanguageSettings
Documentation: This feature enables setting the application language on Android.

Name: kCompanionEnablePageContent
Documentation:
Allow sharing page content with CSC. Enabling this flag alone isn't enough to
share page content - the user still needs to opt in either through a promo or
chrome://settings. When disabled, page content will not be shared even if the
user had previously opted in. The user won't be able to opt in (or out) when
this is disabled.

Name: kSplitHostCacheByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Splits host cache entries by the DNS request's NetworkAnonymizationKey if one
is available. Also prevents merging live DNS lookups when there is a NAK
mismatch.

Name: kOmniboxMaxURLMatches
Documentation:
Feature used to cap the number of URL-type matches shown within the
Omnibox. If enabled, the number of URL-type matches is limited (unless
there are no more non-URL matches available.) If enabled, there is a
companion parameter - OmniboxMaxURLMatches - which specifies the maximum
desired number of URL-type matches.

Name: kExtensionTelemetryDisableOffstoreExtensions
Documentation:
Enables remotely disabling of malicious off-store extensions identified in
Extension Telemetry service reports.

Name: kAutofillLogUKMEventsWithSampleRate
Documentation:
If enabled, we will log information of field types and autofill and forms
with sample rates according to Autofill FormSummary/FieldInfo UKM schema:
https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ZH0JbL6bES3cD4KqZWsGR6n8I-rhnkx6no6nQOgYq5w/.

Name: kV8Turbofan
Documentation: Enables the Turbofan compiler.

Name: kDirectCompositionSoftwareOverlays
Documentation:
Allow overlay swapchain to present on all GPUs even if they only support
software overlays. GPU deny lists limit it to NVIDIA only at the moment.

Name: kReportSearchboxStats
Documentation:
If enabled, Omnibox reports the Searchbox Stats in the gs_lcrp= param in the
Search Results Page URL.

Name: kBlinkHeapConcurrentSweeping
Documentation: Enables concurrently sweeping Blink's heap.

Name: kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsFromUnknown
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, requests to localhost initiated from non-secure
contexts in the `unknown` IP address space are blocked.

See also:
 - kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequests

Name: kFledgeConsiderKAnonymity
Documentation:
Configures FLEDGE to consider k-anononymity. If both
kFledgeConsiderKAnonymity and kFledgeEnforceKAnonymity are on it will be
enforced; if only kFledgeConsiderKAnonymity is on it will be simulated.

Turning on kFledgeEnforceKAnonymity alone does nothing.

Name: kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequests
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, private network requests initiated from
non-secure contexts in the `public` address space  are blocked.

See also:
 - https://wicg.github.io/private-network-access/#integration-fetch
 - kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsFromPrivate
 - kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsFromUnknown

Name: kNoWakeUpsForCanceledTasks
Documentation: This feature controls whether wake ups are possible for canceled tasks.

Name: kWebAssemblyRelaxedSimd
Documentation: Enable the use of WebAssembly Relaxed SIMD operations

Name: kDesktopPWAsTabStripSettings
Documentation: Adds a user settings that allows PWAs to be opened with a tab strip.

Name: kVideoDecodeBatching
Documentation:
Controls whether to pre-dispatch more decode tasks when pending decodes is
smaller than maximum supported decodes as advertiszed by decoder.

Name: kLoadingPredictorDisregardAlwaysAccessesNetwork
Documentation:
Modifies loading predictor so that the value of the |always_access_network|
attribute is not used when computing the predicting score for an origin.

Name: kEnableMSAAOnNewIntelGPUs
Documentation: Enables the use of MSAA in skia on Ice Lake and later intel architectures.

Name: kDirectCompositorThreadIpc
Documentation:
Enables input IPC to directly target the renderer's compositor thread without
hopping through the IO thread first.

Name: kMigrateAlwaysTranslateLanguagesFix
Documentation:
Whether to migrate the obsolete always-translate languages pref to the new
pref during object construction as a fix for crbug/1291356, which had
previously not been migrated at all on iOS. This also enables a more
conservative pref merging process that aims to merge in old always-translate
language values from the obsolete pref without conflicting with any values in
the new pref that may have been added.

TODO(crbug/1303963): This base::Feature only exists to allow a less risky
merge into iOS M98. This base::Feature should be removed once it's no longer
relevant and the enabled behavior should become the only behavior.

Name: kBackgroundTracingPerformanceMark
Documentation:
Used to configure a per-origin allowlist of performance.mark events that are
permitted to be included in slow reports traces. See crbug.com/1181774.

Name: kReducedFrameRateEstimation
Documentation:
Allow CC FrameRateEstimater to reduce the frame rate to half of the default
if the condition meets the requirement.

Name: kBluetoothFlossCoredump
Documentation: Enables/disables the bluetooth devcoredump feature for floss

Name: kFrequencyCappingForLargeStickyAdDetection
Documentation:
Enables the frequency capping for detecting large sticky ads.
Large-sticky-ads are those ads that stick to the bottom of the page
regardless of a user’s efforts to scroll, and take up more than 30% of the
screen’s real estate.

Name: kFledge
Documentation: FLEDGE ad serving runtime flag/JS API.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformAdaptiveToolbarV2Feature
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling adaptive toolbar v2 multi-output model.

Name: kPostQuantumKyber
Documentation: Enables Kyber-based post-quantum key-agreements in TLS 1.3 connections.

Name: kEnableADPFMidFrameBoost
Documentation:
If enabled, Chrome uses ADPF(Android Dynamic Performance Framework) to
request more CPU resources in the middle of a frame production if the frame
is taking longer than expected.

Name: kIdentifiabilityStudy
Documentation:
Root feature for all identifiability study logic.

If the feature is disabled, then this browser instance will not be
participating in the identifiability study. I.e. no identifiability metrics
will be recorded or reported.

Enabling the feature doesn't automatically make this client part of the study
either.

Name: kDropInputEventsBeforeFirstPaint
Documentation: Drop input events before user sees first paint https://crbug.com/1255485

Name: kPasswordSuggestionBottomSheetV2
Documentation:
Enables the refactored Password Suggestion bottom sheet (Touch-To-Fill).
The goal of the refactoring is to transfer the knowledge about the
Touch-To-Fill feature to the browser code completely and so to simplify the
renderer code. In the refactored version it will be decided inside the the
`ContentPasswordManagerDriver::ShowPasswordSuggestions` whether to show the
TTF to the user.

Name: kJavaScriptJsonParseWithSource
Documentation: Enables the JSON.parse with source proposal.

Name: kThumbnailCacheRefactor
Documentation:
A refactoring of the ThumbnailCache and TabContentManager that aims to
optimize performance of the system.

Name: kSiteIsolationForOAuthSites
Documentation:
Controls a mode for dynamically process-isolating sites where the user has
logged in via OAuth.  These sites are determined by runtime heuristics.

This is intended to be used primarily when full site isolation is turned
off.  To check whether this mode is enabled, use
SiteIsolationPolicy::IsIsolationForOAuthSitesEnabled() rather than
checking the feature directly, since that decision is influenced by other
factors as well.

This feature does not affect Android Webview, which does not include this
code.

Name: kBacklightOcr
Documentation:
A feature that makes PDFs displayed in the ChromeOS Media App (AKA Backlight)
accessible by performing OCR on the images for each page.

Name: kMediaSessionService
Documentation:
Enables the Media Session service including audio focus tracking. This allows
clients to consume the Media Session Mojo APIs but should not have any
changes to behavior. It is enabled by default on all platforms except Android.

Name: kEarlyDocumentSwapForBackForwardTransitions
Documentation:
Enable early swapping of RenderFrameHosts during some back/forward
navigations. This is an experimental feature intended to support new kinds of
navigation transitions. See https://crbug.com/1480129.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformFeedSegmentFeature
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling Feed user segments feature.

Name: kSystemCaptionStyle
Documentation: Allows system caption style for WebVTT Captions.

Name: kFallbackAfterDecodeError
Documentation:
Falls back to other decoders after audio/video decode error happens. The
implementation may choose different strategies on when to fallback. See
DecoderStream for details. When disabled, playback will fail immediately
after a decode error happens. This can be useful in debugging and testing
because the behavior is simpler and more predictable.

Name: kUseChimeAndroidSdk
Documentation: The feature flag to determine whether to use Chime Android SDK.

Name: kIsolatedWebAppDevMode
Documentation:
Enables Isolated Web App Developer Mode, which allows developers to
install untrusted Isolated Web Apps.

Name: kAutofillCapturedSiteTestsMetricsScraper
Documentation:
Testing tool that collects metrics during a run of the captured site tests
and dumps the collected metrics into a specified output directory.
