For each test, a file named {test-name}.txt is created. It contains all the
collected metrics in the following format.
histogram-name-1
bucket value
...
histogram-name-2
...
The set of metrics can be restricted using
`kAutofillCapturedSiteTestsMetricsScraperMetricNames`.
It is helpful in conjunction with `tools/captured_sites/metrics-scraper.py`.

Name: kNonUserVisibleDebug
Documentation:
Enables debug info in non-user-visible surfaces, like Chrome Inspector.
Does nothing if `kJourneys` is disabled.

Name: kReduceAcceptLanguageOriginTrial
Documentation:
Gate access to ReduceAcceptLanguage origin trial major code. Currently, All
ReduceAcceptLanguage feature codes are guarded by the feature flag
kReduceAcceptLanguage. This feature flag is useful on control major code
which required to do origin trial. It allows Chrome developers to mitigate
issues when exposed codes cause impacts.

Name: kAutofillLogToTerminal
Documentation: Enables logging the content of chrome://autofill-internals to the terminal.

Name: kVulkan
Documentation:
Enable Vulkan graphics backend for compositing and rasterization. Defaults to
native implementation if --use-vulkan flag is not used. Otherwise
--use-vulkan will be followed.
Note Android WebView uses kWebViewVulkan instead of this.

Name: kDIPS
Documentation:
Enables the DIPS (Detect Incidental Party State) feature.
On by default to allow for collecting metrics. All potentially dangerous
behavior (database persistence, DIPS deletion) will be gated by params.

Name: kProcessHtmlDataImmediately
Documentation:
If set, HTMLDocumentParser processes data immediately rather than after a
delay. This is further controlled by the feature params starting with the
same name. Also note that this only applies to uses that are normally
deferred (for example, when HTMLDocumentParser is created for inner-html it
is not deferred).

Name: kRollbackBookmarksAccountStorage
Documentation:
This feature flags enables the logic that wipes the account storage after
EnableBookmarksAccountStorage rollback. This logic is not enabled by default
to minimize the performance impact.

Name: kOptimizeDataUrls
Documentation: Optimizes parsing and loading of data: URLs.

Name: kEncryptedClientHelloQuic
Documentation:
Enables the TLS Encrypted ClientHello feature for QUIC. Only takes effect if
kEncryptedClientHello is also enabled.

TODO(crbug.com/1287248): Remove this flag when ECH for QUIC is fully
implemented. This flag is just a temporary mechanism for now.

Name: kContentLanguagesInLanguagePicker
Documentation:
This feature enables showing the user's content languages separately at the
top of the language picker menu in the Translate UI.

Name: kFluentOverlayScrollbar
Documentation:
Makes all native scrollbars behave as overlay scrollbars styled to fit the
Windows 11 Fluent design language.
TODO(crbug.com/1479156): Right now this feature flag will force Fluent
overlay scrollbars on. We have yet to decide how we will expose this feature
once it is complete.

Name: kSafeBrowsingDailyPhishingReportsLimit
Documentation:
Enables client side phishing daily reports limit to be configured via Finch
for ESB and SBER users

Name: kWebRtcHideLocalIpsWithMdns
Documentation:
Causes WebRTC to replace host ICE candidate IP addresses with generated
names ending in ".local" and resolve them using mDNS.
http://crbug.com/878465

Name: kBlockMidiByDefault
Documentation: Enables disallowing MIDI permission by default.

Name: kSearchEngineChoiceSettingsUi
Documentation: Enables the new search engine choice setting UI.

Name: kRecordBackForwardCacheMetricsWithoutEnabling
Documentation:
This feature is used to limit the scope of back-forward cache experiment
without enabling it. To control the URLs list by using this feature by
generating the metrics only for "allowed_websites" param. Mainly, to ensure
that metrics from the control and experiment groups are consistent.

Name: kSmartZoom
Documentation:
Allows the use of "Smart Zoom", an alternative form of page zoom, and
enables the associated UI.

Name: kAutofillEnableMerchantOptOutClientSideUrlFiltering
Documentation:
When enabled, client side URL filtering will be triggered for the merchant
opt-out use-case, so that virtual card suggestions are not shown on websites
that are opted-out of virtual cards.

Name: kFledgePst
Documentation:
Secondary flag used by the FLEDGE ads experiment in the interim before
PSTs are fully rolled out to stable.

Name: kWebAssemblyStringref
Documentation:
Enable support for the WebAssembly Stringref proposal:
https://github.com/WebAssembly/stringref.

Name: kFileSystemUrlNavigation
Documentation:
Switch to temporary turn back on file system url navigation.
TODO(https://crbug.com/1332598): Remove this feature.

Name: kNtpModulesLoadTimeoutMilliseconds
Documentation: Dummy feature to set param "NtpModulesLoadTimeoutMillisecondsParam".

Name: kRequestSystemAudioFocus
Documentation:
When enabled, Playing media sessions will request audio focus from the
Android system.

Name: kFeedBottomSyncStringRemoval
Documentation:
When enabled, causes the server to restrig the Sync Promo Banner for the
bottom of Feed to a Signin Promo.

Name: kAttributionReportingCrossAppWeb
Documentation:
Gate access to Attribution Reporting cross app and web APIs that allow
registering with a native attribution API.

Name: kSharedArrayBuffer
Documentation:
http://tc39.github.io/ecmascript_sharedmem/shmem.html
This feature is also enabled independently of this flag for cross-origin
isolated renderers.

Name: kOptimizationGuideUseContinueOnShutdownForPageContentAnnotations
Documentation:
Enables use of task runner with trait CONTINUE_ON_SHUTDOWN for page content
annotations on-device models.

Name: kOmniboxKeywordModeRefresh
Documentation: Feature used to enable the new keyword mode behavior.

Name: kAutofillShowTypePredictions
Documentation:
Controls attaching the autofill type predictions to their respective
element in the DOM.

Name: kCanPlayHls
Documentation:
Enables CanPlayType() (and other queries) for HLS MIME types. Note that
disabling this also causes navigation to .m3u8 files to trigger downloading
instead of playback.

Name: kSuggestionHoverFillShape
Documentation:
If enabled, the shape of the "hover fill" that's rendered for Omnibox
suggestions is updated to match CR23 guidelines.

Name: kWebFeed
Documentation: Feature that allows users to keep up with and consume web content.

Name: kEnterpriseConnectorsEnabledOnMGS
Documentation:
Controls whether the Enterprise Connectors policies should be read by
ConnectorsManager in Managed Guest Sessions.

Name: kPlatformAudioEncoder
Documentation: Allows usage of OS-level (platform) audio encoders.

Name: kClientHintsViewportWidth
Documentation: Enable `sec-ch-viewport-width` client hint.

Name: kWebNfc
Documentation:
Kill switch for the WebNFC feature. This feature can be enabled for all sites
using the kEnableExperimentalWebPlatformFeatures flag.
https://w3c.github.io/web-nfc/

Name: kBlockNotificationPromptsIfDisabledOnAppLevel
Documentation:
When enabled, blocks notifications permission prompt when Chrome doesn't
have app level Notification permission.

Name: kDeprecateCookiesTreeModel
Documentation:
Deprecate CookiesTReeModel and use BrowsingDataModel as the only browsing
data interface.

Name: kAutofillEnableUpdateVirtualCardEnrollment
Documentation:
When enabled, the user will have the ability to update the virtual card
enrollment of a credit card through their chrome browser after certain
autofill flows (for example, downstream and upstream), and from the settings
page.

Name: kUseCommonSelectPopup
Documentation: Used to enable the common select popup.

Name: kUrlScoringModel
Documentation: If enabled, creates Omnibox autocompete URL scoring model.

Name: kNtpPhotosModule
Documentation: If enabled, Google Photos module will be shown.

Name: kPrefetchNoVarySearch
Documentation:
If enabled, then navigation requests should check the match responses in the
prefetch cache by using the No-Vary-Search rules if No-Vary-Search header
is specified in prefetched responses.
Feature Meta bug: crbug.com/1378072.
No-Vary-Search explainer:
  https://github.com/WICG/nav-speculation/blob/main/no-vary-search.md

Name: kBlockPromptsIfDismissedOften
Documentation:
Enables or disables whether permission prompts are automatically blocked
after the user has explicitly dismissed them too many times.

Name: kJourneys
Documentation:
Enables Journeys in the Chrome History WebUI. This flag shouldn't be checked
directly. Instead use `IsJourneysEnabled()` for the system language filter.

Name: kShouldKillSessionOnAcceptChMalformed
Documentation: Whether to kill the session on Error::kAcceptChMalformed.

Name: kWebRtcIgnoreUnspecifiedColorSpace
Documentation:
Causes WebRTC to not set the color space of video frames on the receive side
in case it's unspecified. Otherwise we will guess that the color space is
BT709. http://crbug.com/1129243

Name: kUseDMSAAForTilesAndroidGL
Documentation:
Use DMSAA instead of MSAA for rastering tiles on Android GL backend. Note
that the above flag kUseDMSAAForTiles is used for Android Vulkan backend.

Name: kZeroSuggestPrefetching
Documentation: Enables prefetching of the zero prefix suggestions for eligible users on NTP.

Name: kEnableAccessibilityExposeIgnoredNodes
Documentation:
Enable exposing ignored nodes from Blink to the browser process AXTree.
This will allow us to simplify logic by eliminating the distiction between
"ignored and included in the tree" from "ignored and not included in the
tree".

Name: kPrivacySandboxSuppressDialogOnNonNormalBrowsers
Documentation:
When true, do not show any privacySandbox dialog when the browser isn't a
normal browser.

Name: kUmaBackgroundSessions
Documentation: If enabled, keep logging and reporting UMA while chrome is backgrounded.

Name: kEnablePersistentFilesystemInIncognito
Documentation: Enables persistent Filesystem API in incognito mode.

Name: kOobeMarketingAdditionalCountriesSupported
Documentation: Enables/disables marketing emails for other countries other than US,CA,UK.

Name: kAutofillOnlyCacheIsAutofilledOnFill
Documentation: Makes is_autofilled = true cached only after filling and not previewing.

Name: kEnableTabMuting
Documentation: Enables user control over muting tab audio from the tab strip.

Name: kForceHighPerformanceGPUForWebGL
Documentation:
Forces the attribute powerPreference to be set to "high-performance" for
WebGL contexts.

Name: kFeedHeaderStickToTop
Documentation: Feature that enables sticky header when users scroll down.

Name: kEnforceNoExecutableFileHandles
Documentation: Alphabetical:

Name: kEnableComposeLanguageBypass
Documentation: Controls whether the language check is bypassed for Compose.

Name: kWebApkInstallFailureNotification
Documentation: Enables WebAPK Install Failure Notification.

Name: kSideSearch
Documentation:
Enables the side search feature for Google Search. Presents recent Google
search results in a browser side panel.

Name: kAudioRendererAlgorithmParameters
Documentation: Enables customized AudioRendererAlgorithmParameters.

Name: kSkipLanguageDetectionOnEmptyContent
Documentation:
When enabled, language detection is skipped if no page content was captured
and chrome://translate-internals logs are updated to reflect this.

Name: kAutofillUseAddressRewriterInProfileSubsetComparison
Documentation:
Makes AutofillProfile::IsSubsetOfForFieldSet stop ignoring street address
types during comparison, and instead compares them using address rewriter
normalization.

Name: kSpeculationRulesPrefetchFuture
Documentation:
Controls whether the SpeculationRulesPrefetchFuture origin trial can be
enabled.

Name: kDynamicSchedulerForClients
Documentation: User to parameterize adjustments to clients' deadlines.

Name: kUseAXPositionForDocumentMarkers
Documentation:
Once this flag is enabled, a single codebase in AXPosition will be used for
handling document markers on all platforms, including the announcement of
spelling mistakes.

Name: kAsyncDns
Documentation: Enables the built-in DNS resolver.

Name: kWebAssemblyBaseline
Documentation: Enable WebAssembly baseline compilation (Liftoff).

Name: kAutofillEnableSupportForBetweenStreetsOrLandmark
Documentation:
Controls if Chrome support filling and importing address overflow and
landmark fields.
TODO(crbug.com/1441904) Remove once launched.

Name: kWebBluetooth
Documentation:
Controls whether the Web Bluetooth API is enabled:
https://webbluetoothcg.github.io/web-bluetooth/

Name: kSignedHTTPExchange
Documentation:
Origin-Signed HTTP Exchanges (for WebPackage Loading)
https://www.chromestatus.com/feature/5745285984681984

Name: kBackForwardCacheMemoryControls
Documentation:
BackForwardCacheMemoryControls is enabled only on Android to disable
BackForwardCache for lower memory devices due to memory limiations.

Name: kEnableCrossSiteFlagNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Creates a <double key + is_cross_site> NetworkIsolationKey which is used
to partition the HTTP cache. This key will have the following properties:
`top_frame_site_` -> the schemeful site of the top level page.
`frame_site_` -> absl::nullopt.
`is_cross_site_` -> a boolean indicating whether the frame site is
schemefully cross-site from the top-level site.

Name: kFlushPersistentSystemProfileOnWrite
Documentation:
Determines whether to schedule a flush of persistent histogram memory
immediately after writing a system profile to it.

Name: kOnDeviceClusteringVisitRanking
Documentation: Specifies how visits within clusters are ranked.

Name: kServiceWorkerSkipIgnorableFetchHandler
Documentation:
Enables skipping the service worker fetch handler if the fetch handler is
identified as ignorable.

Name: kAutofillEnableBirthdateParsing
Documentation:
Enables parsing for birthdate fields. Filling is not supported and parsing
is meant to prevent false positive credit card expiration dates.
TODO(crbug.com/1306654): Remove once launched.

Name: kClosedTabCache
Documentation:
All features in alphabetical order. The features should be documented
alongside the definition of their values in the .cc file.

Name: kFencedFramesEnforceFocus
Documentation: Enables browser-side focus verification when crossing fenced boundaries.

Name: kLCPVideoFirstFrame
Documentation: Enables reporting as LCP of the time the first frame of a video was painted.

Name: kAutofillEnableEmailHeuristicOnlyAddressForms
Documentation:
Controls if heuristic field parsing should be performed on email-only forms.
TODO(crbug.com/1493145): Remove when/if launched.

Name: kWebPaymentsExperimentalFeatures
Documentation:
Master toggle for all experimental features that will ship in the next
release.

Name: kAutofillParseAsync
Documentation:
If enabled, AutofillManager::ParseForm() isn't called synchronously.
Instead, all incoming events parse the form asynchronously and proceed
afterwards.
TODO(crbug.com/1309848) Remove once launched.

Name: kFriendlierSafeBrowsingSettingsEnhancedProtection
Documentation:
Enables the new text, layout, links, and icons on both the privacy guide
and on the security settings page for the enhanced protection security
option.

Name: kAccessibilityPerformanceTesting
Documentation: Disables use of performance improvements for experimental testing/dev.

Name: kCastDisableModelNameCheck
Documentation:
TODO(crbug.com/1198616): Remove model name checks for querying receiver
capabilities.

Name: kCustomizeChromeSidePanel
Documentation:
If enabled, Customize Chrome will be an option in the Unified Side Panel
when on the New Tab Page.

Name: kPauseBrowserInitiatedHeavyTrafficForP2P
Documentation:
When kPauseBrowserInitiatedHeavyTrafficForP2P is enabled, then a subset of
the browser initiated traffic may be paused if there is at least one active
P2P connection and the network is estimated to be congested. This feature is
intended to throttle only the browser initiated traffic that is expected to
be heavy (has large request/response sizes) when real time content might be
streaming over an active P2P connection.

Name: kFedCmWithoutWellKnownEnforcement
Documentation: Enables bypassing the well-known file enforcement.

Name: kSiteInstanceGroupsForDataUrls
Documentation:
When enabled, puts subframe data: URLs in a separate SiteInstance in the same
SiteInstanceGroup as the initiator.

Name: kWebAuthnICloudKeychainForActiveWithDrive
Documentation: Enabled in M118. Remove in or after M121.

Name: kDisableFrameNameUpdateOnNonCurrentRenderFrameHost
Documentation:
Feature to prevent name updates to RenderFrameHost (and by extension its
relevant BrowsingContextState) when it is not current (i.e. is in the
BackForwardCache or is pending delete). This primarily will affect the
non-legacy implementation of BrowsingContextState.

Name: kOmniboxSteadyStateHeight
Documentation:
If enabled, Omnibox "steady state" height is increased from 28 dp to 34 dp to
match CR23 guidelines.
TODO(manukh): Clean up feature code 9/12 when m117 reaches stable; we're
  launching the rest of CR23 in m117.

Name: kAppBannerTriggering
Documentation: Keys to use when querying the variations params.

Name: kTextEmbeddingPageContentAnnotations
Documentation: Enables the text embedding model to be annotated on every page load.

Name: kShadowKidsApiWithSafeSites
Documentation:
Runs a shadow no-op safe-sites call alongside kids-api call, to compare
latencies.

Name: kEnableNetworkServiceResourceBlockList
Documentation:
When enabled, resource requests will be evaluated against the Network
Service's block list for NetworkContexts that are not associated with an Off
the Record session. The block list is populated by the MaskedDomainList, so
"MaskedDomainList" will need to also be enabled for the block list to have
any contents.

Name: kAutofillContentEditables
Documentation:
If enabled, contenteditables are extracted and filled.
TODO(crbug.com/1490372): Cleanup when launched.

Name: kForceWebContentsDarkMode
Documentation: Automatically convert light-themed pages to use a Blink-generated dark theme

Name: kNvidiaVpSuperResolution
Documentation: Allow overlay swapchain to use NVIDIA video processor for super resolution.

Name: kPwaRestoreUi
Documentation: Enable the PWA Restore functionality.

Name: kWebRtcCombinedNetworkAndWorkerThread
Documentation: Combine WebRTC Network and Worker threads. More info at crbug.com/1373439.

Name: GetNotificationIphFeatureForFeature
Documentation: Returns the notification IPH feature for the given feature.

Name: kPseudoMetricsEffectFeature
Documentation:
Used to assess the reliability of field trial data by injecting different
levels of effects to pseudo metrics. These pseudo metrics are just mirrors of
some existing metrics.

Name: kDeleteOverwrittenDownloads
Documentation: Whether to delete downloads that are overwritten by others.

Name: kDefaultANGLEVulkan
Documentation: Default to using ANGLE's Vulkan backend.

Name: kCdmProcessSiteIsolation
Documentation:
Use per-CDM-type, per-user and per-site CDM processes (for library CDM). If
disabled, the CDM processes are only per-CDM-type, meaning different sites
using the same CDM type would share one CDM process.

Name: kAutofillRequireNameForProfileImport
Documentation:
Requires a profile to have non-empty full name to import it from a form.
TODO(crbug.com/1413205): Cleanup when launched.

Name: kBFCachePerformanceManagerPolicy
Documentation:
Policy that evicts the BFCache of pages that become non visible or the
BFCache of all pages when the system is under memory pressure.

Name: kWebViewVulkanIntermediateBuffer
Documentation:
Used to debug Android WebView Vulkan composite. Composite to an intermediate
buffer and draw the intermediate buffer to the secondary command buffer.

Name: kUIDebugTools
Documentation: Enables UI debugging tools such as shortcuts.

Name: kNtpHistoryClustersModuleDiscounts
Documentation:
If enabled, Discounts badge will show on the visit tile in the History
clusters module when available.

Name: kPrivateNetworkAccessForIframesWarningOnly
Documentation:
Enables Private Network Access checks in warning mode for iframe navigations.

Does nothing if `kPrivateNetworkAccessForIframes` is disabled.

If both this and `kPrivateNetworkAccessForIframes` are enabled, then PNA
preflight requests for iframe navigations are not required to succeed. If
one fails, a warning is simply displayed in DevTools.

Name: kFileSystemUrlNavigationForChromeAppsOnly
Documentation:
TODO(https://crbug.com/1360512): this feature creates a carveout for
enabling filesystem: URL navigation within Chrome Apps regardless of whether
kFileSystemUrlNavigation is enabled or not.

Name: kPrerender2NewLimitAndScheduler
Documentation:
Enables a new limit and scheduler for prerender triggers.
See crbug.com/1464021 for more details.

Name: kCommercePriceTrackingChipExperiment
Documentation: Feature flag for Price Tracking chip experiment

Name: kWriteBasicSystemProfileToPersistentHistogramsFile
Documentation:
Enables writing basic system profile to the persistent histograms files
earlier.

Name: kContextualPageActionReaderMode
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling reader mode action feature.

Name: kBoostImagePriority
Documentation:
Boost the priority of the first N not-small images.
crbug.com/1431169

Name: kOpaqueResponseBlockingErrorsForAllFetches
Documentation:
Treat ORB blocked responses to script-initiated fetches as errors too.
Complements ORB v0.2, which exempts script-initiated fetches.
Implementing ORB in Chromium is tracked in https://crbug.com/1178928

Name: kUACHOverrideBlank
Documentation:
Changes behavior of User-Agent Client Hints to send blank headers when the
User-Agent string is overridden, instead of disabling the headers altogether.

Name: kGlobalVaapiLock
Documentation:
Enable global VA-API lock. Disable this to use lock-free VA-API function
calls for thread safe backends.

Name: kSafelistFTPToRegisterProtocolHandler
Documentation:
When enabled, it adds FTP / FTPS / SFTP to the safe list for
registerProtocolHandler. This feature is enabled by default and meant to
be used as a killswitch.
https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/system-state.html#safelisted-scheme

Name: kFeatureNotificationGuide
Documentation: Main feature flag for the feature notification guide feature.

Name: kPrivateNetworkAccessForWorkersWarningOnly
Documentation:
Enables Private Network Access checks in warning mode for all types of web
workers.

Does nothing if `kPrivateNetworkAccessForWorkers` is disabled.

If both this and `kPrivateNetworkAccessForWorkers` are enabled, then PNA
preflight requests for workers are not required to succeed. If one fails, a
warning is simply displayed in DevTools.

Name: kClobberTriggersSRPZeroSuggest
Documentation:
Enables on-clobber (i.e., when the user clears the whole omnibox text)
zero-prefix suggestions on the SRP.

Name: kThreadedBodyLoader
Documentation: If enabled, reads and decodes navigation body data off the main thread.

Name: kLCPScriptObserver
Documentation:
If enabled, script execution is observed to determine script dependencies of
the LCP element.

Name: kWebAppBorderless
Documentation: Enable borderless mode for desktop PWAs. go/borderless-mode

Name: kAutofillPageLanguageDetection
Documentation:
Enables detection of language from Translate.
TODO(crbug/1150895): Cleanup when launched.

Name: kImageService
Documentation: Enabled by default because we are only using this as a killswitch.

Name: kPwaUpdateDialogForIcon
Documentation: Shows a confirmation dialog when updates to a PWAs icon has been detected.

Name: kDocumentPictureInPictureCapture
Documentation: Allows document picture-in-picture pages to request capture.

Name: kInvalidateLocalSurfaceIdPreCommit
Documentation:
Invalidate the `viz::LocalSurfaceId` on the browser side when the page is
navigated away. This flag serves as the kill-switch for the uncaught edge
cases in production.

Name: kPartitionHttpServerPropertiesByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Partitions HttpServerProperties based on the NetworkAnonymizationKey
associated with a request.

Name: kTrackingProtectionSettingsPageRollbackNotice
Documentation: Enables showing the rollback notice for Tracking Protection in settings.

Name: kWebRtcAllowInputVolumeAdjustment
Documentation:
TODO(crbug.com/1375239): Inactivate the flag gradually before deleting it.
When disabled, any WebRTC Audio Processing Module input volume recommendation
is ignored and no adjustment takes place.

Name: kJavaScriptArrayGrouping
Documentation: Enables the TC39 Array grouping proposal.

Name: kAutofillDisableAddressImport
Documentation: Kill switch for Autofill address import.

Name: kFillMultiLine
Documentation: chrome:flags switch for the multi line fill feature.

Name: kAllowSyncXHRInPageDismissal
Documentation: Allows for synchronous XHR requests during page dismissal

Name: kSyncUseFCMRegistrationTokensList
Documentation:
Sync invalidation switches.

Enables providing the list of FCM registration tokens in the commit request.

Name: kSplitCacheByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Splits cache entries by the request's NetworkIsolationKey if one is
available.
AboutFlagOs: kOsWin | kOsLinux | kOsLacros | kOsMac | kOsCrOS | kOsAndroid | kOsFuchsia

Name: kParcelTracking
Documentation: Feature flag for parcel tracking.

Name: kReclaimOldPrepaintTiles
Documentation:
When enabled, old prepaint tiles in the "eventually" region get reclaimed
after some time.

Name: kNavigationNetworkResponseQueue
Documentation:
When NavigationNetworkResponseQueue is enabled, the browser will schedule
some tasks related to navigation network responses in a kHigh priority
queue.

Name: kCompanionEnableNewBadgesInContextMenu
Documentation:
When search companion is enabled, show new badges on the context menu items
that open the companion.

Name: kFriendlierSafeBrowsingSettingsStandardProtection
Documentation:
Enables the new text and layout on both the privacy guide and on the
security settings page for the standard protection security option.

Name: kRecoverFromNeverSaveAndroid
Documentation:
Enables showing UI which allows users to easily revert their choice to
never save passwords on a certain website.

Name: kEnforceSHA256Checking
Documentation:
Enforce the use of SHA256 digest for signatures.
If disabled, the device may respond with a signature with SHA1 digest even
though a signature with SHA256 digest was requested in the challenge. This
allows for backwards compatibility with legacy Cast receivers.

Name: kDocumentProviderNoSetting
Documentation:
If enabled, the 'Show Google Drive Suggestions' setting is removed and Drive
suggestions are available to all clients who meet the other requirements.

Name: kWebAuthnSortRecognizedCredentials
Documentation: Sort discoverable credentials in the UI before showing.

Name: kAlpsForHttp2
Documentation:
Enables ALPS extension of TLS 1.3 for HTTP/2, see
https://vasilvv.github.io/tls-alps/draft-vvv-tls-alps.html and
https://vasilvv.github.io/httpbis-alps/draft-vvv-httpbis-alps.html.

Name: kNtpModulesOverflowScrollbar
Documentation: If true, displays a horizontal scrollbar on overflowing modules.

Name: kFeedFollowUiUpdate
Documentation: Feature that enables UI update for Follow.

Name: kAutofillEnablePaymentsAndroidBottomSheet
Documentation:
When enabled, the bottom sheet for save card and VCN enrollment will be
displayed instead of the info bar on Android.

Name: kThrottleDelayable
Documentation:
Based on the field trial parameters, this feature will override the value of
the maximum number of delayable requests allowed in flight. The number of
delayable requests allowed in flight will be based on the network's
effective connection type ranges and the
corresponding number of delayable requests in flight specified in the
experiment configuration. Based on field trial parameters, this experiment
may also throttle delayable requests based on the number of non-delayable
requests in-flight times a weighting factor.

Name: kThirdPartyPartitionedStorageAllowedByDefault
Documentation:
When enabled, partitioned storage will be allowed even if third-party cookies
are disabled by default. Partitioned storage will not be allowed if
third-party cookies are disabled due to a specific rule.

Name: kEnableEarlyHintsOnHttp11
Documentation: Enables Early Hints on HTTP/1.1.

Name: kAutofillEnableAblationStudy
Documentation:
Controls an ablation study in which autofill for addresses and payment data
can be suppressed.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformIntentionalUser
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling intentional user segment.

Name: kFeedExperimentIDTagging
Documentation: When enabled, allow tagging experiments with only an experiment ID.

Name: kPrivateNetworkAccessForIframes
Documentation:
Enables Private Network Access checks for iframe navigations.

The exact checks run are the same as for document subresources, and depend on
the state of other Private Network Access feature flags:
 - `kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequests`
 - `kPrivateNetworkAccessSendPreflights`
 - `kPrivateNetworkAccessRespectPreflightResults`

Name: kFencedFramesM120FeaturesPart2
Documentation:
Enable the new fenced frame-related features in M120. (These are
conditionally dependent on other fenced frame-related feature flags being
enabled.)
Part 2:
* Support leaving interest group from ad components.
* Relax the attestation requirement of post-impression beacons from Protected
Audience only to either Protected Audience or Attribution Reporting.
* Split off the `reserved.top_navigation` automatic beacon type into
  `reserved.top_navigation_start` and `reserved.top_navigation_commit.

Name: kTabGroupsSave
Documentation:
Enables users to explicitly save and recall tab groups.
https://crbug.com/1223929

Name: kFledgeLimitNumAuctions
Documentation:
If enabled, limits the number of FLEDGE auctions that can be run between page
load and unload -- any attempt to run more than this number of auctions will
fail (return null to JavaScript).

Name: kOnBeginFrameAcks
Documentation:
If enabled, CompositorFrameSinkClient::OnBeginFrame is also treated as the
DidReceiveCompositorFrameAck. Both in providing the Ack for the previous
frame, and in returning resources. While enabled we attempt to not send
separate Ack and ReclaimResources signals. However if while sending an
OnBeginFrame there is a pending Ack, then if the Ack arrives before the next
OnBeginFrame we will send the Ack immediately, rather than batching it.

Name: kAutofillUploadThrottling
Documentation: Autofill upload throttling is used for testing.

Name: kRecordWebAppDebugInfo
Documentation:
Enables recording additional web app related debugging data to be displayed
in: chrome://web-app-internals

Name: kOmniboxTriggerForNoStatePrefetch
Documentation:
Enables omnibox trigger no state prefetch. Only one of
kOmniboxTriggerForPrerender2 or kOmniboxTriggerForNoStatePrefetch can be
enabled in the experiment. If both are enabled, only
kOmniboxTriggerForPrerender2 takes effect.
TODO(crbug.com/1267731): Remove this flag once the experiments are completed.

Name: kAutomaticLazyFrameLoadingToAds
Documentation:
Apply lazy-loading to ad frames which have embeds likely impacting Core Web
Vitals.

Name: kSandboxExternalProtocolBlockedWarning
Documentation: Enabled in M100. Flag to be removed in M106

Name: kExpandedLayout
Documentation:
If enabled, Omnibox "expanded state" layout is updated to match CR23
guidelines.

Name: kWebContentsCaptureHiDpi
Documentation:
If active, enable HiDPI mode that increases the display scale factor
while capturing a low-resolution tab.

Name: kBackForwardCacheSize
Documentation:
Allows overriding the sizes of back/forward cache.
Sizes set via this feature's parameters take precedence over others.
Enables BackForwardCache size for
 - desktop: https://crbug.com/1291435.
 - android: https://crbug.com/1395281.

Name: kSafeBrowsingRemoveCookiesInAuthRequests
Documentation: Controls whether cookies are removed when the access token is present.

Name: kUkmReduceAddEntryIPC
Documentation:
This feature controls whether MojoUkmRecorder gets to decide whether to send
an IPC for AddEntry.

Name: kPrefetchFontLookupTables
Documentation: If enabled, font lookup tables will be prefetched on renderer startup.

Name: kAllowDownloadResumptionWithoutStrongValidators
Documentation: Whether download resumption is allowed when there are no strong validators.

Name: kExpandedStateHeight
Documentation: If enabled, Omnibox "expanded state" height is increased from 42 px to 44 px.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidInfrastructure
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether Messages for Android infrastucture components
are initialized. When this feature is disabled all individual message
implementations also fallback to Infobar implementations.

Name: kBackgroundFetch
Documentation: Kill switch for Background Fetch.

Name: kTouchpadAsyncPinchEvents
Documentation:
Enables async touchpad pinch zoom events. We check the ACK of the first
synthetic wheel event in a pinch sequence, then send the rest of the
synthetic wheel events of the pinch sequence as non-blocking if the first
event’s ACK is not canceled.

Name: kPageContentOptIn
Documentation: Enables or disables the page content opt-in and setting.

Name: kEnableVariableRefreshRateAlwaysOn
Documentation: Enables the variable refresh rate feature at all times.

Name: kActiveContentSettingExpiry
Documentation:
Lets the HostContentSettingsMap actively monitor when content settings expire
and delete them instantly. This also notifies observers that will, in turn,
terminate access to capabilities gated on those settings right away.

Name: kWebAuthnWindowsUIv6
Documentation: Delegate to Windows UI with webauthn.dll version six.

Name: kAutofillVoteForSelectOptionValues
Documentation:
If enabled, crowdsourcing considers not just the value V but also the human
readable text HRT of an <option value="V">HRT</option> for voting.
TODO(crbug.com/1395740). This is a kill switch, remove once the feature has
settled.

Name: kCdmStorageDatabase
Documentation:
This serves as an overall kill switch to kill CdmStorageDatabase. If
disabled, which it is by default, no operations will be routed through the
CdmStorage* path, even in the migration code that lives in MediaLicense* code
path.

Name: kUnifiedPasswordManagerLocalPasswordsMigrationWarning
Documentation:
Enables showing the warning about UPM migrating local passwords.
The feature is limited to Canary/Dev/Beta by a check in
local_passwords_migration_warning_util::ShouldShowWarning.

Name: kSplitAuthCacheByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Enables or defaults splittup up server (not proxy) entries in the
HttpAuthCache.

Name: kPriceTrackingIconColors
Documentation: Tonal colors for the expanded state of the price tracking chip on desktop.

Name: kRecordWebAudioEngagement
Documentation: Enables Media Engagement Index recording for Web Audio playbacks.

Name: kSyncFilterOutInactiveDevicesForSingleClient
Documentation:
Enables filtering out inactive devices which haven't sent DeviceInfo update
recently (depending on the device's pulse_interval and an additional margin).

Name: kSafeBrowsingSubresourceFilter
Documentation: The primary toggle to enable/disable the Safe Browsing Subresource Filter.

Name: kJavaScriptRabGsab
Documentation: Enables the Resizable ArrayBuffer proposal.

Name: kSearchEnginesPromoV3
Documentation:
This feature updates the triggering logic for the default search engine
choice promo. See crbug.com/1471643 for more details.

Name: kPasswordManagerEnableSenderService
Documentation:
Enables password sender service including outgoing password sharing
invitation sync data type.

Name: kSafeBrowsingPhishingClassificationESBThreshold
Documentation: Enables new ESB specific threshold fields in Visual TF Lite model files

Name: kPrivateNetworkAccessForWorkers
Documentation:
Enables Private Network Access checks for all types of web workers.

This affects initial worker script fetches, fetches initiated by workers
themselves, and service worker update fetches.

The exact checks run are the same as for other document subresources, and
depend on the state of other Private Network Access feature flags:

 - `kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequests`
 - `kPrivateNetworkAccessSendPreflights`
 - `kPrivateNetworkAccessRespectPreflightResults`

Name: kAutofillUpstream
Documentation:
Controls offering credit card upload to Google Payments. Cannot ever be
ENABLED_BY_DEFAULT because the feature state depends on the user's country.
The set of launched countries is listed in autofill_experiments.cc, and this
flag remains as a way to easily enable upload credit card save for testers,
as well as enable non-fully-launched countries on a trial basis.

Name: kRegisterJSSourceLocationBlockingBFCache
Documentation:
When enabled, Source Location blocking BFCache is captured
to send it to the browser.

Name: kWebRtcExposeNonStandardStats
Documentation: If enabled, expose non-standard stats in the WebRTC getStats API.

Name: kFeedDynamicColors
Documentation: Feature that enables dynamic colors in the feed.

Name: kEnableMachineLearningNeuralNetworkService
Documentation:
Enables the Web Machine Learning Neural Network Service to access hardware
acceleration out of renderer process. Explainer:
https://github.com/webmachinelearning/webnn/blob/main/explainer.md

Name: kPaintHoldingCrossOrigin
Documentation: Enable defer commits to avoid flash of unstyled content, for all navigation.

Name: kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsFromPrivate
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, requests to localhost initiated from non-secure
contexts in the `private` IP address space are blocked.

See also:
 - https://wicg.github.io/private-network-access/#integration-fetch
 - kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequests

Name: kAutofillEnableSupportForPhoneNumberTrunkTypes
Documentation:
If enabled, trunk prefix-related phone number types are added to the
supported and matching types of |PhoneNumber|. Local heuristics for these
types are enabled as well.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformTabResumptionRanker
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling tab resumption ranker.

Name: kAcceleratedStaticBitmapImageSerialization
Documentation:
Enables passing of mailbox backed Accelerated bitmap images to be passed
cross-process as mailbox references instead of serialized bitmaps in
shared memory.

Name: kImageServiceOptimizationGuideSalientImages
Documentation: Enabled the capability by default, can be used as a killswitch.

Name: kPeriodicBackgroundSync
Documentation: Whether web apps can run periodic tasks upon network connectivity.

Name: kFledgeRounding
Documentation:
Configures rounding on reported results from FLEDGE. This feature is intended
to be always enabled, but available to attach FeatureParams to so that we can
adjust the rounding setting via Finch.

Name: kCrossOriginOpenerPolicyByDefault
Documentation:
Shift's COOP's default from `unsafe-none` to `same-origin-allow-popups`.
https://github.com/mikewest/coop-by-default/

Whether download notification service uses new unified API based on offline
item and native persistence of notification IDs.

Name: kV8IgnitionElideRedundantTdzChecks
Documentation:
Elide redundant TDZ hole checks in bytecode. This only sets the V8 flag when
manually overridden.

Name: kAutofillEnableParsingEmptyPhoneNumberLabels
Documentation:
When enabled, phone number local heuristics match empty labels when looking
for composite phone number inputs. E.g. Phone number <input><input>.

Name: kAsyncStackAdTagging
Documentation:
Controls whether the AdTracker will look across async stacks to determine if
the currently running stack is ad related.

Name: kDiscardableMemoryBackingTrial
Documentation: Feature flag enabling the discardable memory backing trial.

Name: kInputMethodSettingsUiUpdate
Documentation:
Update of the virtual keyboard settings UI as described in
https://crbug.com/876901.

Name: kWebRtcApmTellsIfPlayoutReferenceIsNeeded
Documentation:
When enabled, the Audio Processing Module is used to determine whether the
playout reference is needed. Otherwise the decision is based on
`media::AudioProcessingSettings`.

Name: kAdAuctionSignals
Documentation:
Controls the capturing of the Ad-Auction-Signals header, and the maximum
allowed Ad-Auction-Signals header value.

Name: kCustomWebSignInInterceptForSupervisedUsers
Documentation:
Enable different web sign in interception behaviour for supervised users:

1. Supervised user signs in to existing signed out Profile: show modal
   explaining that supervision features will apply.
2. Supervised user signs in as secondary account in existing signed in
   Profile

Only affects Desktop platforms.

Name: kAutofillStructuredFieldsDisableAddressLines
Documentation:
If this feature is enabled, the AddressFieldParser does NOT try to parse
address lines once it has found a street name and house number or other
combinations of fields that indicate that an address form uses structured
addresses. This should be the default in all countries with fully supported
structured addresses. However, if a country is not sufficiently modeled,
autofill may still do the right thing if it recognizes "Street name, house
number, address line 2" as a sequence.
TODO(crbug.com/1441904) Remove once launched.

Name: kPrivateAggregationApi
Documentation:
Enables the Private Aggregation API. Note that this API also requires the
`kPrivacySandboxAggregationService` to be enabled to successfully send
reports.

Name: kUdpSocketPosixAlwaysUpdateBytesReceived
Documentation:
When enabled, UDPSocketPosix increments the global counter of bytes received
every time bytes are received, instead of using a timer to batch updates.
This should reduce the number of wake ups and improve battery consumption.
TODO(https://crbug.com/1189805): Cleanup the feature after verifying that it
doesn't negatively affect performance.

Name: kProcessSharingWithDefaultSiteInstances
Documentation:
Enables process sharing for sites that do not require a dedicated process
by using a default SiteInstance. Default SiteInstances will only be used
on platforms that do not use full site isolation.
Note: This feature is mutally exclusive with
kProcessSharingWithStrictSiteInstances. Only one of these should be enabled
at a time.

Name: kWebAssemblyGarbageCollection
Documentation:
Enable support for the WebAssembly Garbage Collection proposal:
https://github.com/WebAssembly/gc.

Name: kFencedFrames
Documentation:
Enable the <fencedframe> element; see crbug.com/1123606. Note that enabling
this feature does not automatically expose this element to the web, it only
allows the element to be enabled by the runtime enabled feature, for origin
trials.

Name: kWebAssemblyTiering
Documentation: Enable WebAssembly tiering (Liftoff -> TurboFan).

Name: kAutofillUseI18nAddressModel
Documentation:
Enables using the newer i18n address model, overriding the legacy one.
This includes:
- Using newer i18n address format strings.

Name: kRefreshExpirationDate
Documentation: Whether download expiration date will be refreshed on resumption.

Name: kLCPAnimatedImagesReporting
Documentation:
Enables reporting as LCP of the time the first frame of an animated image was
painted.

Name: kResamplingScrollEventsExperimentalPrediction
Documentation:
Enables resampling of scroll events using an experimental latency of +3.3ms
instead of the original -5ms.

Name: kNormalizeSearchSuggestions
Documentation:
If enabled, SearchProvider uses `normalized_term` instead of `term` from the
`keyword_search_terms` table. `normalized_term` is the original search term
in lower case with extra whitespace characters collapsed. To ensure
suggestions from SearchProvider continue to get deduped with those from
ShortcutsProvider, AutocompleteMatch::GURLToStrippedGURL uses the normalized
term to build the destination URLs so they are identical despite case
mismatches in the terms.

Name: kMoreAggressiveSolidColorDetection
Documentation:
Try to play a longer list of ops before giving up in solid color analysis for
tiles.

Name: kHeavyAdInterventionWarning
Documentation:
Enables or disables reporting on the intervention that unloads ad iframes
with intensive resource usage.

Name: kBlockRepeatedAutoReauthnPrompts
Documentation:
Once the user has auto re-authenticated, automatically block subsequent auto
re-authn prompts within the next 10 minutes.

Name: kDownloadTailoredWarnings
Documentation:
The kill switch for download tailored warnings. The main control is on the
server-side.

Name: kDispatchBeforeUnloadOnFreeze
Documentation:
When enabled, the beforeunload handler is dispatched when a frame is frozen.
This allows the browser to know whether discarding the frame could result in
lost user data, at the cost of extra CPU usage. The feature will be removed
once we have determine whether the CPU cost is acceptable.

Name: kDynamicColorGamut
Documentation:
When wide color gamut content from the web is encountered, promote our
display to wide color gamut if supported.

Name: kSpareTab
Documentation:
SpareTab is enabled by default for configuring renderer initialization
through field trial. Users of spareTab should declare their own field trial
feature.

Name: kVaapiVideoMinResolutionForPerformance
Documentation:
Ensure the advertised minimum supported resolution is larger than or equal to
a given one (likely QVGA + 1) for certain codecs/modes and platforms, for
performance reasons. This does not affect JPEG decoding.

Name: kWebUsb
Documentation:
Controls whether the WebUSB API is enabled:
https://wicg.github.io/webusb

Name: kPrivateNetworkAccessSendPreflights
Documentation:
Enables sending CORS preflight requests ahead of private network requests.
See: https://wicg.github.io/private-network-access/#cors-preflight

Name: kEnablePortBoundCookies
Documentation: Enables binding of cookies to the port that originally set them by default.

Name: kSendCnameAliasesToSubresourceFilterFromBrowser
Documentation:
Enables or disables performing SubresourceFilter checks from the Browser
against any aliases for the requested URL found from DNS CNAME records.

Name: kPartitionDomainReliabilityByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation: Partitions Domain Reliability beacons and upload by NetworkIsolationKey.

Name: kRealboxMatchSearchboxTheme
Documentation:
If enabled, the NTP "realbox" will have same border/drop shadow in hover
state as searchbox.

Name: kWebNotesStylizeEnabled
Documentation: Main feature for the Web Notes Stylize project.

Name: kStandardCompliantHostCharacters
Documentation:
When enabled, Chrome uses URL Standard compliant mode to
handle punctuation characters in URL host part.
https://crbug.com/1416013 for details.

Name: kHistoryClustersUseContinueOnShutdown
Documentation: Enables use of task runner with trait CONTINUE_ON_SHUTDOWN.

Name: kSearchReadyOmniboxAllowQueryEdit
Documentation:
If enabled, allows Search Ready Omnibox to populate original search query
when the user presses the <edit> button on EditUrl suggestion.

Name: kGPayAppDynamicUpdate
Documentation:
If enabled, the GooglePayPaymentApp handles communications between the native
GPay app and the browser for dynamic updates on shipping and payment data.

Name: kEnableBrowsingDataLifetimeManager
Documentation:
Enable BrowsingDataLifetimeManager that periodically delete browsing data as
defined by the BrowsingDataLifetime policy.

Name: kMediaDrmPreprovisioningAtStartup
Documentation:
Determines if MediaDrmOriginIdManager should attempt to pre-provision origin
IDs at startup (whenever a profile is loaded). Also used by tests that
disable it so that the tests can setup before pre-provisioning is done.
Note: Has no effect if kMediaDrmPreprovisioning feature is disabled.

Name: kNewEvSignalsEnabled
Documentation:
Feature flag for new private SecureConnect functions exposing additional
device signals.

Name: kNtpSingleRowShortcuts
Documentation: If enabled, shortcuts will be shown in a wide single row.

Name: kNtpDriveModuleShowSixFiles
Documentation: If enabled, six files show in the NTP Drive module, instead of three.

Name: kEnableLensPing
Documentation:
Enables the ping for Lens Standalone, which is sent before the Standalone
request.

Name: kJourneysIncludeSyncedVisits
Documentation: Enables visits from other synced devices to be included in clusters.

Name: kCanvasCompressHibernatedImage
Documentation: Whether to losslessly compress the resulting image after canvas hibernation.

Name: kAudioFocusSessionGrouping
Documentation:
Enables Audio Focus grouping which means that multiple media sessions can
share audio focus at the same time provided that they have the same group id.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformDeviceSwitcher
Documentation: Feature flag for device switcher segment.

Name: kKeepAliveInBrowserMigration
Documentation:
Kill-switch for the fetch keepalive request infra migration.
If enabled, all keepalive requests will be proxied via the browser process.
Design Doc: https://bit.ly/chromium-keepalive-migration
Tracker: https://crbug.com/1356128

Name: kDecodeScriptSourceOffThread
Documentation:
If enabled, script source text will be decoded and hashed off the main
thread.

Name: kAutofillDisableFilling
Documentation: Kill switch for Autofill filling.

Name: kWebAssemblyTailCall
Documentation:
Enable support for the WebAssembly tail-call proposal:
https://github.com/WebAssembly/tail-call.

Name: kFedCmIdPRegistration
Documentation: Enables usage of the FedCM IdP Registration API.

Name: kV8VmFuture
Documentation: Enables future V8 VM features

Name: kInterestFeedV2
Documentation:
InterestFeedV2 takes precedence over InterestFeedContentSuggestions.
InterestFeedV2 is cached in ChromeCachedFlags. If the default value here is
changed, please update the cached one's default value in CachedFeatureFlags.

Name: kPushMessagingDisallowSenderIDs
Documentation: Feature flag to disallow creation of push messages with GCM Sender IDs.

Name: kDestroyProfileOnBrowserClose
Documentation:
Destroy profiles when their last browser window is closed, instead of when
the browser exits.
On Lacros the feature is enabled only for secondary profiles, check the
implementation of `ProfileManager::ProfileInfo::FromUnownedProfile()`.

Name: kAndroidMediaPickerAdoption
Documentation: Controls how the Android Media Picker will be introduced.

Name: kSimulateClickOnAXFocus
Documentation:
TODO(accessibility): This flag is set to accommodate JAWS on Windows so they
can adjust to us not simulating click events on a focus action. It is in the
process of being removed completely and is currently disabled by default on
all platforms. We want to allow users to manually re-enable this behavior for
the next few months in case their users discover issues they still have to
fix. It should be removed by 9/17/2023.

See https://crbug.com/1326622 for more info.

Name: kPartitionedCookies
Documentation:
When enabled, sites can opt-in to having their cookies partitioned by
top-level site with the Partitioned attribute. Partitioned cookies will only
be sent when the browser is on the same top-level site that it was on when
the cookie was set.

Name: kJavaScriptPromiseWithResolvers
Documentation: Enables the Promise.withResolvers proposal.

Name: kForceStartupSigninPromo
Documentation: Features to trigger the startup sign-in promo at boot.

Name: kIOSForceTranslateEnabled
Documentation: Controls whether force translate is enabled on iOS.

Name: kGroupingFrameworkForNonZPS
Documentation:
When enabled, uses the grouping framework with prefixed suggestions (i.e.
autocomplete_grouper_sections.h) to limit and group (but not sort) matches.

Name: kConsumeCompileHints
Documentation:
Load V8_COMPILE_HINTS optimization data from OptimizationGuide and
transmit it to V8. See `ProduceCompileHints` for the data producer side of
this feature.

Name: kMmapSafeBrowsingDatabase
Documentation:
If enabled, the Safe Browsing database will be stored in a separate file and
mapped into memory.

Name: kChromeLabs
Documentation: Enables Chrome Labs menu in the toolbar. See https://crbug.com/1145666

Name: kSwipeToMoveCursor
Documentation: Android only feature, for swipe to move cursor.

Name: kPermissionAuditing
Documentation:
Keep a client-side log of when websites access permission-gated capabilities
to allow the user to audit usage.

Name: kAlmanacGameMigration
Documentation: Enables App Discovery Service to use the Almanac system for fetching games.

Name: kAddTaskLeewayFeature
Documentation:
Under this feature, a non-zero leeway is added to delayed tasks. Along with
DelayPolicy, this affects the time at which a delayed task runs.

Name: kAutofillEnableAndroidNKeyForFidoAuthentication
Documentation: All features in alphabetical order.

Name: kSiteIsolationForPasswordSites
Documentation:
Controls a mode for dynamically process-isolating sites where the user has
entered a password.  This is intended to be used primarily when full site
isolation is turned off.  To check whether this mode is enabled, use
SiteIsolationPolicy::IsIsolationForPasswordSitesEnabled() rather than
checking the feature directly, since that decision is influenced by other
factors as well.

Name: kFeedSportsCard
Documentation: Feature that enables sports card in the feed.

Name: kEnableCompose
Documentation: Controls whether the Compose feature is available

Name: kAutofillAccountProfileStorage
Documentation:
When enabled, creating new kAccount profiles becomes possible for eligible
users. Moreover, users are prompted to migrate existing kLocalOrSyncable
profiles to the kAccount storage.
TODO(crbug.com/1423319): Remove once launched.

Name: kExcludeLowEntropyImagesFromLCP
Documentation:
Controls whether LCP calculations should exclude low-entropy images. If
enabled, then the associated parameter sets the cutoff, expressed as the
minimum number of bits of encoded image data used to encode each rendered
pixel. Note that this is not just pixels of decoded image data; the rendered
size includes any scaling applied by the rendering engine to display the
content.

Name: kEnsureAllowBindingsIsAlwaysForWebUI
Documentation:
TODO(https://crbug.com/1442346): Feature flag to guard extra CHECKs put in
place to ensure that the AllowBindings API on RenderFrameHost is not called
for documents outside of WebUI ones.

Name: kUseMediaHistoryStore
Documentation: Enables using the media history store to store media engagement metrics.

Name: kUsernameFirstFlowWithIntermediateValues
Documentation:
Enables tolerating intermediate fields like OTP or CAPTCHA
between username and password fields in Username First Flow.

Name: kMergeSubprocessMetricsOnBgAndFg
Documentation:
Determines whether to merge histograms from child processes when Chrome is
backgrounded/foregrounded. Only on Android.

Name: kStopInBackground
Documentation:
Freeze scheduler task queues in background after allowed grace time.
"stop" is a legacy name.

Name: kMediaLearningFramework
Documentation:
Enables the general purpose media machine learning framework. Adds reporting
only; does not change media behavior.

Name: kTranslateMessageUI
Documentation: Features

Name: kCustomizeChromeWallpaperSearch
Documentation: If enabled, shows wallpaper search within the Cusotmize Chrome Side Panel.

Name: kUserBypassFeedback
Documentation: Feature to enable the feedback button in the User Bypass UI.

Name: kSyncPollWithoutDelayOnStartup
Documentation:
If enabled, and a poll GetUpdates request is scheduled on browser startup,
there won't be an additional delay.

Name: kAutofillAssociateForms
Documentation:
If enabled, the two most recent address forms and the most recent credit card
forms, which were submitted on the same origin, are associated with each
other. The association only happens if at most `kAutofillAssociateFormsTTL`
time passes between all submissions.

Name: kAutofillPreventOverridingPrefilledValues
Documentation:
When enabled, Autofill would not override the field values that were either
filled by Autofill or on page load.
TODO(crbug/1275649): Remove once experiment is finished.

Name: kPrivacySandboxFirstPartySetsUI
Documentation: Enables the First Party Sets UI.

Name: kDelayAsyncScriptExecution
Documentation:
If enabled, async script execution will be delayed than usual.
See https://crbug.com/1340837.

Name: kDedicatedMediaServiceThread
Documentation: Runs the media service in the GPU process on a dedicated thread.

Name: kScrollSnapPreferCloserCovering
Documentation:
When enabled, if a snap container is snapping to a large snap area, it will
snap to the closest covering position if it is closer than the aligned
position. This avoid unnecessary jumps that attempt to honor the
scroll-snap-align value.

Name: kDomainSuggestions
Documentation:
Feature to determine if the HQP should double as a domain provider by
suggesting up to the provider limit for each of the user's highly visited
domains.

Name: kWebAuthnAndroidCredManForHybrid
Documentation: Use the Android 14 Credential Manager API for hybrid requests.

Name: kConsumeCodeCacheOffThread
Documentation: Controls off-thread code cache consumption.

Name: kMediaOptimizer
Documentation:
Enable the prototype global optimization of tuneables via finch.  See
media/base/tuneable.h for how to create tuneable parameters.

Name: kVaapiVP8Encoder
Documentation: Enable VA-API hardware encode acceleration for VP8.

Name: kSplitCacheByIncludeCredentials
Documentation: Splits cache entries by the request's includeCredentials.

Name: kAutofillUpstreamAllowAllEmailDomains
Documentation:
When enabled, Chrome allows credit card upload to Google Payments, no matter
the user's email domain.

Name: kAutofillParsingPatternProvider
Documentation:
If enabled, use the parsing patterns from a JSON file for heuristics, rather
than the hardcoded ones from autofill_regex_constants.cc.
The specific pattern set is controlled by the
`kAutofillParsingPatternActiveSource` parameter.

This feature is intended to work with kAutofillPageLanguageDetection.

Enabling this feature is also a prerequisite for emitting shadow metrics.
TODO(crbug/1121990): Remove once launched.

Name: kDisablePrivacySandboxPrompts
Documentation:
Disables any Privacy Sandbox related prompts. Should only be used for testing
purposes. This feature is used to support external automated testing using
Chrome, where additional prompts break behavior expectations.

Name: kSecurePaymentConfirmation
Documentation:
Browser-side feature flag for Secure Payment Confirmation (SPC) that also
controls the render side feature state. SPC is not currently available on
Linux or ChromeOS, as it requires platform authenticator support.

Name: kLogUrlScoringSignals
Documentation: Omnibox ML scoring.

Name: kExpandedStateShape
Documentation:
If enabled, Omnibox "expanded state" corner radius is increased from 8px to
16px.

Name: kAutofillEnableSupportForAddressOverflowAndLandmark
Documentation:
Controls if Chrome support filling and importing address overflow and
landmark fields.
TODO(crbug.com/1441904) Remove once launched.

Name: kKeyPressMonitoring
Documentation:
Keypress detection which serves as input to noise suppression methods
in WebRTC clients. This functionality is enabled by default but it can be
disabled experemantally by using --disable-features=KeyPressMonitoring.

Name: kLogAccountEnhancedProtectionStateInProtegoPings
Documentation: Enable logging of the account enhanced protection setting in Protego pings.

Name: kIncognitoNtpRevamp
Documentation: When enabled, users will see updated UI in Incognito NTP

Name: kCanvasContextLostInBackground
Documentation:
Enables canvas to free its resources by default when it's running in
the background.

Name: kAutofillEnableDependentLocalityParsing
Documentation:
Controls if Autofill parses ADDRESS_HOME_DEPENDENT_LOCALITY.
TODO(crbug.com/1157405): Remove once launched.

Name: kWebRtcSendPacketBatch
Documentation: Feature flag for batching sending of WebRTC RTP UDP packets.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformPowerUserFeature
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling Power user segmentation.

Name: kDestroySystemProfiles
Documentation:
DestroyProfileOnBrowserClose only covers deleting regular (non-System)
Profiles. This flags lets us destroy the System Profile, as well.

Name: kNewQuotaEvictionRoutine
Documentation:
A kill switch for the new approach to storage eviction on low disk space. See
crbug.com/1382847

Name: kTimeoutTcpConnectAttempt
Documentation:
Enables a timeout on individual TCP connect attempts, based on
the parameter values.

Name: kMediaLearningSmoothnessExperiment
Documentation:
Enables the smoothness prediction experiment.  Requires
kMediaLearningFramework to be enabled also, else it does nothing.

Name: kDynamicMaxAutocomplete
Documentation:
Feature used to cap max suggestions to a dynamic limit based on how many URLs
would be shown. E.g., show up to 10 suggestions if doing so would display no
URLs; else show up to 8 suggestions if doing so would include 1 or more URLs.

Name: kWebAuthnAndroidHybridClientUi
Documentation:
Enable UI options to explicitly invoke hybrid CTAP authentication on
Android.

Name: kWebBluetoothNewPermissionsBackend
Documentation:
Controls whether Web Bluetooth should use the new permissions backend. The
new permissions backend uses ObjectPermissionContextBase, which is used by
other device APIs, such as WebUSB. When enabled,
WebBluetoothWatchAdvertisements and WebBluetoothGetDevices blink features are
also enabled.

Name: kFedCmIdpSigninStatusEnabled
Documentation:
Enables the IDP signin status API for use with FedCM, including avoiding
network requests when not signed in and mismatch handling.

Name: kTranslate
Documentation:
This allows the user to disable translate by using the
`--disable-features=Translate` command-line flag.

Name: kTabSearchRecentlyClosed
Documentation: Controls feature parameters for Tab Search's `Recently Closed` entries.

Name: kLowDelayVideoRenderingOnLiveStream
Documentation: Enables low-delay video rendering in media pipeline on "live" stream.

Name: kAutofillEnableRemadeDownstreamMetrics
Documentation: When enabled, some extra metrics logging for Autofill Downstream will start.

Name: kFirstPartySets
Documentation: Enables usage of First Party Sets to determine cookie availability.

Name: kDefaultTypedNavigationsToHttps
Documentation: Navigation experiments.

Name: kPepperCrossOriginRedirectRestriction
Documentation: Kill-switch to introduce a compatibility breaking restriction.

Name: kDeleteExpiredDownloads
Documentation: Whether to delete expired download.

Name: kWebAudioSinkSelection
Documentation:
A server-side switch for the output device (sink) selection in Web Audio API.
This enables the selection via the AudioContext constructor and also via
AudioContext.setSinkId() method.

Name: kAutofillEnableFpanRiskBasedAuthentication
Documentation:
When enabled, server card retrieval will begin with a risk-based check
instead of jumping straight to CVC or biometric auth.

Name: kConfirmSuggestionRemovals
Documentation:
The features should be documented alongside the definition of their values in
the .cc file.

Name: kUseAAudioDriver
Documentation:
Enables loading and using AAudio instead of OpenSLES on compatible devices,
for audio output streams.

Name: kUsernameFirstFlowStoreSeveralValues
Documentation:
Enables storing more possible username values in the LRU cache. Part of the
`kUsernameFirstFlowWithIntermediateValues` feature.

Name: kQueryTilesSegmentation
Documentation: Whether segmentation rules are applied to query tiles.

Name: kPaintPreviewDemo
Documentation:
Used to enable a main menu item on Android that captures and displays a paint
preview for the current page. The paint preview UI will be dismissed on back
press and all associated stored files deleted. This intended to test whether
capturing and playing paint preview works on a specific site.

Name: kLoadingPhaseBufferTimeAfterFirstMeaningfulPaint
Documentation:
A feature to control whether the loading phase should be extended beyond
First Meaningful Paint by a configurable buffer.

Name: kMerchantWidePromotion
Documentation: Feature flag for Merchant Wide promotion.

Name: kClientHintsDPR_DEPRECATED
Documentation: Enable legacy `dpr` client hint.

Name: kOmniboxHistoryClusterProvider
Documentation:
Enables the `HistoryClusterProvider` to surface Journeys as a suggestion row
instead of an action chip. Enabling this won't actually disable
`kOmniboxAction` but for user experiments, the intent is to only have 1
enabled. `kJourneys` must also be enabled for this to take effect.

Name: kAutofillEnableZipOnlyAddressForms
Documentation:
Some countries like BR and MX have address forms with only a zip code.
If this feature is enabled, those fields may be classified as zip code fields
for users who are located in BR/MX, even though our typical policy is to
disable local heuristics for forms with <3 fields.

Name: kAutofillEnableManualFallbackForVirtualCards
Documentation: When enabled, enable manual falling component for virtual cards on Android.

Name: kMetricsReportingFeature
Documentation: TODO(crbug.com/1068796): Replace kMetricsReportingFeature with a better name.

Name: kSafeBrowsingSkipImageCssFont
Documentation:
Controls whether to skip Safe Browsing checks on images, CSS and font URLs in
renderer URL loader throttle.

Name: kExtensionsMenuInAppMenu
Documentation:
Create new Extensions app menu option (removing "More Tools -> Extensions")
with submenu to manage extensions and visit chrome web store.

Name: kSynchronousPageFlipTesting
Documentation:
Indicates whether DrmOverlayManager should used the synchronous API to
perform pageflip tests.

Name: kFeedNoViewCache
Documentation: When enabled, no view cache is used.

Name: kNtpHistoryClustersModuleBeginTimeDuration
Documentation: Dummy feature to set kNtpHistoryClustersModuleBeginTimeDurationHoursParam.

Name: kFileSystemAccessDoNotOverwriteOnMove
Documentation:
TODO(crbug.com/1381621): Remove this flag eventually.
When enabled, move() will result in a promise rejection when the specified
destination to move to exists. This feature was disabled since it does not
match standard POSIX behavior. See discussion at
https://github.com/whatwg/fs/pull/10#issuecomment-1322993643.

Name: kLinkPreviewNavigation
Documentation: Enables the Link Preview specific new navigation code path.

Name: kGpuCleanupInBackground
Documentation:
When the application is in background, whether to perform immediate GPU
cleanup when executing deferred requests.

Name: kMediaStreamTrackTransfer
Documentation: Allow cross-context transfer of MediaStreamTracks.

Name: kPrefetchUseContentRefactor
Documentation:
If enabled, then prefetch requests from speculation rules should use the code
in content/browser/preloading/prefetch/ instead of
chrome/browser/preloadingprefetch/prefetch_proxy/.

Name: kBrowsingTopicsParameters
Documentation:
Decoupled with the main `kBrowsingTopics` feature, so it allows us to
decouple the server side configs.

Name: kSupportSearchSuggestionForPrerender2
Documentation:
This flag controls whether to trigger prerendering when the default search
engine suggests to prerender a search result.

Name: kSyncEntityMetadataRecordDeletedByVersionOnLocalDeletion
Documentation: Flag to enable setting `deleted_by_version` on a `EntityMetadata`.

Name: kAllowMediaCodecSoftwareDecoder
Documentation:
Allow the media pipeline to prioritize the software decoder provided by
MediaCodec, instead of the built-in software decoders. This is only enabled
for platforms which shows worse performance when using the built-in software
decoders, e.g. Cast on ATV.

Name: kDisableThirdPartyStoragePartitioningDeprecationTrial
Documentation:
Kill-switch for a deprecation trial that unpartitions storage in third-party
contexts under the registered top-level site. If
`kDisableThirdPartyStoragePartitioningDeprecationTrial` is enabled, the
deprecation trial information can be sent to and enabled in the browser
process (i.e. when the base::Feature is enabled, the deprecation trial is
enabled in the browser process too).

Name: kAutofillAcrossIframesIos
Documentation: All features in alphabetical order.

Name: kUseButtonTranslateBubbleUi
Documentation: This feature uses the existing UI for the Full Page Translate bubble.

Name: kSecurePaymentConfirmationUseCredentialStoreAPIs
Documentation:
Used to control whether SecurePaymentConfirmation is able to rely on OS-level
credential store APIs, or if it can only rely on the user-profile database.

Name: kWebRTCColorAccuracy
Documentation:
Inform webrtc with correct video color space information whenever
possible.

Name: kRedWarningSurvey
Documentation: Enables HaTS surveys for users encountering red warnings.

Name: kBackForwardCacheUnloadAllowed
Documentation:
Controls the interaction between back/forward cache and
unload. When enabled, pages with unload handlers may enter the
cache.

Name: kNotificationGesturesUpdate
Documentation: Used to enable gesture changes for notifications.

Name: kAutofillEnableSupportForLandmark
Documentation:
Controls if Chrome support filling and importing landmarks.
TODO(crbug.com/1441904) Remove once launched.

Name: kCodeBasedRBD
Documentation: Feature flag for Code-based RBD.

Name: kMlUrlScoring
Documentation:
If enabled, runs the ML scoring model to assign new relevance scores to the
URL suggestions and reranks them.

Name: kSpdyHeadersToHttpResponseUseBuilder
Documentation: Enables a more efficient implementation of SpdyHeadersToHttpResponse().

Name: kChangePictureVideoMode
Documentation: Enables change picture video mode.

Name: kTimedHTMLParserBudget
Documentation:

Name: kAvoidUnnecessaryBeforeUnloadCheckSync
Documentation:
The following two features, when enabled, result in the browser process only
asking the renderer process to run beforeunload handlers if it knows such
handlers are registered. The two slightly differ in what they do and how
they behave:
. `kAvoidUnnecessaryBeforeUnloadCheckPostTask` in this case content continues
  to report a beforeunload handler is present (even though it isn't). When
  asked to dispatch the beforeunload handler, a post task is used (rather
  than going to the renderer).
. `kAvoidUnnecessaryBeforeUnloadCheckSync` in this case content does not
  report a beforeunload handler is present. A ramification of this is
  navigations that would normally check beforeunload handlers before
  continuing will not, and navigation will synchronously continue.
Only one should be used (if both are set, the second takes precedence). The
second is unsafe for Android WebView (and thus entirely disabled via
ContentBrowserClient::SupportsAvoidUnnecessaryBeforeUnloadCheckSync()),
because the embedder may trigger reentrancy, which cannot be avoided.

collected into the profile's `token_quality()`.

Name: kLinkPreview

Name: kAutofillAllowDuplicateFormSubmissions
Documentation:

below feature allows duplicate form submissions.

Name: kDisableProcessReuse

Name: kPrerender2MainFrameNavigation
Documentation:
Enables the same-origin main frame navigation in a prerendered page.
See https://crbug.com/1239281.

Name: kSHA1ServerSignature
Documentation:
If enabled allows the use of SHA-1 by the server for signatures
in the TLS handshake.

Name: kCwsDarkLogo

(see crbug.com/1329552). This is enabled by default to allow finch to disable
this NTP treatment in the case of unexpected regressions.

Name: kTextFragmentAnchor

Name: kWebRtcUseGpuMemoryBufferVideoFrames

represents a set of frames that can script each other. Currently, Chrome does

optimization target. This is useful in exceptional situations when a bad

immediate remedy is needed to stop serving those versions.

Name: kUpdatedConnectionSecurityIndicators

used, on non-Android platforms this is controlled through the

Name: kAutofillDisableSilentProfileUpdates

Name: EnableContextMenuInLensSidePanel

such as Translate) of the local/regional language(s) corresponding to the

Name: kWebAuthnPRFEvalDuringCreate

Name: kSearchWebInSidePanel

So users are not forced to switch to a new tab to view the search results

Name: kAutofillEnableServerIban

Name: kForceProduceCompileHints

Name: kAutoApproveSharedPasswordUpdatesFromSameSender

- allow-top-navigation-to-custom-protocols
- allow-top-navigation-with-user-gesture (+ user gesture)

Motivation:
Developers are surprised that a sandboxed iframe can navigate and/or
redirect the user toward an external application.
General iframe navigation in sandboxed iframe are not blocked normally,
because they stay within the iframe. However they can be seen as a popup or
a top-level navigation when it leads to opening an external application. In
this case, it makes sense to extend the scope of sandbox flags, to block
malvertising.

Implementation bug: https://crbug.com/1253379
I2S: https://groups.google.com/a/chromium.org/g/blink-dev/c/-t-f7I6VvOI

codebase is ignored and the new password view subpage is force enabled. When
enabled, Sync machinery will read and writes password notes to the
`encrypted_notes_backup` field inside the PasswordSpecifics proto. Together
with the logic on the server. this protects against notes being overwritten
by legacy clients not supporting password notes.
This feature is added here instead of the password manager codebase to avoid
cycle dependencies.
This feature is used in Credential Provider Extension on iOS. Keep the
default value in sync with the default value in
ios/chrome/credential_provider_extension/ui/feature_flags.mm.

Name: kUserMediaCaptureOnFocus
Documentation:
If enabled, GetUserMedia API will only work when the concerned tab is in
focus

Name: kAudioServiceLaunchOnStartup
Documentation: Launches the audio service on the browser startup.

Name: kInputPredictorTypeChoice
Documentation:
This flag is used to set field parameters to choose predictor we use when
kResamplingInputEvents is disabled. It's used for gathering accuracy metrics
on finch and also for choosing predictor type for predictedEvents API without
enabling resampling. It does not have any effect when the resampling flag is
enabled.

Name: kThrottleForegroundTimers
Documentation: Throttles Javascript timer wake ups on foreground pages.

Name: kAutofillOverridePredictions
Documentation:
Allows passing a set of overrides for Autofill server predictions.
Example command line to override server predictions manually:
chrome --enable-features=AutofillOverridePredictions:spec/1_2_4-7_8_9
This creates two manual overrides that supersede server predictions as
follows:
* The server prediction for the field with signature 2 in the form with
  signature 1 is overridden to be 4 (NAME_MIDDLE).
* The server prediction for the field with signature 8 in the form with
  signature 7 is overridden to be 9 (EMAIL_ADDRESS).

See components/autofill/core/browser/server_prediction_overrides.h for more
examples and details on how to specify overrides.

Name: kSSVTrailerWriteNewVersion
Documentation:
These control a major serialization change to include information about
exposed interfaces in trailer data, to allow emergency fixes.
Regardless, data which might have been serialized to disk must continue to be
deserializable. These should be removed after a couple milestones.

See https://crbug.com/1341844.

`kSSVTrailerWriteNewVersion`
  If disabled, Blink will revert to writing a pre-trailer format.
  This will become impractical once any other incompatible wire format
  changes are made.
`kSSVTrailerWriteExposureAssertion`
  If enabled, Blink will include assertions about which interfaces are
  exposed in trailers to serialized messages. Has no effect if
  kSSVTrailerWriteNewVersion is disabled.
`kSSVTrailerEnforceExposureAssertion`
  If enabled, Blink will reject messages which cannot be deserialized in the
  current realm. Otherwise, all interfaces will be treated as exposed in all
  contexts for the purposes of serialization.

Name: kEnableNetworkServiceResourceBlockListInOtrSessions
Documentation:
When enabled, resource requests will be evaluated against the Network
Service's block list for NetworkContexts that are associated with an Off the
Record session. The block list is populated by the MaskedDomainList, so
"MaskedDomainList" will need to also be enabled for the block list to have
any contents.

Name: kTrackCurrentShaders
Documentation:
Track current program's shaders at glUseProgram() call for crash report
purpose. Only effective on Windows because the attached shaders may only
be reliably retrieved with ANGLE backend.

Name: kRedInterstitialFacelift
Documentation: Controls whether we are using red interstitial facelift updates.

Name: kNtpModulesDragAndDrop

Name: kOnDeviceClusteringBlocklists
Documentation: Specifies various blocklists for on-device clustering backend.

Documentation:
Controls if Chrome supports filling and importing administrative area

Name: kNotReachedIsFatal
Documentation:

NOTREACHED()s with NOTREACHED_NORETURN() as part of NOTREACHED() migration.

Name: kPartitionConnectionsByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Partitions connections based on the NetworkAnonymizationKey associated with a
request.

Name: kDXGIWaitableSwapChain
Documentation: Use waitable swap chain on Windows to reduce display latency.

Name: kDelayLowPriorityRequestsAccordingToNetworkState
Documentation:
If enabled, the ResourceLoadScheculer will take the current network state
into consideration, when it plans to delay a low-priority throttleable
requests in the tight mode. The factors include:

Name: kRecordMediaEngagementScores
Documentation:
Enables Media Engagement Index recording. This data will be used to determine
when to bypass autoplay policies. This is recorded on all platforms.

Name: kEnableCanvas2DLayers
Documentation: Enables canvas 2d methods BeginLayer and EndLayer.

Name: kStaticKeyPinningEnforcement
Documentation: Controls whether static key pinning is enforced.

Name: kSharedImageManager
Documentation:
Causes us to use the SharedImageManager, removing support for the old
mailbox system. Any consumers of the GPU process using the old mailbox
system will experience undefined results.

Name: kFileSystemAccessMoveLocalFiles
Documentation:

the OPFS).

Name: kEnumerateDevicesHideDeviceIDs
Documentation:
If this feature is enabled and device permission is not granted by the user,
media-device enumeration will provide at most one device per type and the
device IDs will not be available.

Name: kWebRtcAllowWgcWindowCapturer

Name: kPermissionStorageAccessAPI

omnibox integration.

Name: kSplitCodeCacheByNetworkIsolationKey

is available. Note that this feature is also gated behind
`net::HttpCache::IsSplitCacheEnabled()`.

When kPriorityRequestsDelayableOnSlowConnections is enabled, HTTP

servers are not subject to kMaxNumDelayableRequestsPerHostPerClient limit.

flush to actually reclaim resources.

Whether to display a "Managed by your parent" or similar text for supervised
users in various UI surfaces.

Enables retrying to obtain list of available cameras after restarting the
video capture service if a previous attempt failed, which could be caused
