Name: kPrewarmLookalikeCheck
Documentation:
A feature to enable Prewarming the Lookalike check during navigation. URLs in
the redirect chain are queried while the request is on the wire instead of
when the request is ready to commit.

Name: kTaskPerMessage
Documentation:
Enables a task to be scheduled for each individual message dispatched to a
Mojo binding endpoint (or reply to an InterfacePtr).

When disabled, dispatch happens eagerly in batch, so when a binding is
scheduled to dispatch messages, it fully flushes and dispatches all queued
messages within the extent of a single scheduler task.

Enabling this feature allows for more fine-grained performance control
through the scheduler, but may initially cause some important edge cases to
regress in performance due to high-priority messages seeing increased
latency. Ideally we'd address these cases by giving the affected bindings
higher-priority TaskRunners.

Name: kUseTaskRunnerForMojoVEAService
Documentation:
Use TaskRunner for each MojoVideoEncodeAcceleratorService. Replaces
per-accelerator encoding task runner.

Name: kMergeSubtypes
Documentation:
If enabled, merges the suggestion subtypes for the remote suggestions and the
local verbatim and history suggestion duplicates at the provider level. This
is needed for omnibox::kCategoricalSuggestions to function correctly but is
being controlled by a separate feature in case there are unintended side
effects beyond the categorical suggestions.

Name: kBackForwardCacheEmitZeroSamplesForKeyMetrics
Documentation:
Enables to emit zero values for some key metrics when back-forward cache is
used.

With this flag disabled, no samples are emitted for regular VOLT metrics
after the page is restored from the back-forward cache. This means that we
will miss a lot of metrics for history navigations after we launch back-
forward cache. As metrics for history navigations tend to be better figures
than other navigations (e.g., due to network cache), the average of such
metrics values will become worse and might seem regression if we don't take
any actions.

To mitigate this issue, we plan to emit 0 samples for such key metrics for
back-forward navigations. This is implemented behind this flag so far, and we
will enable this by default when we reach the conclusion how to adjust them.

For cumulative layout shift scores, we use actual score values for back-
forward cache navigations instead of 0s.

accommodate the autocompletions.

Whether to enable new touch text editing features such as extra touch

for filling.

blink. Currently enabled by default on Windows only.

Documentation: Enables FLEDGE and Attribution Reporting API integration.

Name: kAudioServiceOutOfProcess
Documentation: Runs the audio service in a separate process.

Name: kSoundContentSetting
Documentation:
Enables or disables the ability to use the sound content setting to mute a
website.

Name: kAutofillFallbackForAutocompleteUnrecognized
Documentation:
When enabled, an entry is added to the context menu of ac=unrecognized fields
which allows triggering Autofill suggestions. Selecting such a suggestion
fills all address fields in the field's section, independently of the
autocomplete attribute.
TODO(crbug.com/1446318): Remove when launched.

Name: kWebXr
Documentation: Controls whether the WebXR Device API is enabled.

Name: kPrefetchRedirects
Documentation: IF enabled, then redirects will be followed when prefetching.

Name: kDownloadServiceForegroundSessionIOSFeature
Documentation:
Enable download service to download in foreground.
TODO(crbug/1232027): This is for iOS only and temporary fix to circumvent
issues with background downloads reported as crashes.

Name: kSyncSegmentationDataType
Documentation: If enabled, Segmentation data type will be synced.

Name: kHideIncognitoMediaMetadata
Documentation:
Hides the media metadata from the OS' media player if running in an Incognito
session.

Name: kUseWindowBoundsForPip
Documentation:
Safety switch to allow us to revert to the previous behavior of using the
restored bounds for PiP windows, rather than the window bounds.  If this
feature is enabled (the default), then we'll use the window bounds.

Name: kExtensionTelemetryFileData
Documentation:
Allows the Extension Telemetry Service to process installed extension files
and attach file data to reports.

Name: kWebSQLNonSecureContextAccess
Documentation: If enabled, allows the use of WebSQL in non-secure contexts.

Name: kEagerCacheStorageSetupForServiceWorkers
Documentation:
Enable eagerly setting up a CacheStorage interface pointer and
passing it to service workers on startup as an optimization.

Name: kDemographicMetricsReporting
Documentation: Feature switch to report user's noised birth year and gender.

Name: kV8CompactCodeSpaceWithStack
Documentation: Enable code space compaction when finalizing a full GC with stack.

Name: kOmniboxRemoveSuggestionsFromClipboard
Documentation: Feature used to allow users to remove suggestions from clipboard.

Name: kQuietNotificationPrompts
Documentation: Enables using quiet prompts for notification permission requests.

Name: kTailoredSecurityObserverRetries
Documentation:
Enable an observer-based retry mechanism for the tailored security dialogs.
When enabled, the tailored security integration will use tab observers to
retry the tailored security logic when a WebContents becomes available.

Name: kPasswordIssuesInSpecificsMetadata
Documentation:
Killswitch for changes regarding password issues in
`PasswordSpcificsMetadata`. Guards writing issues to metadata and preserving
the new notification field.

Name: kReduceGpuPriorityOnBackground
Documentation:
Reduce the priority of GPU process when in background so it is more likely
to be killed first if the OS needs more memory.

Name: kUseClientConfigIPH
Documentation:
A feature for enabling In-Product Help (IPH) to use client side
configuration. When this flag is enabled, finch config will be ignored for
all IPHs.

Name: kEarlyExitOnNoopClassOrStyleChange
Documentation:
Early exit when the style or class attribute of an element is set to the same
value as before.

Name: kPersistedClusters
Documentation: Enables persisting and using persisted clusters.

Name: kProcessPerSiteUpToMainFrameThreshold
Documentation:
Reuses RenderProcessHost up to a certain threshold. This mode ignores the
soft process limit and behaves just like a process-per-site policy for all
sites, with an additional restriction that a process may only be reused while
the number of main frames in that process stays below a threshold.

Name: kInstallPromptGlobalGuardrails
Documentation: Enables or disables the installable ambient badge message.

Name: kWebAuthnICloudKeychainForActiveWithoutDrive
Documentation: Not yet enabled by default.

Name: kPrivateNetworkAccessPreflightShortTimeout
Documentation:
Reduce PNA preflight response waiting time to 200ms.
See: https://wicg.github.io/private-network-access/#cors-preflight

Name: kInstallPromptSegmentation
Documentation: Use segmentation to decide whether install prompt should be shown.

Name: kRemoveCanceledTasksInTaskQueue
Documentation: Controls whether or not canceled delayed tasks are removed from task queues.

Name: kAutofillPopupDisablePaintChecks
Documentation:
If the feature is enabled, paint checks over individual `PopupCellView`s (to
verify that a user's cursor has been outside the cell before accepting it)
are disabled.

Name: kUseSequencedTaskRunnerForMediaService
Documentation: Use SequencedTaskRunner for MediaService.

Name: kShortLaxAllowUnsafeThreshold
Documentation:
When enabled, the time threshold for Lax-allow-unsafe cookies will be lowered
from 2 minutes to 10 seconds. This time threshold refers to the age cutoff
for which cookies that default into SameSite=Lax, which are newer than the
threshold, will be sent with any top-level cross-site navigation regardless
of HTTP method (i.e. allowing unsafe methods). This is a convenience for
integration tests which may want to test behavior of cookies older than the
threshold, but which would not be practical to run for 2 minutes.

Name: kAllowJITInstallationWhenAppIconIsMissing
Documentation: Used to test icon refetch for JIT installed apps with missing icons.

Name: kNetworkQualityEstimator
Documentation:
Enables optimizing the network quality estimation algorithms in network
quality estimator (NQE).

Name: kDefaultAllowPrivacySandboxAttestations
Documentation:
Enable the Privacy Sandbox Attestations to default allow when the
attestations map is absent.

Name: kNtpHandleMostVisitedNavigationExplicitly
Documentation:
If enabled, handles navigations from the Most Visited tiles explicitly and
overrides the navigation's transition type to bookmark navigation before the
navigation is issued.
TODO(crbug.com/1147589): When removing this flag, also remove the workaround
in ChromeContentBrowserClient::OverrideNavigationParams.

Name: kUnifiedPasswordManagerSyncUsingAndroidBackendOnly
Documentation:
If enabled, the built-in sync functionality in PasswordSyncBridge becomes
unused, meaning that SyncService/SyncEngine will no longer download or
upload changes to/from the Sync server. Instead, an external Android-specific
backend will be used to achieve similar behavior.

Name: kTranslateCompactUI
Documentation: Feature flag for "Translate Compact Infobar UI" project.

Name: kWebRtcAllowDxgiGdiZeroHz
Documentation:
When enabled we will tell WebRTC that we want to use the 0Hz mode of the
DirectX and GDI based DesktopCapturers in combination with sharing the screen
or a separate window. In this mode, only frames with new content will be sent
to the client leading to to 0fps for a static source. A special flag called
kWebRtcAllowWgcZeroHz is used to specify the support when using the WGC
capture API.
This flag has no effect if kWebRtcAllowWgcDesktopCapturer is enabled. Use
kWebRtcAllowWgcZeroHz for WGC.

Name: kInfoCardAcknowledgementTracking
Documentation: Feature that enables tracking the acknowledgement state for the info cards.

Name: kEnableADPFRendererMain
Documentation:
If enabled, Chrome includes the Renderer Main thread(s) into the
ADPF(Android Dynamic Performance Framework) hint session.
see https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/e7507d15614ac7f499fb89086b3a09772fa8deb4

Name: kClientHintsFormFactor
Documentation: Enable `form-factor` client hint.

Name: kLacrosColorManagement
Documentation: Enables chrome color management wayland protocol for lacros.

Name: kUseBuiltInRecoveryIfSupported
Documentation:
When enabled, `sql::BuiltInRecovery` can be used if it's supported. See
https://crbug.com/1385500.

This is an overarching kill switch which overrides any database-specific
flag. See `sql::BuiltInRecovery::RecoverIfPossible()` for more context.

Name: kUseBlinkSchedulerTaskRunnerWithCustomDeleter
Documentation:
Kill switch for using a custom task runner in the blink scheduler that makes
DeleteSoon/ReleaseSoon less prone to memory leaks.

Name: kPartitionSSLSessionsByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Partitions TLS sessions and QUIC server configs based on the
NetworkAnonymizationKey associated with a request.

This feature requires kPartitionConnectionsByNetworkIsolationKey to be
enabled to work.

Name: kActionsInSuggest
Documentation:
Actions in Suggest - Action Chips for Entity Suggestions.
Data driven feature; flag helps tune behavior.

Name: kWebMidi
Documentation:
Enable the browser process components of the Web MIDI API. This flag does not
control whether the API is exposed in Blink.

Name: kAutofillAddressProfileSavePromptAddressVerificationSupport
Documentation:
When enabled, address data will be verified and autocorrected in the
save/update prompt before saving an address profile. Relevant only if the
AutofillAddressProfileSavePrompt feature is enabled.

Name: kCastStreamingAv1
Documentation:
NOTE: callers should always use the free functions in
/media/cast/encoding/encoding_support.h instead of accessing these features
directly.
TODO(https://crbug.com/1453388): Guard Cast Sender flags with !IS_ANDROID.

Name: kContentCaptureInWebLayer
Documentation:
ContentCapture in WebLayer, this flag is independent from the kContentCapture
flag.

Name: kChromeRefresh2023
Documentation:
Exposed for testing and flags integration. For actual checks please use
IsChromeRefresh2023().

Name: kV8Maglev
Documentation:
Enables Maglev compiler. Note that this only sets the V8 flag when
manually overridden; otherwise it defers to whatever the V8 default is.

Name: kBiddingAndScoringDebugReportingAPI
Documentation: Debug reporting runtime flag/JS API.

Name: kAutofillEnableOffersInClankKeyboardAccessory
Documentation:
When enabled, offers will be displayed in the Clank keyboard accessory during
downstream.

Name: kBackForwardCacheNoTimeEviction
Documentation:
Removes the time limit for cached content. This is used on bots to identify
accidentally passing tests.

Name: kEyeDropper
Documentation: Used to enable the eye-dropper in the refresh color-picker.

Name: kEnableAccessibilityExposeHTMLElement
Documentation:
Enable exposing the <html> element to the browser process AXTree
(as an ignored node).

Name: kMediaDrmPreprovisioning
Documentation:
Enables MediaDrmOriginIdManager to provide preprovisioned origin IDs for
MediaDrmBridge. If disabled, MediaDrmBridge will get unprovisioned origin IDs
which will trigger provisioning process after MediaDrmBridge is created.

Name: kSystemKeyboardLock
Documentation: Allows system keyboard event capture via the keyboard lock API.

Name: kAndroidExtendedKeyboardShortcuts
Documentation: Extended physical keyboard shortcuts for Android.

Name: kMojoDedicatedThread
Documentation:
If enabled Mojo uses a dedicated background thread to listen for incoming
IPCs. Otherwise it's configured to use Content's IO thread for that purpose.

Name: kThreadedPreloadScanner
Documentation: If enabled, the HTMLPreloadScanner will run on a worker thread.

Name: kRestrictRendererPoliciesInBaseline
Documentation:
When enabled, this features restricts a set of syscalls in
BaselinePolicyAndroid that are used by RendererProcessPolicy.

Name: kContextualPageActionShareModel
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling reader mode action feature.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidStackingAnimation
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether Messages for Android should use
new Stacking Animation.

Name: kRealboxWidthBehavior
Documentation:
Determines the behavior of the width of the realbox in relation to the width
for secondary column.

Name: kUsePageViewportInLCP
Documentation:
Uses page viewport instead of frame viewport in the Largest Contentful Paint
heuristic where images occupying the full viewport are ignored.

Name: kDismissPromos
Documentation:
If enabled, "middle slot" promos on the bottom of the NTP will show a dismiss
UI that allows users to close them and not see them again.

Name: kUseExtensionListForPSLMatching
Documentation:
Improves PSL matching capabilities by utilizing PSL-extension list from
affiliation service. It fixes problem with incorrect password suggestions on
websites like slack.com.

Name: kV8TurboshaftInstructionSelection
Documentation: Enable running instruction selection on Turboshaft IR directly.

Name: kIPv6Probing
Documentation: Enable IPv6 ping probes to RIPE DNS.

Name: kLazyInitializeMediaControls
Documentation: Enable lazy initialization of the media controls.

Name: kEnableSchemeBoundCookies
Documentation:
Enables binding of cookies to the scheme that originally set them. Also
enables domain cookie shadowing protection.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidPopupBlocked
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether "popup blocked" prompts use Messages or
Infobars infrastructure.

Name: kPopularSitesBakedInContentFeature
Documentation:
This feature is enabled by default. Otherwise, users who need it would not
get the right configuration timely enough. The configuration affects only
Android or iOS users.

Name: kNtpDriveModuleSegmentation
Documentation:
If enabled, segmentation data will be collected to decide whether or not to
show the Drive module.

Name: kReduceAcceptLanguage
Documentation:
Enables support for the `Variants` response header and reduce
accept-language. https://github.com/Tanych/accept-language

Name: kFledgeUseInterestGroupCache
Documentation: Enables caching when loading interest groups for a bidder in an auction.

Name: kShowDiscountOnNavigation
Documentation: Discount on navigation

Name: kNtpChromeCartHistoryClusterCoexist
Documentation:
If enabled, ChromeCart module will show together with ChromeCart+History
cluster module when available.

Name: kIncognitoFileSystemContextForTesting
Documentation:
Creates FileSystemContexts in incognito mode. This is used to run web tests
in incognito mode to ensure feature parity for FileSystemAccessAccessHandles.

Name: kAllowPageWithIDBConnectionInBFCache
Documentation:
Feature for allowing page with open IDB connection to be
stored in back/forward cache.

Name: kRTCGpuCodecSupportWaiter
Documentation:
Enables waiting for codec support status notification from GPU factory in RTC
codec factories.

Name: kWebOtpBackendAuto
Documentation:
Controls which backend is used to retrieve OTP on Android. When disabled
we use User Consent API.

Name: kNoAESHardwareMessage
Documentation: Show a warning message to user if aes hardware is not found

Name: kAudioFocusLossSuspendMediaSession
Documentation:
Only affects Android. Suspends a media session when audio focus is lost; when
this setting is disabled, an Android media session will not be suspended when
Audio focus is lost. This is used by Cast which sometimes needs to drive
multiple media sessions.

Name: kIncognitoScreenshot
Documentation: Only affects devices on API version < 33.

Name: kUsePopularSitesSuggestions
Documentation: If this feature is enabled, we enable popular sites in the suggestions UI.

Name: kDocumentProvider
Documentation: Document provider and domain suggestions

Name: kLiveCaptionSystemWideOnChromeOS
Documentation: Live Caption runs system-wide on ChromeOS, as opposed to just in the browser.

Name: kTimerSlackMac
Documentation:
Under this feature, slack is added on mac message pumps that support it when
allowed per DelayPolicy.

Name: kSeedAccountsRevamp
Documentation: Feature to refactor how and when accounts are seeded on Android.

Name: kChromeCartDomBasedHeuristics
Documentation: Feature flag for DOM-based heuristics for ChromeCart.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformIosModuleRanker
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling ios module ranker.

Name: kSlidingWindowForDroppedFrameCounter
Documentation:
When enabled, DroppedFrameCounter will use an adjusted sliding window
interval specified by field trial params.

Name: kCapReferrerToOriginOnCrossOrigin
Documentation:
When kCapReferrerToOriginOnCrossOrigin is enabled, HTTP referrers on cross-
origin requests are restricted to contain at most the source origin.

Name: kFeedUserInteractionReliabilityReport
Documentation: Feature that enables reporting feed user interaction reliability.

Name: kForceDisableExtendedSyncPromos
Documentation: This feature disables all extended sync promos.

Name: kCompressReportingPipeline
Documentation:
Feature to enable/disable compression.
By default compression is disabled, until server can support compression.

Name: kReducedReferrerGranularity
Documentation:
Reduce the amount of information in the default 'referer' header for
cross-origin requests.

Name: kNoWorkerThreadReclaim
Documentation:
Under this feature, worker threads are not reclaimed after a timeout. Rather,
only excess workers are cleaned up immediately after finishing a task.

Name: kSameSiteDefaultChecksMethodRigorously
Documentation:
When enabled, the SameSite by default feature does not add the
"Lax-allow-unsafe" behavior. Any cookies that do not specify a SameSite
attribute will be treated as Lax only, i.e. POST and other unsafe HTTP
methods will not be allowed at all for top-level cross-site navigations.
This only has an effect if the cookie defaults to SameSite=Lax.

Name: kLensSearchOptimizations
Documentation:
Enables a variety of changes aimed to improve user's engagement with current
Lens features.

Name: kReportAssistedQueryStats
Documentation: Omnibox Logging.

Name: kOnDeviceClustering
Documentation: Enables configuring the on-device clustering backend.

Name: kV8SparkplugNeedsShortBuiltinCalls
Documentation:
Makes sure the experimental Sparkplug compiler is only enabled if short
builtin calls are enabled too.

Name: kServiceWorkerStaticRouter
Documentation:
Enables ServiceWorker static routing API.
https://github.com/yoshisatoyanagisawa/service-worker-static-routing-api

Name: kOmitCorsClientCert
Documentation:
Do not send TLS client certificates in CORS preflight. Omit all client certs
and continue the handshake without sending one if requested.

Name: kDeepScanningEncryptedArchives
Documentation:
Controls whether we prompt encrypted archive deep scans to provide a
password.

Name: kAutofillEnableLabelPrecedenceForTurkishAddresses
Documentation:
When enabled, the precedence is given to the field label over the name when
they match different types. Applied only for parsing of address forms in
Turkish.
TODO(crbug.com/1156315): Remove once launched.

Name: kOriginTrialStateHostApplyFeatureDiff
Documentation:
Kill-switch for any calls to the mojo interface OriginTrialStateHost
in the RuntimeFeatureStateOverrideContext class. If
`kOriginTrialStateHostApplyFeatureDiff` is disabled,
origin/deprecation trial token information is not sent to the browser
process.

Name: kSetLowPriorityForBeacon
Documentation:
When enabled, beacons (and friends) have ResourceLoadPriority::kLow,
not ResourceLoadPriority::kVeryLow.

Name: kKalmanDirectionCutOff
Documentation:
Enables discarding the prediction if the predicted direction is opposite from
the current direction.

Name: kThirdPartyStoragePartitioning
Documentation:
Enables partitioning of third party storage (IndexedDB, CacheStorage, etc.)
by the top level site to reduce fingerprinting.

Name: kAutofillFeedback
Documentation: Enables support to submit feedback on Autofill. Used only in Desktop.

Name: kHeavyAdPrivacyMitigations
Documentation:
Enables or disables the privacy mitigations for the heavy ad intervention.
This throttles the amount of interventions that can occur on a given host in
a time period. It also adds noise to the thresholds used. This is separate
from the intervention feature so it does not interfere with field trial
activation, as this blocklist is created for every user, and noise is decided
prior to seeing a heavy ad.

Name: kAutofillUseImprovedLabelDisambiguation
Documentation:
Controls whether suggestions' labels use the improved label disambiguation
format.

Name: kAcceptCHFrame
Documentation:
Enable support for ACCEPT_CH H2/3 frame as part of Client Hint Reliability.
See:
https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-davidben-http-client-hint-reliability-02#section-4.3

Name: kStylusWritingToInput
Documentation: Stylus handwriting recognition to text input feature.

Name: kJourneysLabels
Documentation: Enables labelling of Journeys in UI.

Name: kReduceSubresourceResponseStartedIPC
Documentation:
When enabled, sends SubresourceResponseStarted IPC only when the user has
allowed any HTTPS-related warning exceptions. From field data, (see
`SSL.Experimental.SubresourceResponse`), ~100% of subresource notifications
are not required, since allowing certificate exceptions by users is a rare
event. Hence, if user has never allowed any certificate or HTTP exceptions,
notifications are not sent to the browser. Once we start sending these
messages, we keep sending them until all exceptions are revoked and browser
restart occurs.

Name: kShowRelatedWebsiteSetsPermissionGrants
Documentation:
When enabled, blocks condition to exclude auto granted permissions for
storage access exceptions. This will allow RWS permission grants to be
visible in the Embedded content settings page.

Name: kPrivateAggregationApiBundledEnhancements
Documentation:
Enables a set of bundled Private Aggregation API enhancements. Specifically:
- Controls whether third-party cookie eligibility should be queried before
  allowing debug mode to be used by a context. If enabled, any
  `enableDebugMode()` calls in a context that does not have third-party
  cookie eligibility will essentially have no effect. This feature has no
  effect on debug mode if
  `blink::features::kPrivateAggregationApiDebugModeEnabledAtAll` is disabled.
- Whether to send a null report if a context ID is specified.
- Whether to reduce the delay for reports if a context ID is specified.

Name: kHighPriorityBeforeUnload
Documentation:
Tells the RenderFrameHost to send beforeunload messages on a different
local frame interface which will handle the messages at a higher priority.

Name: kHardwareSecureDecryption
Documentation:
Enables hardware secure decryption if supported by hardware and CDM.
TODO(xhwang): Currently this is only used for development of new features.
Apply this to Android and ChromeOS as well where hardware secure decryption
is already available.

Name: kSmallerInterestArea
Documentation: Feature to reduce the area in which invisible tiles are kept around.

Name: kNetworkServiceSandbox
Documentation:
Enables network service sandbox.
(Only causes an effect when feature kNetworkServiceInProcess is disabled.)

Name: kTabHoverCardImages
Documentation:
Enables preview images in tab-hover cards.
https://crbug.com/928954

Name: kSafetyCheckUnusedSitePermissions
Documentation: Feature to enable the unused site permissions module of Safety Check.

Name: kRenameJourneys
Documentation: Enables renaming Journeys in the UI.

Name: kAccessibilityPerformanceFiltering
Documentation:
Enable filtered AXModes based on running services. If disabled, then AXModes
will not be available to be set.

Name: kCheckHTMLParserBudgetLessOften
Documentation:
If enabled, the HTMLDocumentParser will only check its budget after parsing a
commonly slow token or for one out of 10 fast tokens. Note that this feature
is a no-op if kTimedHTMLParserBudget is disabled.

Name: kOptimizationHints
Documentation:
Enables the syncing of the Optimization Hints component, which provides
hints for what optimizations can be applied on a page load.

Name: kNtpFeedModule
Documentation: If enabled, Following Feed module will be shown.

Name: kMediaCodecCodedSizeGuessing
Documentation: Allow FrameInfoHelper to guess coded size information for MediaCodec frames.

Name: kConversionMeasurementAPIAlternativeUsage
Documentation:
Field trial feature for controlling usage restriction of the
Conversion Measurement API's origin trial tokens. When disabled, the API
cannot be enabled by tokens using the user subset usage restriction.

Name: kFencedFramesAutomaticBeaconCredentials
Documentation:
Temporarily un-disable credentials on fenced frame automatic beacons until
third party cookie deprecation.
TODO(crbug.com/1496395): Remove this after 3PCD.

Name: kLiveCaptionLogFlickerRate
Documentation:
Log the amount of flickering between partial results. This measures how often
the system revises earlier outputs, to quantify the system's output
instability or flicker. Intuitively, it measures how many tokens must be
truncated from the previous text before appending any new text. The erasure
of the current timestep can be calculated from its longest common prefix with
the previous timestep.

Name: kDrawImmediatelyWhenInteractive
Documentation: If enabled, surface activation and draw do not block on dependencies.

Name: kNtpChromeCartModule
Documentation: If enabled, chrome cart module will be shown.

Name: kWebFeedOnboarding
Documentation: Feature that provides the user assistance in using the web feed.

Name: kReportVisibleLineBounds
Documentation:
Report rectangles around lines of text in the currently focused editable
element.

Name: kTrackingProtection3pcd
Documentation: Feature to enable redesigned tracking protection UX + prefs for 3PCD.

Name: kServiceWorkerRegistrationCache
Documentation:
Enable registration cache to skip calling FindRegistrationForClientUrl while
there is a live registration. (https://crbug.com/1446216)

Name: kSearchEngineChoice
Documentation: Enables the search engine choice feature for existing users.

Name: kUseInProgressDownloadManagerForDownloadService
Documentation:
Whether in-progress download manager will be used to initialize download
service.

Name: kClientHintsResourceWidth
Documentation: Enable `sec-ch-width` client hint.

Name: kSkipInvalidationOptimizationsWhenDeviceInfoUpdated
Documentation:
When enabled, optimization flags (single client and a list of FCM
registration tokens) will be disabled if during the current sync cycle
DeviceInfo has been updated.

Name: kOptimizationGuideInstallWideModelStore
Documentation:
Enables the new model store that is tied with Chrome installation and shares
the models across user profiles.

Name: kPushNotifications
Documentation: Enables push notification of hints.

Name: kHlsPlayer
Documentation:
Enables the use of MediaPlayerRenderer for HLS playback. When disabled,
HLS manifests will fail to load (triggering source fallback or load error).

Name: kCoopRestrictPropertiesOriginTrial
Documentation:
Enables the origin trial for COOP: restrict-properties. We need a new feature
because token validation is not possible in the network process. This also
allows us to keep using CoopRestrictProperties to enable COOP: RP for WPTs.

Name: kUserActivationSameOriginVisibility
Documentation:
Allows user activation propagation to all frames having the same origin as
the activation notifier frame.  This is an intermediate measure before we
have an iframe attribute to declaratively allow user activation propagation
to subframes.

Name: kStructuredMetrics
Documentation: This can be used to disable structured metrics as a whole.

Name: kSharedStorageAPIM118
Documentation:
Additional Shared Storage API features shipped in M118.
TODO(crbug.com/1218540): Merge this flag with `kSharedStorageAPI` once
shipped.

Name: kDisableArrayBufferSizeLimitsForTesting
Documentation:
TODO(https://crbug.com/1201109): temporary flag to disable new ArrayBuffer
size limits, so that tests can be written against code receiving these
buffers. Remove when the bindings code instituting these limits is removed.

Name: kRealboxSecondaryZeroSuggest
Documentation:
If enabled, allows up to
`OmniboxFieldTrial::kRealboxMaxPreviousSearchRelatedSuggestions` zero-prefix
suggestions in the 2nd column of realbox.

Name: kExposeSwDecodersToWebRTC
Documentation:
If enabled, when RTCVideoDecoderAdapter is used then SW decoders will be
exposed directly to WebRTC.

Name: kNetworkTimeServiceQuerying
Documentation: Feature that enables network time service querying.

Name: kServiceWorkerPaymentApps
Documentation:
Service worker based payment apps as defined by w3c here:
https://w3c.github.io/webpayments-payment-apps-api/
TODO(rouslan): Remove this.

Name: kAutofillUseParameterizedSectioning
Documentation:
Controls whether to use the newest, parameterized sectioning algorithm.
TODO(crbug.com/1153539): Remove the feature when the experiment is completed.

Name: kPushSubscriptionWithExpirationTime
Documentation:
Feature flag to enable push subscription with expiration times specified in
/chrome/browser/push_messaging/push_messaging_constants.h

Name: kPartialLowEndModeOn3GbDevices
Documentation:
Force to enable LowEndDeviceMode partially on Android 3Gb devices.
(see PartialLowEndModeOnMidRangeDevices below)

Name: kNtpPhotosModuleCustomizedOptInArtWork
Documentation: If enabled, a customized art work will be shown on the opt-in card.

Name: kTabToGTSAnimation
Documentation:
Enabled, but often disabled in tests to reduce animation flakes and test
low-end device behavior where this animation is disabled.

Name: kUseEngagementScoreCache
Documentation: Uses an in-memory cache that stores engagement score.

Name: kOriginKeyedProcessesByDefault
Documentation:
Enables origin-keyed processes by default, unless origins opt out using
Origin-Agent-Cluster: ?0. This feature only takes effect if the Blink feature
OriginAgentClusterDefaultEnable is enabled, since origin-keyed processes
require origin-agent-clusters.

Name: kAllBookmarksBaselineFolderVisibility
Documentation:
This feature controls the default visibility for permanent folders when
empty. It effectively swaps in "other bookmarks" as the default-visible
empty folder on mobile. This flag has no effect for desktop.

Name: kPreemptiveLinkToTextGeneration
Documentation: Enables link to text to be generated in advance.

Name: kContextMenuPerformanceInfoAndRemoteHintFetching
Documentation:
Enables performance info in the context menu and fetching from a remote
Optimization Guide Service.

Name: kNtpHistoryClustersModuleMinimumImagesRequired
Documentation: Dummy feature to set kNtpHistoryClustersModuleMinimumImagesRequiredParam.

Name: kAutofillIgnoreUnmappableAutocompleteValues
Documentation:
When enabled, HTML autocomplete values that do not map to any known type, but
look reasonable (e.g. contain "address") are simply ignored. Without the
feature, Autofill is disabled on such fields.

Name: kAImageReader
Documentation: Use AImageReader for MediaCodec and MediaPlyer on android.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformCrossDeviceUser
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling cross device user segment.

Name: kCookieDomainRejectNonASCII
Documentation: When enabled, cookies with a non-ASCII domain attribute will be rejected.

Name: kV8CodeMemoryWriteProtection
Documentation:
Enables W^X code memory protection in V8.
This is enabled in V8 by default. To test the performance impact, we are
going to disable this feature in a finch experiment.

Name: kResamplingInputEvents
Documentation: Enables resampling input events on main thread.

Name: kWinrtGeolocationImplementation
Documentation:
Enables usage of the Windows.Devices.Geolocation WinRT API for the
LocationProvider instead of the NetworkLocationProvider on Windows.

Name: kPervasivePayloadsList
Documentation: Load Pervasive Payloads List for Cache Transparency.

Name: kOmniboxAction
Documentation:
Enables the Journeys Omnibox Action chip. `kJourneys` must also be enabled
for this to take effect.

Name: kNtpModulesLoad
Documentation:
If enabled, modules will be loaded but not shown. This is useful to determine
if a user would have seen modules in order to counterfactually log or
trigger.

Name: kReceiveEcn
Documentation: Enables receiving ECN bit by sockets in Chrome.

Name: kV8SlowHistograms
Documentation:
Enables slow histograms that provide detailed information at increased
runtime overheads.

Name: kUseDnsHttpsSvcb
Documentation:
Enables querying HTTPS DNS records that will affect results from HostResolver
and may be used to affect connection behavior. Whether or not those results
are used (e.g. to connect via ECH) may be controlled by separate features.

Name: kTabGroupsSaveNudgeDelay
Documentation: Wrapper flag to control the nudge delay of the #tab-groups-save feature.

Name: kMdnsResponderGeneratedNameListing
Documentation:
If this feature is enabled, the mDNS responder service responds to queries
for TXT records associated with
"Generated-Names._mdns_name_generator._udp.local" with a list of generated
mDNS names (random UUIDs) in the TXT record data.

Name: kOmitParametersInReadyToPay
Documentation:
If enabled, then the web merchant origin and web wallet parameters will be
omitted from the isReadyToPayRequest. See: https://crbug.com/1406655.

Name: kTangibleSync
Documentation: Enables a new version of the sync confirmation UI.

Name: kRestrictCanAccessDataForOriginToUIThread
Documentation:
When enabled, CanAccessDataForOrigin can only be called from the UI thread.
This is related to Citadel desktop protections. See
https://crbug.com/1286501.

Name: kForceMajorVersionInMinorPositionInUserAgent
Documentation:
If enabled, the major version number returned by Chrome will be locked at
99. The minor version number returned by Chrome will be forced to the
value of the major version number. The purpose of this
feature is a back up plan for if the major version moving from
two to three digits breaks unexpected things.

Name: kSyncAutofillWalletCredentialData
Documentation: Controls whether to enable syncing of Autofill Wallet Credential Data.

Name: kAutocompleteActionPredictorConfidenceCutoff
Documentation:
This is used to enable an experiment for modifying confidence cutoff of
prerender and preconnect for autocomplete action predictor.

Name: kShareThisTabInsteadButtonGetDisplayMediaAudio
Documentation:
If kShareThisTabInsteadButtonGetDisplayMedia is ENABLED, this flag controls
whether a "Share this tab instead" button should be enabled for
getDisplayMedia captures with audio.
If kShareThisTabInsteadButtonGetDisplayMedia is DISABLED, this flag has no
effect.
Note: This flag does not control if the "Share this tab instead" button is
shown for chrome.desktopCapture captures.

Name: kKAnonymityServiceOHTTPRequests
Documentation:
When enabled, the k-Anonymity Service will send requests to the Join and
Query k-anonymity servers.

Name: kEventTimingReportAllEarlyEntriesOnPaintedPresentation
Documentation:
This feature (EventTimingReportAllEarlyEntriesOnPaintedPresentation) is
having an effect only when EventTimingMatchPresentationIndex is turned on.

Name: kV8ConcurrentSparkplug
Documentation: Enables the concurrent Sparkplug compiler.

Name: kDesktopScreenshots
Documentation:
Feature flag to enable the screenshots feature, currently accessed only
through the sharing hub.

Name: kRunTextInputUpdatePostLifecycle
Documentation:
If enabled, IME updates are computed at the end of a lifecycle update rather
than the beginning.

Name: kVaapiVP9Encoder
Documentation: Enable VA-API hardware encode acceleration for VP9.

Name: kAutofillSilentProfileUpdateForInsufficientImport
Documentation:
Allows silent profile updates even when the profile import requirements are
not met.

Name: kIsolateFencedFrames
Documentation: LINT.ThenChange(//PRESUBMIT.py)

Name: kAutofillDontPreserveAutofillState
Documentation:
FormStructure::RetrieveFromCache used to preserve an AutofillField's
is_autofilled from the cache of previously parsed forms. This makes little
sense because the renderer sends us the autofill state and has the most
recent information. Dropping the old behavior should not make any difference
but to be sure, this is gated by a finch experiment.
TODO(crbug.com/1373362) Cleanup when launched.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidFullyVisibleCallback
Documentation:
Feature that exposes a listener to notify whether the current message
is fully visible.

Name: kEnforcePrivacySandboxAttestations
Documentation: Enables enforcement of Privacy Sandbox Enrollment/Attestations.

Name: kConsolidatedIPCForProxyCreation
Documentation:
When enabled, when creating new proxies for all nodes in a `FrameTree`, one
IPC is sent to create all child frame proxies instead of sending one IPC per
proxy.

Name: kWebFontsCacheAwareTimeoutAdaption
Documentation:
Enables cache-aware WebFonts loading. See https://crbug.com/570205.
The feature is disabled on Android for WebView API issue discussed at
https://crbug.com/942440.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidOfferNotification
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether offer notifications use Messages or Infobars
infrastructure.

Name: kMediaControlsExpandGesture
Documentation:
Enable a gesture to make the media controls expanded into the display cutout.
TODO(beccahughes): Remove this.

Name: kPasswordManagerLogToTerminal
Documentation:
Enables logging the content of chrome://password-manager-internals to the
terminal.

Name: kUiCompositorScrollWithLayers
Documentation: Enables scrolling with layers under ui using the ui::Compositor.

Name: kWebAuthnAndroidIncognitoConfirmation
Documentation: Show an incognito confirmation sheet on Android when creating a credential.

Name: kToolbarUseHardwareBitmapDraw
Documentation:
Determines how screenshots of the toolbar uses Software or Hardware drawing.
Works on Android 10+.

Name: kDisconnectExtensionMessagePortWhenPageEntersBFCache
Documentation:
Enables disconnecting the `ExtensionMessagePort` when the page using the port
enters BFCache.

Name: kDesktopPWAsEnforceWebAppSettingsPolicy
Documentation: Whether to parse and enforce the WebAppSettings policy.

Name: kDelayUnsafeAds
Documentation:
Enables the artificial delaying of ads that are considered unsafe (e.g. http
or same-domain to the top-level).

Name: kReadLaterBackendMigration
Documentation:
Feature flag used for enabling the reading list backend migration.
When enabled, reading list data will also be stored in the Bookmarks backend.
This allows each platform to migrate their reading list front end to point at
the new reading list data stored in the bookmarks backend without
interruption to cross device sync if some syncing devices are on versions
with the migration behavior while others aren't. See crbug/1234426 for more
details.

Name: kNotificationTriggers
Documentation: Enables the notification trigger API.

Name: kUseGles2ForOopR
Documentation: Used to limit GL version to 2.0 for skia raster and compositing.

Name: kFedCmIdpSigninStatusMetrics
Documentation:
Enables metrics collection for signin status mismatches. Also enables
parsing the signin status HTTP headers.
kFedCmIdpSigninStatusEnabled takes precedence over this feature flag.

Name: kCORSErrorsIssueOnly
Documentation:
Suppresses console errors for CORS problems which report an associated
inspector issue anyway.

Name: kBluetoothCoredump
Documentation: Enables/disables the bluetooth devcoredump feature

Name: kWebPaymentsSingleAppUiSkip
Documentation:
Used to control whether the Payment Sheet can be skipped for Payment Requests
with a single URL based payment app and no other info requested.

Name: kBlockRepeatedNotificationPermissionPrompts
Documentation:
Once the user declines a notification permission prompt in a WebContents,
automatically dismiss subsequent prompts in the same WebContents, from any
origin, until the next user-initiated navigation.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformTabletProductivityUser
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling tablet productivity user segment.

Name: kRemotePageMetadata
Documentation: Enables fetching page metadata from the remote Optimization Guide service.

Name: kSuggestionAnswersColorReverse
Documentation:
If enabled, finance ticker answer from omnibox will reverse the color for
stock ticker. only colors being swapped are those that represent "growth" and
"loss" to represent colors red and green in a way that is appropriate for a
given country/culture

Name: kTranslateRecentTarget
Documentation:
Enables or disables using the most recent target language as the default
target language option.

Name: kConsiderPoisonedDatabasesClosed
Documentation: Alphabetical:

Name: kMediaDevicesSystemMonitorCache
Documentation:
If this feature is enabled, media-device enumerations use a cache that is
invalidated upon notifications sent by base::SystemMonitor. If disabled, the
cache is considered invalid on every enumeration request.

Name: kWindowOpenFileSelectFix
Documentation: Flag guard for fix for crbug.com/1414936.

Name: kReportAllAvailablePointerTypes
Documentation:
Reports all of the available pointer types (i.e. coarse, fine) to content
rather than just the first one detected.

Name: kAndroidSurfaceControlMagnifier
Documentation:
Use chromim's implementation of selection magnifier built using surface
control APIs, instead of using the system-provided magnifier.

Name: kSharedStorageSelectURLLimit
Documentation:
If enabled, limits the number of times per origin per pageload that
`sharedStorage.selectURL()` is allowed to be invoked.

Name: kPrivacySandboxProactiveTopicsBlocking
Documentation: Enables Privacy Sandbox Proactive Topics Blocking.

Name: kAutofillDefaultToCityAndNumber
Documentation:
Crowdsourcing already prefers PHONE_HOME_CITY_AND_NUMBER over
PHONE_HOME_WHOLE_NUMBER. With this feature, local heuristics do the same.
TODO(crbug.com/1474308): Clean up when launched.

Name: kAdAuctionReportingWithMacroApi
Documentation: Enable the Protected Audience's reporting with ad macro API.

Name: kNtpOneGoogleBar
Documentation: If enabled, OneGoogleBar will be shown.

Name: kSyntheticPointerActions
Documentation:
Dispatch touch events to "SyntheticGestureController" for events from
Devtool Protocol Input.dispatchTouchEvent to simulate touch events close to
real OS events.

Name: kNvidiaVpTrueHDR
Documentation: Allow overlay swapchain to use NVIDIA video processor for trueHDR.

Name: kDownloadRange
Documentation: Arbitrary range request support for download system.

Name: kMBIMode
Documentation:
The MBI mode controls whether or not communication over the
AgentSchedulingGroup is ordered with respect to the render-process-global
legacy IPC channel, as well as the granularity of AgentSchedulingGroup
creation. This will break ordering guarantees between different agent
scheduling groups (ordering withing a group is still preserved).
DO NOT USE! The feature is not yet fully implemented. See crbug.com/1111231.

Name: kPageTextExtraction
Documentation:
This feature flag does not turn off any behavior, it is only used for
experiment parameters.

Name: kFeedLoadingPlaceholder
Documentation:
Feature that shows placeholder cards instead of a loading spinner at first
load.

Name: kPersonalizeFeedUnsignedUsers
Documentation: Personalize feed for unsigned users.

Name: kExtensionTelemetryConfiguration
Documentation:
Allows the Extension Telemetry Service to accept and use configurations
sent by the server.

Name: kNtpMiddleSlotPromo
Documentation: If enabled, middle slot promo will be shown.

Name: kClientSideDetectionModelIsFlatBuffer
Documentation: The client side detection model is a flatbuffer.

Name: kAutofillEnableSupportForBetweenStreets
Documentation:
Controls if Chrome support filling and importing between streets.
TODO(crbug.com/1441904) Remove once launched.

Name: kAutofillModelPredictions
Documentation:
When enabled, all behaviours related to the on-device machine learning
model for field type predictions will be guarded.
TODO(crbug.com/1465926): Remove when launched.

Name: kSuppressClipboardSuggestionAfterFirstUsed
Documentation:
If enabled, clipboard suggestion for distinct clip data will not show after
first use.

Name: kStylusSpecificTapSlop
Documentation:
Uses a stylus-specific tap slop region parameter for gestures.  Stylus taps
tend to slip more than touch taps (presumably because the user doesn't feel
the movement friction with a stylus).  As a result, it is harder to tap with
a stylus. This feature makes the slop region for stylus input bigger than the
touch slop.

Name: kOmniboxTriggerForPrerender2
Documentation:
This flag is used for enabling Omnibox triggered prerendering. See
crbug.com/1166085 for more details of Omnibox triggered prerendering.

Name: kWebAuthnFilterGooglePasskeys
Documentation:
Filter a priori discovered credentials on google.com to those that have a
user id that starts with "GOOGLE_ACCOUNT:".

Name: kRunTasksByBatches
Documentation: Feature to run tasks by batches before pumping out messages.

Name: kEnableFileBackedBlobFactory
Documentation:
If enabled, file backed blobs are registered by using the
FileBackedBlobFactory interface. This interface allows to capture the URL
from which these blobs are accessed. Access from certain URLs may be disabled
for managed users according to Data Leak Prevention policies.

Name: kScriptStreaming
Documentation: Controls script streaming.

Name: kAdsInterventionsEnforced
Documentation: Enables the blocking of ads on sites that have ads violations.

Name: kStoreTitleInContentsAndUrlInDescription
Documentation:
Provider-specific - These features change the behavior of specific providers.
TODO(crbug.com/1202964): Clean up feature flag used in staged roll-out of
various CLs related to the contents/description clean-up work.

Name: kAutofillParseVcnCardOnFileStandaloneCvcFields
Documentation:
When enabled, Autofill will attempt to find standalone CVC fields for VCN
card on file when parsing forms.

Name: kBeforeUnloadBrowserResponseQueue
Documentation:
When enabled, the browser will schedule before unload tasks that continue
navigation network responses in a kHigh priority queue.
TODO(b/281094330): Run experiment on ChromeOS. Experiment was not run on
ChromeOS due to try bot issue.

Name: kEnableRegionSearchKeyboardShortcut
Documentation: Enable keyboard shortcut for the Lens Region Search feature.

Name: kForceDeferScriptIntervention
Documentation:
If enabled, parser-blocking scripts are force-deferred.
https://crbug.com/1339112

Name: kGb18030_2022Enabled
Documentation: Use Gb18030-2022 for encoding/decoding GB18030.

Name: kWebAuthConditionalUIExperimentation
Documentation: Allow sites to opt into experimenting with conditional UI presentations.

Name: kBlockTruncatedCookies
Documentation:
When enabled, cookie-related code will treat cookies containing '\0', '\r',
and '\n' as invalid and reject the cookie.

Name: kAddWarningShownTSToClientSafeBrowsingReport
Documentation: Enables adding warning shown timestamp to client safe browsing report.

Name: kDefaultPassthroughCommandDecoder
Documentation:
All features in alphabetical order. The features should be documented
alongside the definition of their values in the .cc file.

Name: kDelayedWarnings
Documentation: Controls whether the delayed warning experiment is enabled.

Name: kContextualPageActions
Documentation:
Feature flag for enabling contextual page actions. Only effective when at
least one action is enabled.

Name: kUseRendererProcessPolicy
Documentation: Enables the renderer on Android to use a separate seccomp policy.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformUkmEngine
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling UKM based engine.

Name: kRenderBlockingFonts
Documentation:
Makes preloaded fonts render-blocking up to the limits below.
See https://crbug.com/1412861

Name: kCastStreamingExponentialVideoBitrateAlgorithm
Documentation:
Controls whether the new exponential bitrate calculate logic is used, or
the legacy linear algorithm.

Name: kSharingMatchPulseInterval
Documentation: Feature flag for matching device expiration to pulse interval.

Name: kGroupNIKByJoiningOrigin
Documentation:
Group network isolation key(NIK) by storage interest group joining origin to
improve privacy and performance -- IGs of the same joining origin can reuse
sockets, so we don't need to renegotiate those connections.

TODO(crbug.com/1479754): Keep this feature DISABLED until all the cross site
leaks are fixed. Check comments for more information.

Name: kUseParallelRequestsForHTTP2
Documentation: Whether parallel download is used for HTTP2 connections.

Name: kSyntheticCapabilities
Documentation:
When enabled, allows the server to unilaterally alter capabilities sent
by the client, primarily to retroactively work around bugs.

Name: kPageTimelineMonitor
Documentation:
Enable PageTimelineMonitor timer and by extension, PageTimelineState event
collection.

Name: kEnforceFullDelegation
Documentation: Used to reject the apps with partial delegation.

Name: kScrollableTabStrip
Documentation: Enables tabs to scroll in the tabstrip. https://crbug.com/951078

Name: kSyncEnableWalletMetadataInTransportMode
Documentation:
Flags to allow AUTOFILL_WALLET_METADATA and AUTOFILL_WALLET_OFFER,
respectively, to run in transport mode.

Name: kExpandedStateColors
Documentation:
If enabled, Omnibox "expanded state" colors are updated to match CR23
guidelines.

Name: kForceHardwareAudioDecoders
Documentation:
Forces use of hardware (platform) audio decoders in
`media::DecoderSelector`.

Name: kAllowNonSecureOverlays
Documentation:
Should we allow video playback to use an overlay if it's not needed for
security?  Normally, we'd always want to allow this, except as part of the
power testing A/B experiment.  https://crbug.com/1081346 .

Name: kV8ExperimentalRegexpEngine
Documentation: Enables fallback to a breadth-first regexp engine on excessive backtracking.

Name: kCdmHostVerification
Documentation:
CDM host verification is enabled by default. Can be disabled for testing.
Has no effect if ENABLE_CDM_HOST_VERIFICATION buildflag is false.

Name: kZeroSuggestInMemoryCaching
Documentation:
If enabled, zero prefix suggestions will be stored using an in-memory caching
service, instead of using the existing prefs-based cache.

Name: kIntelVpSuperResolution
Documentation: Allow overlay swapchain to use Intel video processor for super resolution.

Name: kNtpModulesFirstRunExperience
Documentation: If enabled, the first run experience for Modular NTP Desktop v1 will show.

Name: kDumpOnAudioServiceHang
Documentation:
If enabled, base::DumpWithoutCrashing is called whenever an audio service
hang is detected.

Name: kVibration
Documentation: Enables vibration; an user gesture will still be required if enabled.

Name: kVaapiAV1Encoder
Documentation: Enable VA-API hardware encode acceleration for AV1.

Name: kRequestDesktopSiteWindowSetting
Documentation: Request Desktop Site based on window width for Android.

Name: kExtensionTelemetryTabsExecuteScriptSignal
Documentation:
Enables collection of telemetry signal whenever an extension invokes the
tabs.executeScript API call.

Name: kEnableWALModeByDefault
Documentation: Enable WAL mode for all SQLite databases.

Name: kPlzDedicatedWorker
Documentation:
Enable browser-initiated dedicated worker script loading
(PlzDedicatedWorker). https://crbug.com/906991

Name: kAutofillEnableImportWhenMultiplePhoneNumbers
Documentation:
Controls whether to save the first number in a form with multiple phone
numbers instead of aborting the import.
TODO(crbug.com/1167484) Remove once launched.

Name: kClearCrossSiteCrossBrowsingContextGroupWindowName
Documentation:
Clear the window.name property for the top-level cross-site navigations that
swap BrowsingContextGroups(BrowsingInstances).

Name: kFailFastQuietChip
Documentation:
Enables a faster permission request finalization if it is displayed as a
quiet chip.

Name: kAutofillEnableSupportForParsingWithSharedLabels
Documentation:
Controls if the heuristic field parsing utilizes shared labels.
TODO(crbug.com/1165780): Remove once shared labels are launched.

Name: kCookieAccessDetailsNotificationDeDuping
Documentation: Enables de-duping of cookie access details sent to observers.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformModelExecutionSampling
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling model execution report sampling.

Name: kUseDMSAAForTiles
Documentation: Use DMSAA instead of MSAA for rastering tiles.

Name: kEnableTLS13EarlyData
Documentation: Enables TLS 1.3 early data.

Name: kNavigationPredictor
Documentation:
Used to control the collection of anchor element metrics (crbug.com/856683).
If kNavigationPredictor is enabled, then metrics of anchor elements
in the first viewport after the page load and the metrics of the clicked
anchor element will be extracted and recorded.

Name: kLogTLSResumption
Documentation: Log TLS resumption.

Name: kAutofillEnableRankingFormulaAddressProfiles
Documentation:
When enabled, autofill will use the new ranking algorithm for address profile
autofill suggestions.

Name: kNormalPriorityImageDecoding
Documentation:
When enabled, SupportsBackgroundThreadPriority is set to kNo for
GpuImageDecodeTaskImpl and SoftwareImageDecodeTaskImpl.
Introduced to fix https://crbug.com/1116624

Name: kSyncAutofillWalletUsageData
Documentation: Controls whether to enable syncing of Autofill Wallet Usage Data.

Name: kOmniboxActionsUISimplification
Documentation: Feature used to enable the simplified actions UI design.

Name: kUnrestrictedSharedArrayBuffer
Documentation:
This feature is for a reverse Origin Trial, enabling SharedArrayBuffer for
sites as they migrate towards requiring cross-origin isolation for these
features.
TODO(bbudge): Remove when the deprecation is complete.
https://developer.chrome.com/origintrials/#/view_trial/303992974847508481
https://crbug.com/1144104

Name: kReportingServiceAlwaysFlush
Documentation:
Determines whether to always flush Local State immediately after an UMA/UKM
log upload. If this is disabled, Local State is only immediately flushed
after an upload if this is a mobile platform and the browser is in the
background.

Name: kDesktopPWAsCacheDuringDefaultInstall
Documentation:
When installing default installed PWAs, we wait for service workers
to cache resources.

Name: kPageInfoStoreInfo
Documentation: Enables the store info row for Page Info.

Name: kWebAuthnAccessibleTimeouts
Documentation:
Update the minimum, maximum, and default timeout values for webauthn requests
to be more generous and meet https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/#enough-time.

Name: kWebUITabStripContextMenuAfterTap
Documentation:
Controls whether the context menu is shown on a touch press or a touch
tap gesture on the WebUI Tab Strip.

Name: kClientHintsResourceWidth_DEPRECATED
Documentation: Enable legacy `width` client hint.

Name: kExperimentalKeywordMode
Documentation:
Please do not add more features to this "big blob" list.
Instead, use the categorized and alphabetized lists below this "big blob".
You can create a new category if none of the existing ones fit.

Name: kShareCrowButton
Documentation:
Feature that enables the Crow feature.
Owned by the CwF team but located here until it makes sense to create a crow
component, since it is being used in the feed component.

Name: kAntiPhishingTelemetry
Documentation: Enables logging new phishing prevention data.

Name: kVizFrameSubmissionForWebView
Documentation:
Submit CompositorFrame from SynchronousLayerTreeFrameSink directly to viz in
WebView.

Name: kAutofillSendUnidentifiedKeyAfterFill
Documentation:
If disabled (default for many years), autofilling triggers KeyDown and
KeyUp events that do not send any key codes. If enabled, these events
contain the "Unidentified" key.

Name: kAggressiveSkiaGpuResourcePurge
Documentation:
Use shorter timeout when performDeferredCleanup, and enable
performDeferredCleanup for Android WebView.

Name: kGetCookiesStringUma
Documentation:
Enables UMA to track received GetCookiesString IPCs. This feature is enabled
by default, it is just here to allow some tests to disable it. These tests
make use of TaskEnvironment::FastForward with very long delays (days) which
interacts poorly with this metric that is recorded every 30s.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformCollectTabRankData
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling data collection for tab ranking.

Name: kPrefetchPrivacyChanges
Documentation:
Prefetch request properties are updated to be privacy-preserving. See
crbug.com/988956.

Name: kEnablePreferencesAccountStorage
Documentation:
Enables a separate account-scoped storage for preferences, for syncing users.
(Note that opposed to other "account storage" features, this one does not
have any effect for signed-in non-syncing users!)

Name: kMouseAndTrackpadDropdownMenu
Documentation:
When enabled, shows a dropdown menu for mouse and trackpad secondary
clicks (i.e. right click) with respect to text selection.

Name: kMediaCapabilitiesQueryGpuFactories
Documentation:
When enabled, MediaCapabilities will check with GPU Video Accelerator
Factories to determine isPowerEfficient = true/false.

Name: kMemoryCacheStrongReferenceFilterImages
Documentation:
Exclude images from the saved strong references for resources.
See https://crbug.com/1409349.

Name: kFedCmSelectiveDisclosure
Documentation:
Enables usage of the FedCM API with the Selective Disclosure API at the same
time.

Name: kVulkanFromANGLE
Documentation: Enable sharing Vulkan device queue with ANGLE's Vulkan backend.

Name: kAugmentExistingImageLabels
Documentation:
Enables Get Image Descriptions to augment existing images labels,
rather than only provide descriptions for completely unlabeled images.

Name: kPath2DPaintCache
Documentation:
Enables the use of the PaintCache for Path2D objects that are rasterized
out of process.  Has no effect when kCanvasOopRasterization is disabled.

Name: kAggressiveFrameCulling
Documentation:
Whether to:
- Perform periodic inactive frame culling.
- Cull *all* frames in case of critical memory pressure, rather than keeping
  one.

Name: kQueryTilesEnableQueryEditing
Documentation:
Feature flag to determine whether the user will have a chance to edit the
query before in the omnibox sumbitting the search. In this mode only one
level of tiles will be displayed.

Name: kDisplayLocking
Documentation: Enable Display Locking JavaScript APIs.

Name: kSplitTabStrip
Documentation:
Splits pinned and unpinned tabs into separate TabStrips.
https://crbug.com/1346019

Name: kDisallowManagedProfileSignout
Documentation: Disables signout for enteprise managed profiles

Name: kNtpPhotosModuleSoftOptOut
Documentation: If enabled, Google Photos opt-in card will show a button to soft opt-out.

Name: kMantaService
Documentation:
This flag is used for enabling the Manta Service, a profile keyed service for
the google chrome Manta project.

Name: kSitePerProcess
Documentation:
Alternative to switches::kSitePerProcess, for turning on full site isolation.
Launch bug: https://crbug.com/810843.  This is a //chrome-layer feature to
avoid turning on site-per-process by default for *all* //content embedders
(e.g. this approach lets ChromeCast avoid site-per-process mode).

TODO(alexmos): Move this and the other site isolation features below to
browser_features, as they are only used on the browser side.

Name: kFontSrcLocalMatching
Documentation:
Enables fixes for matching src: local() for web fonts correctly against full
font name or postscript name. Rolling out behind a flag, as enabling this
enables a font indexer on Android which we need to test in the field first.

Name: kOnBeginFrameThrottleVideo
Documentation:
if enabled, Any CompositorFrameSink of type video that defines a preferred
framerate that is below the display framerate will throttle OnBeginFrame
callbacks to match the preferred framerate.

Name: kWebAuthnICloudKeychain
Documentation: Enable support for iCloud Keychain

Name: kEnableMachineLearningModelLoaderWebPlatformApi
Documentation:
Enables the Machine Learning Model Loader Web Platform API. Explainer:
https://github.com/webmachinelearning/model-loader/blob/main/explainer.md

Name: kTracingServiceInProcess
Documentation:
The features should be documented alongside the definition of their values
in the .cc file.

Name: kHideDelegatedFrameHostMac
Documentation:
On mac, when the RenderWidgetHostViewMac is hidden, also hide the
DelegatedFrameHost. Among other things, it unlocks the compositor frames,
which can saves hundreds of MiB of memory with bfcache entries.

Name: kAutofillDetectRemovedFormControls
Documentation:
If enabled, whenever form controls are removed from the DOM, the ChromeClient
is informed about this. This enables Autofill to trigger a reparsing of
forms.

Name: kOriginTrialsSampleAPIThirdPartyAlternativeUsage
Documentation:
Sample field trial feature for testing alternative usage restriction in
origin trial third party tokens.

Name: kOriginAgentClusterDefaultWarning
Documentation:
This flag enables a console warning in cases where document.domain is set
without origin agent clustering being explicitly disabled.
(This is a transitory behaviour on the road to perma-enabling
kOriginAgentClusterDefaultEnabled above.)

Name: kIPHDummyGroup
Documentation: A feature to ensure all arrays can contain at least one group.

Name: kJourneysZeroStateFiltering
Documentation: Enables filtering of the zero-state Journeys WebUI.

Name: kContextMenuSaveVideoFrameAs
Documentation: Enables the "Save Video Frame As" context menu item.

Name: kZeroSuggestPrefetchingOnSRP
Documentation: Enables prefetching of the zero prefix suggestions for eligible users on SRP.

Name: kAutofillRemoveInaccessibleProfileValuesOnStartup
Documentation:
Removes setting-inaccessible field types from existing profiles on startup.
TODO(crbug.com/1300548): Cleanup when launched.

Name: kPreloadingHeuristicsMLModel
Documentation:
If enabled, the machine learning model will be employed to predict the next
click for speculation-rule based pre-loadings.

Name: kRustyQrCodeGeneratorFeature
Documentation:
Exposing the feature so that tests can inspect it and turn it on/off,
but product code should instead use `IsRustyQrCodeGeneratorFeatureEnabled`.

Name: kAboutThisSiteAsyncFetching
Documentation:
Enables usage of the async fetching method for cacao and caching fetched
metadata in a TabHelper.

Name: kFillingAcrossAffiliatedWebsitesAndroid
Documentation:
Enables filling password on a website when there is saved password on
affiliated website.

Name: kV8MidtierRegallocFallback
Documentation:
The currently enabled fallback to the mid-tier register allocator for huge
Wasm functions. We want to remove this fallback in the future.

Name: kV8OptimizeJavascript
Documentation: Enables optimization of JavaScript in V8.

Name: kWebAppManifestLockScreen
Documentation:
Controls parsing of the "lock_screen" dictionary field and its "start_url"
entry in web app manifests.  See explainer for more information:
https://github.com/WICG/lock-screen/
Note: the lock screen API and OS integration is separately controlled by
the content feature `kWebLockScreenApi`.

Name: kCacheStorageCodeCacheHintHeader
Documentation:
When enabled allows the header name used in the blink
CacheStorageCodeCacheHint runtime feature to be modified.  This runtime
feature disables generating full code cache for responses stored in
cache_storage during a service worker install event.  The runtime feature
must be enabled via the blink runtime feature mechanism, however.

Name: kUseTaskRunnerForMojoAudioDecoderService
Documentation:
Feature flag to run the MojoAudioDecoderService in a sequence different than
the other mojo media services. On some Android devices, MediaCodec may block
the thread which leads to frequent audio decoder underrun in renderer.
Running the audio decoder in a separate sequence can improve the performance.
Note: running audio decoder in a separate thread/sequence will cause
multithread access to mojo media services. For Android audio decoder, the
thread safety is easier to guarantee because:
  1. The audio decoder and most of the other mojo media services don't cross
  reference each other.
  2. The only exception is CDM so we use a lock inside MojoCdmServiceContext
  for thread safety.

Name: kRemoteResourceCache
Documentation:
If enabled, renderers look for cached resources from another renderer
that has the same process isolation policies. Note that renderers don't
use cached resources in other rendereres yet, just record histograms.
See https://crbug.com/1414262

Name: kDOMContentLoadedWaitForAsyncScript
Documentation:
If enabled, DOMContentLoaded will be fired after all async scripts are
executed.

Name: kServiceWorkerBypassFetchHandler
Documentation:
Enables bypassing the service worker fetch handler. Unlike
`kServiceWorkerSkipIgnorableFetchHandler`, this feature starts the service
worker for subsequent requests.

Name: kKalmanHeuristics
Documentation: Enables changing the influence of acceleration based on change of direction.

Name: kPageInfoAboutThisSite
Documentation:
Controls the feature for English and other languages that are enabled by
default. Use IsAboutThisSiteFeatureEnabled() to check a specific language.

Name: kGlobalMediaControlsPictureInPicture
Documentation: Show picture-in-picture button in Global Media Controls.

Name: kUseUtilityThreadGroup
Documentation:
Under this feature, a utility_thread_group will be created for
running USER_VISIBLE tasks.

Name: kV8NoReclaimUnmodifiedWrappers
Documentation: Disables reclaiming of unmodified wrappers objects.

Name: kBlockInstallPromptIfIgnoreRecently
Documentation:
When enabled, the web app install prompt will be block on the site if
user ignored the prompt recently. The number of days the prompt will be
blocked is controlled by feature |kAppBannerTriggering| with params
|days_after_ignore|.

Name: kLowLatencyCanvas2dImageChromium
Documentation:
Enables the use of GpuMemoryBuffer images for low latency 2d canvas.
TODO(khushalsagar): Enable this if we're using SurfaceControl and GMBs allow
us to overlay these resources.

Name: kAttributionReportingInBrowserMigration
Documentation:
Enables attribution reporting to be proxied via the browser process using the
same path as other fetch keepalive requests.
See https://crbug.com/1374121.

Name: kVisualFeaturesSizes
Documentation:
Controls the behavior of visual features in CSD pings. This feature is
checked for the final size of the visual features and the minimum size of
the screen.

Name: kUpdateBrowserControlsWithoutProxy
Documentation:
Updating browser controls state will IPC directly from browser main to the
compositor thread. Previously this proxied through the renderer main thread.

Name: kReportOmniboxOnDeviceSuggestionsHeader
Documentation:
Whether to enable reporting the header. Included as a quick escape hatch in
case of crashes.

Name: kIncreaseBufferCountForHighFrameRate
Documentation: Increase number of buffers and pipeline depth for high frame rate devices.

Name: kAutomaticLazyFrameLoadingToEmbeds
Documentation:
Apply lazy-loading to frames which have embeds likely impacting Core Web
Vitals.

Name: kWebRtcApmDownmixCaptureAudioMethod
Documentation:
When enabled, overrides the Audio Processing Module parameter that controls
how multi-channel capture audio is downmixed to mono (when downmixing is
needed).

Name: kWebAuthnScreenReaderMode
Documentation:
A webauthn UI mode that detects screen readers and makes the dialog title
focusable.

Name: kIsolateSandboxedIframes
Documentation:
Allow process isolation of iframes with the 'sandbox' attribute set. Whether
or not such an iframe will be isolated may depend on options specified with
the attribute. Note: At present, only iframes with origin-restricted
sandboxes are isolated.

Name: kMemoryCacheStrongReference
Documentation:
Keep strong references in the blink memory cache to maximize resource reuse.
See https://crbug.com/1409349.

Name: kV8ShortBuiltinCalls
Documentation: Enables short builtin calls feature.

Name: kAllowRTCEncodedVideoFrameSetMetadataAllFields
Documentation: Allow all fields to be set when calling RTCEncodedVideoFrame.setMetadata.

Name: kDeprecateUnload
Documentation:
Enables unload handler deprecation via Permissions-Policy.
https://crbug.com/1324111

Name: kSafeBrowsingLookupMechanismExperiment
Documentation:
Controls whether the lookup mechanism experiment is enabled, which runs all
three lookup mechanisms instead of just real-time URL lookups for ESB users.
The other two lookup mechanisms are run in the background, and the results
of the three are logged for comparison purposes. This experiment is also
known as the hash-prefix real-time lookup experiment, since that mechanism is
the main comparison anchor.

Name: kGroupingFrameworkForZPS
Documentation:
Features that affect the "twiddle" step of AutocompleteController, e.g.,
deduping or `SortAndCull()`.

Name: kBlockPromptsIfIgnoredOften
Documentation:
Enables or disables whether permission prompts are automatically blocked
after the user has ignored them too many times.

Name: kV8SlowHistogramsCodeMemoryWriteProtection
Documentation:
Multiple finch experiments might use slow-histograms. We introduce
separate feature flags to circumvent finch limitations.

Name: kAutofillAddressProfileSavePromptNicknameSupport
Documentation:
TODO(crbug.com/1135188): Remove this feature flag after the explicit save
prompts for address profiles is complete.
When enabled, address profile save problem will contain a dropdown for
assigning a nickname to the address profile. Relevant only if the
AutofillAddressProfileSavePrompt feature is enabled.

Name: kSafeBrowsingNewGmsApiForBrowseUrlDatabaseCheck
Documentation: Use new GMSCore API for hash database check on browser URLs.

Name: kRevokeNotificationsPermissionIfDisabledOnAppLevel
Documentation:
Feature flag to revoke site-level Notifications permissions and FCM
registration.

Name: kAppStoreBilling
Documentation:
Used to control whether the invoking TWA can handle payments for app store
payment method identifiers.

Name: kUseMultiPlaneFormatForHardwareVideo
Documentation:
Enables creating single shared image and mailbox for multi-planar formats for
hardware video decoders.

Name: kViewportSegments
Documentation:
Enable the viewport segments API.
Tracking bug for enabling viewport segments API: https://crbug.com/1039050.

Name: kGlobalMediaControlsAutoDismiss
Documentation: Auto-dismiss global media controls.

Name: kNetworkServiceInProcess
Documentation: If the network service is enabled, runs it in process.

Name: kCustomizeChromeSidePanelExtensionsCard
Documentation:
If enabled, shows an extension card within the Customize Chrome Side
Panel for access to the Chrome Web Store extensions.

Name: kRestartNetworkServiceUnsandboxedForFailedLaunch
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, the network service will restart unsandboxed if
a previous attempt to launch it sandboxed failed.

Name: kLoadingPredictorUseLocalPredictions
Documentation:
All features in alphabetical order. The features should be documented
alongside the definition of their values in the .cc file.

Name: kSharingOfferKeyPairRead
Documentation: Kill switch to read sharing-offer related keys.

Name: kClearClientCertsOnExtensionReport
Documentation:
Feature flag to clear cached client certificates for given URLs when
the private enterprise.reportingPrivate.getCertificate extension API
is invoked.

Name: kEnableServiceWorkersForChromeUntrusted
Documentation: Enables service workers on chrome-untrusted:// urls.

Name: kPushSubscriptionChangeEvent
Documentation:
Fires the `pushsubscriptionchange` event defined here:
https://w3c.github.io/push-api/#the-pushsubscriptionchange-event
for subscription refreshes, revoked permissions or subscription losses

Name: kNoPreserveLastMutation
Documentation:
When enabled, LayerTreeImpl will not preserve the last mutation. This map
of the last mutated value should not be necessary as animations are always
ticked after the commit which should restore their animated values. Removing
this should improve performance and reduce technical complexity.

Name: kWebAuthnPinRequiredMeansNotRecognized
Documentation: Count kCtap2ErrPinRequired as meaning not recognised.

Name: kEnableAndroidGamepadVibration
Documentation: Enables gamepad vibration on Android 12+.

Name: kBlinkHeapIncrementalMarkingStress
Documentation:
Enables a marking stress mode that schedules more garbage collections and
also adds additional verification passes.

Name: kRTCOfferExtmapAllowMixed
Documentation:
Determines if the SDP attrbute extmap-allow-mixed should be offered by
default or not. The default value can be overridden by passing
{offerExtmapAllowMixed:false} as an argument to the RTCPeerConnection
constructor.

Name: kInterestGroupStorage
Documentation: Backend storage + kill switch for Interest Group API origin trials.

Name: kEvictSubtree
Documentation: enabled by default

Name: kWebAuthnEnclaveAuthenticator
Documentation: Enable use of a cloud enclave authenticator service.

Name: kCreateShortcutIgnoresManifest
Documentation:
When the user clicks "Create Shortcut" in the dot menu, the current page is
used as start-url, instead of the manifest-supplied value.
This allows subpages of web apps to be bookmarked via shortcuts
separately from their parent app.
For installing the parent app, the existing "Install Site" should be used
instead. With this feature, "Install Site" now also shows up for websites
without service worker, as long as they have a manifest.

Name: kOverscrollHistoryNavigationSetting
Documentation: Setting to control overscroll history navigation.

Name: kUserLevelMemoryPressureSignal
Documentation: Enables user level memory pressure signal generation on Android.

Name: kCertificateTransparency
Documentation: Enables Certificate Transparency

Name: kAutofillUpstreamAllowAdditionalEmailDomains
Documentation:
When enabled, Chrome allows credit card upload to Google Payments if the
user's email domain is from a common email provider (thus unlikely to be an
enterprise or education user).

Name: kBackForwardTransitions
Documentation: Enable showing a page preview during back/forward navigations.

Name: kAdaptiveSuggestionsCount
Documentation: Suggestions UI - these affect the UI or function of the suggestions popup.

Name: kPageInfoAboutThisSiteMoreLangs
Documentation: Controls the feature for languages that are not enabled by default yet.

Name: kHttpsFirstModeV2ForTypicallySecureUsers
Documentation:
Enables HTTPS-First Mode for typically secure users. No-op if
HttpsFirstModeV2 or HTTPS-Upgrades is disabled.

Name: kSafeBrowsingOnUIThread
Documentation: Run Safe Browsing code on UI thread.

Name: kUsernameFirstFlowFallbackCrowdsourcing
Documentation:
Enables support of sending additional votes on username first flow. The votes
are sent on single password forms and contain information about preceding
single username forms.
TODO(crbug.com/959776): Clean up if the main crowdsourcing is good enough and
we don't need additional signals.

Name: kWebAssemblyMultipleMemories
Documentation:
Enable support for multiple memories according to the multi-memory proposal:
https://github.com/WebAssembly/multi-memory. See
https://chromestatus.com/feature/5106389887746048.

Name: kAutofillAllowNonHttpActivation
Documentation:
Controls whether autofill activates on non-HTTP(S) pages. Useful for
automated tests with data URLS in cases where it's too difficult to use the
embedded test server. Generally avoid using.

Name: kClientHintsPrefersReducedTransparency
Documentation: Enable `sec-ch-prefers-reduced-transparency` client hint.

Name: kSpecCompliantCanPlayThrough
Documentation: CanPlayThrough issued according to standard.

Name: kAutofillEnableSupportForHonorificPrefixes
Documentation:
Controls whether honorific prefix is shown and editable in Autofill Settings
on Android, iOS and Desktop.
TODO(crbug.com/1141460): Remove once launched.

Name: kPaymentHandlerAlwaysRefreshIcon
Documentation:
If enabled, the web-app manifest for already-installed service-worker apps
will always be refetched for every Payment Request, in order to potentially
refresh the icon for the app.

Name: kMojoRecordUnreadMessageCount
Documentation:
Enables measurement of MessageChannel unread message counts. When enabled, a
small random selection of Connectors enable the unread message count quota
on their associated message pipe, and record the highest unread message count
seen during the Connector's lifetime.

Name: kShouldAllowFirstPartyStorageKeyOverrideFromEmbedder
Documentation:
Kill switch for creating first-party StorageKeys in
RenderFrameHostImpl::CalculateStorageKey for frames with extension URLs.

Name: kForceFieldTrialSetupCrashForTesting
Documentation:
A testing feature that forces a crash during field trial creation
on developer and test builds.

Name: kClientHintsDPR
Documentation: Enable `sec-ch-dpr` client hint.

Name: kDelegateTransforms
Documentation: Allows delegating transforms over Wayland when it is also supported by Ash.

Name: kCanvasOopRasterization
Documentation: Enables the use of out of process rasterization for canvas.

Name: kSuppressDifferentOriginSubframeJSDialogs
Documentation:
Disallows window.{alert, prompt, confirm} if triggered inside a subframe that
is not same origin with the main frame.

Name: kAutofillSuggestionsForAutocompleteUnrecognizedFieldsOnMobile
Documentation:
When enabled, the keyboard accessory is shown for autocomplete=unrecognized
fields. Selecting a keyboard accessory suggestion will fill the triggering
field (independently of the autocomplete attribute) and all
autocomplete != unrecognized fields in the triggering field's section.
Note that this only affects address fields, since credit cards already ignore
autocomplete=unrecognized.
TODO(crbug.com/1446318): Remove when launched.

Name: kDisruptiveNotificationPermissionRevocation
Documentation:
Enables notification permission revocation for origins that may send
disruptive notifications.

Name: kDigitalGoodsApi
Documentation:
Controls whether the Digital Goods API is enabled.
https://github.com/WICG/digital-goods/

Name: kRequireHdcpKeyProvisioning
Documentation:
A temporary flag to require Content Protection to use provisioned key as the
kernel doesn't expose that it requires this yet.(b/112172923)

Name: kVisualSearchSuggestionsAgent
Documentation:
Enables triggering visual search capabilities from renderer agent.
This flag is mainly used to test the model download mechanism and guard
against breakages from pushing new models to production.

Name: kAutofillGranularFillingAvailable
Documentation:
Controls whether granular filling will be available in the autofill popup.
TODO(crbug.com/1459990): Clean up when launched.

Name: kV8PerContextMarkingWorklist
Documentation: Enables per-context marking worklists in V8 GC.

Name: kUseDnsHttpsSvcbAlpn
Documentation: Update protocol using ALPN information in HTTPS DNS records.

Name: kDownloadBubbleV2
Documentation:
The V2 of the download bubble, consisting of features that were not available
on the download shelf. This is only eligible to be enabled when
kDownloadBubble is already enabled.

Name: kFillingAcrossGroupedSites
Documentation:
This flag enables password filling across grouped websites. Information about
website groups is provided by the affiliation service.

Name: kPauseBackgroundMutedAudio
Documentation: Pauses muted (and uncaptured) playbacks in the background.

Name: kNtpHistoryClustersModuleEnableContentClustering
Documentation:
If enabled, the History clsuters module will enable content clustering for
the displayed clusters.

Name: kEnforceNonceChecking
Documentation:
Enforce nonce checking when enabled.
If disabled, the nonce value returned from the device is not checked against
the one sent to the device. As a result, the nonce can be empty and omitted
from the signature. This allows backwards compatibility with legacy Cast
receivers.

Name: kDefaultBucketUsesRelaxedDurability
Documentation:
Changes the hard-coded durability for default buckets to relaxed. This only
affects IndexedDB.

Name: kImageCacheNoCache
Documentation: Whether images marked "no-cache" are cached. When disabled, they are.

Name: kClientHintsSaveData
Documentation: Enable `save-data` client hint.

Name: kAutofillConsiderPhoneNumberSeparatorsValidLabels
Documentation:
If enabled, label inference considers strings entirely made up of  '(', ')'
and '-' as valid labels.
TODO(crbug.com/1311937): Cleanup when launched.

Name: kRetryLanguageDetection
Documentation:
When enabled, language detection is attempted when the page finishes loading
if no page content is captured when parsing completes.

Name: kAutofillEnablePaymentsMandatoryReauth
Documentation:
When enabled, in use-cases where we would not have triggered any user-visible
authentication to autofill payment methods, we will trigger a device
authentication.

Name: kReadingListEnableDualReadingListModel
Documentation:
Feature flag that controls a technical rollout of a new codepath that doesn't
itself cause user-facing changes but sets the foundation for later rollouts
namely, `kReadingListEnableSyncTransportModeUponSignIn` below).

Name: kOmniboxSteadyStateTextColor
Documentation:
If enabled, Omnibox "steady state" text color is updated to match CR23
guidelines.
